title: corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease an 8-inch square baking pan or a 10-inch iron skillet. Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir in corn meal.
In a medium size bowl, beat egg with a fork just enough to blend yolk and white.
Stir milk and shortening into egg. Add dry ingredients and stir to blend thoroughly.
Beat just until smooth.
Pour into greased pan and bake about 25 minutes.

title: cashew pork stir-fry
directions: Cut pork tenderloin into thin strips.
Set aside.
Combine next 6 ingredients, stirring well.
Heat one tablespoon oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add carrots and celery, stir-frying about 3 minutes.
Remove vegetables; set aside.
Pour remaining tablespoon oil into skillet.
Add pork, stir-frying about 3 minutes.
Return vegetables to pan; add orange juice mixture and cashews.
Cook, stirring constantly over medium-high heat, until thickened.
Serve over hot rice, if desired.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and cool.
Add dressing and 1/2 bottle salad seasoning.
Cut up vegetables small and add.
Let stand overnight. Tomato may be added just before serving.

title: simple salisbury steak
directions: In large bowl, mix 1/4 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, onion and egg.
Shape into 6 patties.
In a 10-inch skillet on medium high heat, cook 1/2 patties in hot oil until brown on both sides. Remove and set aside.
Repeat with rest of patties.
In same skillet, combine remaining soup and mushrooms.
Heat to boiling. Return patties to skillet.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; cook for 20 minutes, or until patties are done, stirring occasionally.

title: crab dip
directions: Drain crab meat.
Add to bowl with cream cheese, mayo and pepper (dash).
Mix well.

title: calico beans(main dish)
directions: Brown meat with onion; drain.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: filled sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Sift dry ingredients and stir into creamed mixture together with milk.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with large cookie cutter.
Place 1 teaspoon mincemeat in center of each cookie.
(I use None Such mincemeat by Borden which comes in a jar.)
Fold cookies in half.
Seal edges with fork.
Bake in moderate 350° oven for about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients, beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour sweet potato mixture in pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 35 minutes. Place foil on edges if pastry is browning too much.
Cool completely.
Garnish pie with whipped topping and pecans, if desired.

title: chili cheese nachos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Warm chili in boiler or microwave. Place tortilla chips on bread pan.
Top with cheeses.
Put in oven until cheeses are melted.
Remove and top with chili and peppers to taste.
Serve hot with sour cream.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Boil for five minutes the oleo, brown sugar and white corn syrup.
Remove from heat and add salt, vanilla and baking soda. Pour over popcorn.
Stir to mix.
Bake at 250° for 40 minutes. Stir about twice while in the oven.
Cool on wax paper.
Break apart.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: You will need an 8-inch square baking pan.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare 1 large package of vanilla instant pudding as package directions indicate.
Blending at low speed, add Cool Whip and 1/2 of the sour cream container.
Beginning with vanilla wafers, then sliced bananas and pudding, layer until finishing with a layer of vanilla wafers for topping.
Enjoy!

title: chex after school mix
directions: Place cereal in a large bowl. Set aside.
In a small saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate morsels, peanut butter and margarine until smooth. Stir often.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla. Pour over cereal, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated. Place cereal mixture on sugar in large paper bag.
Shake until all pieces are well coated.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 9 cups.

title: chicken vegetable casserole
directions: Place frozen vegetables in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Beat eggs, then add eggs to mayonnaise, cream of mushroom soup and chopped onion.
Pour this mixture over vegetables.
Place layer of chicken (turkey or ham) over soup mixture.
Sprinkle grated cheese over and top with Stove Top dressing which has been moistened with 3/4 to 1 cup melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; remove from oven and cover with foil for another 10 to 15 minutes.
(Foil keeps dressing from getting too hard.)

title: swedish cream
directions: Mix together the cream, sugar and gelatin.
Heat gently and stir until gelatin is completely dissolved.
Cool until slightly thickened.
Fold in sour cream and vanilla.
Chill in refrigerator until firm.
Spoon into serving dishes and top with sweetened fruit or berries.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Boil broccoli in water until soft.
Mash with a potato masher. Add milk, chicken broth and salt, pepper and margarine (optional) and heat.
Thicken with flour and water mixture to desired consistency.
Better second day.

title: walnut creme cheese bonbons
directions: Soften the cream cheese.
Blend with a little cream.
Add chopped walnuts.
Roll into small balls and chill.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients together well until well mixed. Stir the oil, eggs and vanilla until mixed, then pour into dry ingredients; mix well. Add the apples and pecans and mix.
Pour into oblong pan, approximately 9 x 16-inches, greased and floured, and bake 45 to 55 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot water to dissolve.
Add frozen orange juice and cold water and juice from the can of oranges.
Let partially set.
Add Mandarin oranges and bananas.
Serves 6.

title: chopstick tuna
directions: Mix soup and water.
Add 1 cup noodles, dash of pepper and rest of ingredients.
Stir.
Turn into casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining noodles atop.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until hot.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Serve as dip for fresh vegetables.
Our favorites are carrots, celery, cauliflower, cucumbers, broccoli, radishes, raw squash, zucchini and mushrooms.

title: mrs. dash chili
directions: In medium saucepan, combine first 5 ingredients.
Simmer over medium heat for 5 to 10 minutes.
Garnish with grated cheese and onions if desired.
Serves 4.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Dust meat in flour, salt and pepper mixture.
Brown meat quickly in oil. Add all remaining ingredients, except sour cream.
Simmer until meat is tender. Stir sour cream into meat mixture.
Heat until bubbly. Serve over rice.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add egg yolks. Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla. Add soda and mix well. Add coconut.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased and floured angel food or Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 290° for about 2 hours. Cool before removing from pan. Stays moist for several days, or can be frozen for future use real well.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook hamburger and onion in skillet.
Add rest of ingredients and cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Saut onions and green peppers in 2 tablespoons oil until soft in large skillet. Add 2 tablespoons oil and brown ground beef. Stir in canned tomatoes, tomato paste, enchilada sauce mix, water and beans. Lower heat and simmer 10 minutes.

title: nutty brussels sprouts
directions: In saucepan, bring 1-inch water to a boil.
Place steamer rack or metal colander in saucepan and add sprouts and carrots.
Cover and steam 6 to 8 minutes.
In medium skillet, melt margarine.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add walnuts and cook, stirring frequently, until brown.
Stir in sprouts, carrots, salt and cinnamon.
Toss until well coated.

title: rice with mushrooms(slow cooker)
directions: Add soup to butter and heat.
Add rice to soup mixture and cook until juice is absorbed.

title: white wash
directions: Mix this real good and it is real good for fences or buildings.

title: easy pocket pizzas
directions: Cut each pita bread round in half crosswise to form 2 pockets. Spread 2 tablespoons pizza sauce inside each pita half.
Arrange about 6 pepperoni slices inside each half.
Divide Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses evenly among pockets.

title: angel gingerbread
directions: Mix ingredients together, then add 1 cup boiling water.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook onions and zucchini; drain.
Combine soup and sour cream. Stir in carrots; fold in zucchini and onions.
Combine stuffing mix and oleo and spread 1/2 of stuffing mix on bottom of 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.
Spoon remaining stuffing over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tolerene
directions: Sauce:
Fry onion, garlic and pepper in 2 tablespoons oil until lightly browned.
Add tomatoes and simmer.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: First
make
your regular meat loaf the way your family likes. If you
use tomato sauce or ketchup, stop.
Substitute 8 ounces of pizza sauce and bake as normal.	When meat loaf is cool, slice 1/4
to
1/2-inch
slices;	arrange
on flat tray. cover with remaining
sauce.
Heat
until
warm;
add	cheese. Turn to broil and
watch	for
cheese
to melt.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: scallops and bacon
directions: Wash scallops.
Wrap with bacon; secure with toothpick.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Broil for about 10 minutes.
Great snack food.

title: foolproof biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Add buttermilk, stir together. Add enough flour until it is not sticky.
Roll out and cut.
Bake on greased pan at 400 degrees until light brown (about 10-12 minutes).

title: taco bean casserole
directions: Brown and drain beef. Add beans, soup, tomatoes and season with chili powder. Mix well. Layer crushed chips on bottom of 9 x 13; top with beef mixture and top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot through and cheese melted.

title: wacky chocolate cake(bake auction)
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Make 3 holes in dry batter.
Put butter in first hole, vinegar in second hole and vanilla in third hole.
Pour water over and mix until wet.
Don't beat!
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes one 8 or 9-inch layer.
Double amounts for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Combine crumbs, 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese, oregano, garlic and pepper.
Coat chicken in this mixture.
Arrange chicken pieces in a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Turn pieces over; bake 20 minutes longer.
Blend soup and milk together; pour over chicken.
Top with remaining 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Bake an additional 20 minutes.

title: strawberry pineapple-ade
directions: Put all ingredients in punch bowl; mix carefully (except strawberries).
Add ice cubes or ice ring.
Float strawberries atop.
Makes 15 (4 ounce) servings.

title: oriental pork steaks
directions: Cut pork into serving size pieces, brown in large skillet. add gravy mix, water, soy sauce, sugar and ginger, stirring to blend. cover and simmer for 30-40 minutes, until tender, and well done.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve sugar, salt and shortening in boiling water; cool. Dissolve yeast in cup of warm water.
Mix yeast mixture, eggs and 6 cups of flour to sugar mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Place in refrigerator.
Cover with damp cloth and lid.
When ready to bake, remove what is needed.
Roll into desired shapes.
Place on greased pan.
Let rise 1 hour before baking.
Bake at 375° until lightly browned.
Will keep in refrigerator several days.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Boil hen.
Brown the beef.
Grind chicken, beef, onions and potatoes.
Cook until tender.
Add lima beans and corn (grind limas, if desired).
Cook for 3 to 4 hours.
Simmer on low, stirring often so as not to stick.
Yields 5 to 6 quarts.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, soup, water chestnuts, mayonnaise, onion and cheese together.
Pour into casserole dish.
Melt oleo; pour over crushed crackers.
Top the casserole with crackers-oleo mixture. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: asparagus soup
directions: After draining juice from asparagus, snip off the tip ends and save.
Mix milk and rice flour.
Gradually add bouillon and bring to a boil.
Add asparagus chunks.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Add cream, bring to a boil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Blend well in blender, then strain.
Add parsley and asparagus tips before serving.
After hot soup is helped in bowls, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: sandy's sauerkraut relish
directions: Drain sauerkraut, rinse with cold water and drain thoroughly. Combine sauerkraut and green pepper, celery and onion in bowl. Combine remaining ingredients, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Pour over vegetables and mix.
Cover and chill for 4 hours or overnight.
Great on hot dogs!

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, vegetables and soup together in bowl.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with other pie crust.
Make 2 to 3 slits in top crust and press edges together.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes, until light brown.

title: plum nutty cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in greased and floured tube pan for 60 minutes at 325°.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: lebanese bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Put 5 pounds flour, salt and oil in large pan.
Add dissolved yeast and lukewarm water.
Mix well and knead, turning over many times until smooth.
Cover with dry cloth and set in warm place about 1 1/2 to 2 hours until dough rises.
Cut in sections the size of an orange and roll between cupped hands.
Cover and allow to rise for 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 450°.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream the butter until light and fluffy. Blend in sugar and eggs, one at a time.
Continue beating until thoroughly blended. Stir dry ingredients and add alternately with mashed bananas.
Add vanilla.
Butter and flour a loaf pan and pour in the batter. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Test for doneness.
Cake will be very moist because of the bananas.

title: butter pecan cake
directions: Mix cake mix with liquid ingredients.
Blend in pudding mix and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Combine soups, mushrooms and sour cream.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add chicken breasts that have been cut in half.
Place in crock-pot.
Cook on low speed for 6 hours or on high for 4 hours.
Serve over bed of rice.
Serves 4.

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: Cream shortening and white sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix sugar with salad dressing and vinegar; add milk.
I use eggbeater to assure thoroughly mixed.
Cook macaroni until about half done; drain and rinse with hot water.
Mix all ingredients while macaroni is hot.
Cool in refrigerator overnight.
Mixture will be soupy but will thicken as it cools.
Makes a large bowl. This keeps in refrigerator for several days.

title: buffalo fire wings
directions: Fry unbreaded wings according to directions on the package. Melt margarine and stir in remaining ingredients.
Coat wings with sauce and bake 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve with celery sticks with Blue cheese salad dressing.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all, except corn flakes, and bake in a large flat pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: potato candy
directions: Mash potato while hot; add salt, butter and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Add sugar, gradually, stirring with spoon until mixture is pliable but not too stiff to roll out.
Place on waxed paper, flour and roll out.
Spread with peanut butter and roll up about the size of a quarter in diameter.
Cut 1/4 inch thick. Looks like pinwheels.

title: cranberry apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place gingersnaps and margarine in food processor.
Blend until finely ground.
Press mixture onto bottom and up side of 8-inch pie plate.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Blend in flour and salt.
Add broth all at once.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly. Add remaining ingredients.
Heat until bubbly.

title: low-fat stir-fry chicken
directions: Cut chicken into strips and cube tofu.
Mix soy sauce, cornstarch, sherry and garlic. Stir in chicken. Set aside for about 15 minutes. Add broth and vinegar. Heat wok or large skillet over high heat.
Spray with Pam. Add chicken and stir-fry 2 minutes. Remove chicken from wok and add remaining ingredients, except tofu. Cook 3 minutes. Add chicken and broth mixture and cook until sauce thickens.
Fold in tofu. Cook until warm.

title: bacon and tomato potato skins
directions: Scrub potatoes and prick with fork.
Microwave 100% power for 17 to 22 minutes or until tender (or bake in a 425° oven for 40 to 45 minutes).
Cool.
Halve each potato lengthwise.
Scoop out the inside of each potato half, leaving about a 1/4-inch thick shell. Cover and chill the leftover fluffy white part of potatoes for another use.
Combine the cooking oil, chili powder and hot pepper sauce.
With a pastry brush, brush insides of potato halves with the oil mixture.
Cut the potato halves in half lengthwise. Return to baking sheet.
Sprinkle potato quarters with bacon, tomato and green onion.
Top with cheese.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw out frozen spinach and squeeze out the water.
Mix the mayonnaise, sour cream, spinach, soup mix, chopped onion and chestnuts together in a bowl.
Purchase round sourdough bread, non-sliced.
Cut a hole in the middle and scoop mix into hole. Serve with sliced bread.

title: mustard glaze fruit
directions: Heat oven at 375°.
Melt butter; stir in brown sugar and mustard.
Heat and stir until boils, remove from heat and stir in fruit.
Pour in baking dish and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: blanche's stuffed peppers
directions: Cut off tops of peppers and save. Cut peppers in two, lengthwise. Wash and boil in salted water until a little soft. Carefully remove and set in rows in pan.
Let set until stuffing is made.

title: baked honey-glazed ham
directions: Make diagonal slits, 1/2 inch apart, halfway through ham to where knife touches bone.
Place ham in deep bowl and barely cover with water.
Stir in sugar.
Soak for at least 2 days in refrigerator.
Drain.

title: southern chocolate gravy
directions: Mix cocoa, flour and sugar in a pot with a fork or whisk until well blended. Add all other ingredients and bring to a boil, stirring constantly, over medium heat. Continue cooking until the gravy is the desired thickness. Serve hot over homemade biscuits with lots of butter. Great for breakfast.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large skillet, brown meat well while stirring.
Stir in onion soup mix, tomato sauce and water. Cover; simmer for 15 minutes.
In a 2-quart rectangular baking dish, alternate layers of noodles, meat sauce and cheese, ending with cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes, or until bubbling.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean (check in the middle of the cake), approximately 30 minutes.

title: hot salsa
directions: Devein and seed jalapenos. Set aside. Put peppers, onion, garlic and cilantro in food processor and chop well. Put tomatoes and vinegar in saucepan. Add chopped vegetables. Add jalapeno veins and seeds to desired hotness. (A little for mild or a lot for hot.) Add salt and bring to a boil. Remove from heat and cool to room temperature to serve.

title: crab delights fettucini
directions: Cook fettucini according to package directions, drain.
Heat butter and garlic in skillet on medium until garlic is lightly browned.
Add half and half, Crab Delights and pepper.
Heat about 3 minutes, or until mixture just begins to bubble, stirring occasionally.
Add Parmesan cheese; stir for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Toss Crab Delights sauce with fettuccini.
Serve immediately with additional Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Makes 4 (1 cup) servings.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Mix altogether and put in an 8 or 9-inch square pan or individual molds.
I add a little Knox gelatine to Jell-O.

title: mixed vegetable dijon
directions: Cook cauliflower in boiling water for 3 minutes.
Add broccoli and red pepper, cooking 30 seconds longer.
Drain.
In large nonstick skillet, cook onion in margarine until soft.
Add flour; cook, stirring, for 1 minute.
Gradually whisk in chicken broth and milk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook, whisking, 2 to 3 minutes, until sauce boils and thickens.
Pour over vegetables.

title: meat loaf(crockery cooking)
directions: Break bread into small pieces; soak in milk.
Pour into crock-pot with rest of ingredients.
Combine and knead until thoroughly mixed.
Shape into round loaf and cook on high 1 hour; drain off fat.
Turn heat to low and cook 5 or 6 hours more.
Turn off heat.
Let cool at least 20 minutes before serving.
Serve with tomato sauce or gravy.

title: elsie cobbler
directions: Cream the butter or oleo with sugar.
Mix in dry ingredients. Add milk.
Pour into greased baking pan (9 x 9-inch).
Top with berries or peaches; sprinkle sugar over.
Pour juice on top.
If using fresh fruit, add water instead of juice.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: creamy stuffed celery
directions: Cut celery into 3-inch pieces.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Stuff the celery pieces with cream cheese mixture. Yields 9 celery pieces.

title: chicken sopa
directions: Brown onions in butter; combine with soups, broth, chilies and chicken.
Mix well.
Place layer of tortillas in 9 x 11 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with layer of chicken mixture and then a layer of cheese.
Repeat all three layers until dish is filled, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: indian relish
directions: Grind tomatoes, peppers and onions; drain.
Mix all ingredients; bring to a boil.
Cook for 25 minutes.
Pour into hot pint jars; seal.
Yields 6 to 7 pints.

title: spicy black beans(original recipe)
directions: Place all ingredients in Dutch oven.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until beans are soft and liquid has reduced.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix and let stand 3 or 4 hours or overnight.
When ready to serve, add 1 large bottle of ginger ale and ice water to suit your taste.

title: spanish rice
directions: In a large skillet, heat the oil over medium heat.
Add beef, onions, green peppers and cook until meat is browned.
Drain liquid.

title: yum yum snack mix
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in a large bowl.
Put brown sugar, syrup and butter in a saucepan and boil for 5 minutes.
Add a dash of cream of tartar, salt and soda.
Pour over the cereal-nut mix and stir.
Spread out on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Stir a few times.

title: brownies *
directions: Melt shortening and chocolate.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Bake in greased pan at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.
Cut in squares.

title: tuna crunch casserole
directions: Blend soup and milk in a 1-quart casserole.
Blend and stir in tuna, eggs and peas.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with potato chips or chow mein noodles and bake 5 minutes longer. Makes 4 servings.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Put milk and marshmallows in top of double boiler. Cook until melted.
Pour over the rest of the mixture. Form a long loaf so it can be sliced as you serve it. Wrap in foil and keep in refrigerator.

title: shoepeg corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in baking dish, 9 x 13 x 2.

title: peach frozen yogurt
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over milk in a saucepan; let stand 1 minute. Cook over low heat stirring constantly until gelatin dissolves. Remove from heat, add sugar and salt, stirring until dissolved. Stir in yogurt, vanilla and peaches.
Cover and chill.
Pour yogurt mixture into ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: kiwi tropical punch
directions: Cut sherbet into large pieces in punch bowl.
Add kiwi juice drink and ginger ale in equal portions.
Add more as needed during serving.
Makes 25 to 30 servings.

title: creamy milk
directions: Pour
boiling
water
over dates.
Let stand 5 minutes. Blend smooth all except additional water.
When smooth, slowly add water and whiz.
Chill.

title: prairie chicken (comanche)(modern)
directions: Peel sweet potatoes; chop pecans.
Flour birds and season with salt and pepper.
Brown on all sides in hot lard.
Place birds in baking dish.
Add sweet potatoes.
Pour sorghum over and sprinkle with nuts.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in same pan; onion first, then add meat chopped up.
Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and place in casserole.
Add meat and onion mixture.
Add chopped green pepper and remaining ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.

title: chicken pilau (perlow)
directions: Place hen in a pot with ham or bacon slices.
Simmer until well done and remove the chicken from pot and keep warm.
Take 1 quart of fat stock.
Save for gravy.
Add enough water to make 3 cups.
Add 2 cups rice and simmer slowly until all liquid is absorbed.
Cut up the chicken and mash the eggs and mix with gravy.

title: sweetheart cookies
directions: Mix together softened butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks and the vanilla.
Slowly add flour.
Form into soft balls, then poke holes in the middle with your fingers.
Fill the hole with strawberry jam.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes.
When still warm, sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes 3 dozen.
Enjoy!!!!

title: spanish rice
directions: In frying pan brown rice in oil until rice is golden brown, stirring until done.
In saucepan add 2 cups water, bouillon cubes, tomato sauce and browned rice.
Bring to a rolling boil. Turn heat down to low. Cover with lid.
Cook for 20 minutes.

title: hello dollies
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt butter.
Sprinkle crumbs into pan.
Top with chips and coconut (layer it).
Pour milk over this.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until lightly browned.
Cut into bars.
Store at room temperature, lightly covered.
Chopped nuts can be added, if desired.

title: golden cream soup
directions: Combine potatoes, water, celery, carrots, onion, parsley, seasonings and bouillon cube.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until veggies are tender.
Gradually add milk to flour, stirring until well blended.
Add flour mixture to veggies.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens.
Add process cheese spread until melted.

title: three bean salad
directions: Combine beans, onion and parsley in large bowl.
Combine dressing, sugar and garlic.
Pour over bean mixture and toss. Cover; refrigerate at least 3 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: nichole's barbecue beef
directions: Cook in slow cooker 5 to 6 hours.

title: "smashed" apricots(serves 12)
directions: Layer as follows into a 3-quart casserole: butter, apricots, sugar and crackers.
Repeat.
Layer a total of 3 times.
Bake 1 hour at 300° until lightly browned and bubbly.
Good side dish with ham.

title: potatoes o'brien
directions: Boil potatoes in water 20 to 25 minutes, or until tender. Remove from heat and add cold water until potatoes are cooled slightly.
Peel and cut into 1-inch cubes.
In a large nonstick skillet, saute onions and green pepper in oil until tender.
Add potatoes and sprinkle with black pepper and paprika.
Cook over medium heat 10 minutes, or until potatoes are browned, stirring frequently.
Serve hot.
Makes 5 servings.

title: pink dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill and serve.

title: vegetables italiano
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. In large plastic food storage bag, combine crumbs and cheese. Shake and blend well. In another large plastic bag, combine mayonnaise and vegetables. Coat well. Add mayonnaise coated vegetables, half at a time, to crumb mixture; shake and coat well. Arrange in single layer on ungreased cookie sheet so pieces don't touch. Bake 10 minutes or until golden.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs and add milk and crumbs.
Add corn, onion, seasoning and melted butter.
Mix well and pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat up eggs!
Add sugar, Karo, pecans, and butter. Pour into pie shell; cook at 350 until firm.

title: roman ice
directions: Mix and boil; freeze overnight.
Cut into blocks, chip.
Like a slushy.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cover the bottom of a clear glass bowl with refrigerated whipped topping.
Add about 1/3 of the Oreo cookie crumbs, spreading them evenly over the topping.
Add the cherry pie filling.
Add another layer of topping and a layer of cookie crumbs.
Add one more layer of topping and the last of the cookie crumbs.
Top with whole Oreos.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours to allow flavors to harmonize and serve chilled.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: crab rangoon(hors d'oeuvres for 4 to 6)
directions: Thoroughly mix together.
Fill and wrap according to directions on won ton wrapper.
Fry for 2 to 3 minutes or until browned, as desired.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Chill milk.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add lemon juice.
Chill in refrigerator until it has consistency of egg whites.
Blend sugar, cheese and vanilla until smooth.
Whip milk until stiff.
Blend cheese and sugar mixture to the Jell-O.
Mix together with whipped mixture.

title: better blender cheese cake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and butter; mix well.
Press into bottom of pan.
Set aside.

title: deviled ham canapes
directions: Mix the deviled ham with the onions until smooth.
Spread on the toast; sprinkle with the cheese.
Place under a hot broiler until cheese melts.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each section of dough in 4 pieces.
Roll each piece in sugar and cinnamon mixture and place in Bundt pan.
Fill remaining mixture to 3/4 cup and add 1 cube butter (melted).
Spoon mixture over top of biscuits.
Place in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Turn over into a plate while warm.

title: edna's sweet dill pickles
directions: Slice
pickles;
do
not
peel.
Put
1 sprig dill or 1 tablespoon
dill seed in jars first, then pickles, followed by 1 clove
garlic.
Cold
pack to boiling.
Let set 1 hour.
Or boil 8 minutes and take off heat.

title: cyclone chili
directions: Heat lard in kettle.
Add meat about 1 pound at a time, removing after each pound is browned.
After all 4 pounds are browned, put onion and garlic in kettle and cook until soft. Return beef to kettle.
Rinse cactus pieces; drain and add to beef.
Add peppers, green tomatoes, tomato paste, beef stock, coriander, cumin, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer about 2 1/2 hours.
Makes about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: cream cheese pineapple torte
directions: Melt milk and marshmallows together on low heat. Add cream cheese. Add to mixture and melt. Cool. Then beat whipping cream and add to mixture.
Add pineapple. Mix all together and put in 9 x 12 graham cracker crust.

title: mussels ala marinara
directions: Coarsely chop tomatoes; set aside.
In large saucepot, heat oil over medium heat.
Add carrots, onions and garlic.
Saute for 3 to 4 minutes or until softened.
Add wine, tomatoes, salt and pepper and bring to a boil over high heat.
Add mussels, cover and cook 3 to 4 minutes or until they open.
(Discard any that do not open.) Serve this half-soup/half-stew in bowls over angel hair or linguini.
Serves 4.

title: english trifle
directions: Using a large clear glass bowl layer pound cake slices on bottom.
Sprinkle Grand Marnier on the pound cake.
Layer with fresh fruit in order listed.
Layer cake and fruit until 3 inches from top of bowl.
Add a layer of coconut cream pudding.
Then top with whipped cream.
Decorate with some fresh fruit.

title: homemade swiss steak
directions: Fry minute steak in pan until brown.
Drain fat.
Pour can of tomatoes on top of steak.
Add diced onions and green peppers. Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer on low for 30 minutes.

title: cracker candy
directions: Mix sugar and milk and bring to a boil. Let boil for 3 minutes, stirring to prevent burning. Remove from heat and add crackers, peanut butter, and vanilla. Beat until thick, pour into buttered pan and cut into squares after it sits.

title: stir-fry
directions: Take cubed beef and brown in skillet.
Slice the onion, mushrooms and bell pepper.
The mushrooms and pepper should be approximate size of beef cubes.
Leave onions in rings.
Once the beef is cooked to desired taste, remove any extra liquid that is remaining in the skillet.
Add vegetables to the top of the meat and add half a bottle of wine and cover.
Simmer until the vegetables are cooked, but firm.
Can be served with or without rice.
Chicken can be substituted for beef and different vegetables can be used depending on individual tastes.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Mix hamburger, oatmeal, onion, pepper, milk and salt and shape into balls.
Put in baking pan or dish.
Mix Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, brown sugar, onion, catsup and water.
Pour this mixture over meat balls.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.
These freeze good, so could be made ahead.

title: chess pie(club member: brandi cook)
directions: Beat eggs together well. Add other ingredients, one at a time. Mix well and pour into pie shell. Cook 1 hour in 325° oven.

title: "veggie" pizza
directions: Spray pizza pan with Pam.
Spread crescent rolls evenly, blending edges together to form 1 crust.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes (until it begins to brown).
Cool.

title: southern baked corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Mix thoroughly and spread in an ungreased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown on top.
Last few minutes of baking, sprinkle cheese on top and finish baking until cheese is melted.

title: short ribs with mustard sauce
directions: Heat butter or margarine in a large heavy skillet. Brown ribs, a few at a time, on all sides.
Lift to large heatproof casserole. Sprinkle with lemon peel and pepper.
Add pinch of thyme and bay leaves. Cover with boiling water.
Stir in mustard, mixing completely. Bring to a boil again.
Cover and simmer about 1 1/2 hours.
Lift ribs to heated platter and keep warm.
Mix 2 tablespoons flour with butter or margarine in skillet to
make gravy base, blending smoothly. Add to liquid in casserole, gradually, for a smooth sauce.
Bring to a boil and cook for a few minutes. Remove bay leaves.
Return ribs to sauce and bring to boiling point. Serve piping hot with rice or freshly boiled potatoes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together; drain.
Add cheese and butter. Put in casserole bowl and top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake until brown, about 20 minutes, at 400°.

title: key lime chiffon pie
directions: Mix pie filling with 1/2 cup sugar.
Gradually add water; stir in egg yolks.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring until mixture comes to a boil.
Blend beaten egg white mixture into pudding. Pour into cooled baked pie crust.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook to a soft ball stage and add peanut butter.
Do not stir. Cool to lukewarm, then beat until thickened.
Pour into buttered pan.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: grandma jagger's beef stew
directions: Brown beef with spices in hot oil.
(Tip:
Use your boiling pot; saves dishes.)
Drain.
Add vegetables and fill pot with water to 1 inch below top edge.
(Tip:
Don't boil over.)
Bring to a boil, then cook on low heat for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serves a small army and tastes great reheated.
Can be cooled and frozen for later.

title: broccoli hash brown quiche
directions: Press hash browns into a greased 9-inch glass pie plate. Add egg and sour cream mixture; add broccoli. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Roll into small meatballs, fry and drain.
Add cooked meatballs to sauce and put in a crock-pot on low.
Take to a party or gathering.

title: sausage au gratin
directions: In small mixing bowl, beat cheese spread and sour cream until smooth.
Add onion, parsley and salt.
Fold sauce and sausage into potatoes.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: delicious caesar salad dressing
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together well.
Then add other ingredients.
Chill and pour over fresh Romaine lettuce.

title: overnight layered salad
directions: Remove outer leaves and break cauliflower into flowerets. Wash thoroughly.
Layer lettuce, cauliflower and peas in 3 quart bowl (in that order).
Combine sour cream and mayonnaise, mixing well.
Spread evenly over top, sealing edge of bowl.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients in the order listed.
Cover bowl tightly and chill overnight.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: grammie's date pinwheels
directions: Cook dates, white sugar and water for 10 minutes;
chill filling.

title: skillet hash
directions: In a large skillet put potatoes, add just enough water to boil for about 10 minutes on medium heat. Then add corned beef, chopped in small pieces.
Add tomato sauce with 1 can of water.
Stir well.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Then simmer about 30 minutes or until potatoes are done and it has cooked down somewhat.
This also makes good open face sandwiches.

title: tortellini soup
directions: In a large pot, combine all ingredients.
Bring to a slow boil. Simmer gently until tortellini are done and vegetables are tender.
Delicious with garlic bread and salad!

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients for 1 minute. Add the remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper to cool. (You can add things like raisins, nuts, coconut, etc.)

title: mom's garlic pickles
directions: Take 4 to 5-inch cucumbers; put in cold water overnight.
Next morning, slice lengthwise and put in jars.
Add to each quart jar 1 head dill, 1 clove garlic, 1 piece celery and wedged onion. Boil sugar, vinegar, water and salt; pour hot over pickles and seal.

title: perfect pears
directions: Drain pears and reserve juice.
Arrange pears in baking dish, split side up.
Combine remaining ingredients with reserved juice and spoon onto pear halves.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Baste with juice.
Serves 4.

title: orange-pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake mix and bake according to package directions. Combine undrained pineapple, Cool Whip and instant pudding mix. Let stand 5 minutes.
Spread over cooled cake.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute the onion and margarine together.
Mix them with all of the other ingredients.
Top with grated cheese and bread crumbs (seasoned or plain).
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: ranch house chicken
directions: Take 2 c corn flakes and put in a zip lock bag. Crush them up. Coat each chicken breast with Ranch dressing, then roll in crushed corn flakes. Place coated chicken breast in a lightly greased shallow baking dish. Bake at 375 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: dictum ditty
directions: Saute the onion, green pepper and pimiento in the butter until onion is transparent.
Add the tomatoes and cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Add the well beaten eggs.
Cook until creamy. Serve over toast.

title: english trifle
directions: Put cake in bottom of a large crystal bowl.
Dissolve Jell-O in 3 cups of boiling water.
When partly set, add drained fruit cocktail.
Pour cocktail juice over cake.
Put Jell-O mixture over cake.
Place in refrigerator.
When set firmly, put pudding mixture on top of Jell-O.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Refrigerate.

title: dutch baby
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Heat cast-iron skillet.
Heat butter until it sizzles.
Blend flour, milk and eggs.
Pour into skillet. Bake for 13 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and lemon juice.
Serve hot with jam.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: delicious dinosaur eggs
directions: Step 1:
Gently tap the hard-cracked eggs all over until the shells crack.
Do not take the shells off the eggs.

title: kit kat bars
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with crackers.

title: half-time spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve compressed yeast in lukewarm water.
Combine sugar, salt, shortening and scalded milk.
Cool to lukewarm by adding cold water.
Blend in egg and yeast.
Add flour; mix until blended.
Place in bowl (cover).
Let rise in warm place 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add beaten eggs. Add combined dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Dissolve jello in cold water.
Cook pineapple and juice, sugar and lemon juice until steaming hot.
Add jello; put in refrigerator until almost set.
Add cheese, Cool Whip and nuts. Refrigerate until firm.

title: squash casserole
directions: Place squash in bowl and stir in butter, sugar, raisins and nuts.
Put in 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with marshmallows. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until heated through and marshmallows begin to brown.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Mix together.
Cook covered for 4 hours at 300°.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: spinach balls
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend and shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
When completely frozen, place in plastic bag until ready to bake.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: almond crescents
directions: Mix butter, 1/2 cup powdered sugar and flavorings.
Mix at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Turn to low and add flour and salt. Beat until smooth.
Add almonds and blend.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Shape into crescents.
Bake 8 minutes at 400°.
While warm, shake in bag of powdered sugar to coat.

title: yam-apple casserole
directions: Boil yams until tender.
Peel and cube.
Core apples and cut in 1/4-inch rings.
Mix sugar, margarine and pecans.
Let cook until thickened.
Place yams and apples in layers in casserole dish, which has been buttered.
Top with pecans and pour hot syrup over this.
Let cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: cranberry cheese bars(yields 24 bars)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, mix flour, oats, 3/4 cup sugar and margarine until crumbly.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups crumb mixture.
Press remainder firmly on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, in small bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice.
Spread evenly over prepared crust.
In small bowl, combine remaining tablespoon sugar and cornstarch and stir in cranberry sauce.
Spoon evenly over cheese layer.
Top with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake 40 minutes until golden.
Cool.
Chill.
Store chilled and covered.
Enjoy!

title: country-style cabbage
directions: Combine butter and salt in skillet; heat until butter melts. Add cabbage.
Cover and cook 5 to 6 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add light cream.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes longer or until heated through.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: raisin pie
directions: Add raisins to boiling water.
Cook until tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in mixture of sugar and flour.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Pour into 9-inch deep pie crust.
Cover with top crust.
Cut slits in top crust.
Bake until brown.
Serve slightly warm.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Cook vegetables and garlic in oil until tender.
Stir in sauce and oregano; simmer 15 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese.
In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer 1/2 each of the noodles, sauce, cottage cheese and Mozzarella.
Repeat layering.
Cover; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: giblet gravy(power level: medium, 50% and high, 100%)
directions: Pour drippings in 4-cup measure or 1-quart casserole. Microwave on High (100%) for 30 to 45 seconds until bubbly.
Mix together cornstarch, salt, pepper and water until smooth.
Stir into drippings.
Microwave on High (100%) for 4 to 6 minutes or until thickened.
Stir occasionally to prevent lumps.
Serve immediately over meat, potatoes or dressing.

title: petite cheesecake
directions: Put vanilla wafers in bottom of cupcake tins (use paper cups). Mix cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs and lemon juice; beat until smooth.
Pour over vanilla wafers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with pie filling.

title: mom's enchilada sauce
directions: Melt and blend shortening and flour.
Add rest of recipe and cook 15 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, salt and cornstarch together.
Cook until thick.
Add butter and beets and cook until beets are heated through.

title: shrimp and feta on linguine
directions: Saute shrimp and red pepper flakes in 2 tablespoons olive oil in large skillet until shrimp are pink.
Arrange shrimp in a baking dish (10 x 6 x 2-inch).
Sprinkle with crumbled Feta cheese.
Add remaining olive oil to skillet.
Saute garlic.
Add tomatoes and cook for 1 minute.
Stir in wine and the next 4 ingredients.
Pour over shrimp.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 375°.
Serve over pasta.
Serves 2.

title: italian sausage and zucchini stir-fry
directions: Brown meat. Add onion when nearly done. Drain.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese. Cook, uncovered, 5 minutes, stirring frequently. Remove. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Mix yeast, 1/4 cup sugar and warm water and set aside.
Mix flour, eggs, butter, shortening and remaining sugar.
Add yeast mixture, knead with dough hook for 5 minutes.
Cover in warm place for about 1 hour or until doubled.
Wrap dough around cheese for individual puffs.
Let rise, spread with butter, bake until golden brown and spread with butter again.

title: linda mini pizza
directions: Brown chuck, sausage, onion and pepper; drain well.
Add oregano and anis.
Cut Velveeta into chunks.
Add and stir until melted.
Spread on bread.
Bake in 350° oven 10 minutes.

title: 7-layer lettuce salad
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar; spread over the top.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Dice onions and saute.
Add ground chuck.
Stir to lightly cooked.
Add tomatoes, diced green pepper, salt, cheese and red pepper.
Cook until cheese melts.
Cook spaghetti in boiling salted water until tender.
Mix sauce and spaghetti together.
Lightly spray 3-quarts oblong dish.
Pour mixture into dish.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour covered with foil. Serve with tossed salad and garlic toast.

title: lemon-lime cookies
directions: Beat sugar and shortening until well blended.
Add lemon peel and lime juice.
Stir well.
Beat eggs.
Add to sugar mixture. Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Blend mixtures together.
Drop on greased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: baked stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 400° for one hour.
Cut slice from top of each.
Remove potatoes.
Mash potatoes while still warm.
Add enough milk to make potatoes smooth.
Add butter; stir in remaining ingredients.

title: marge's better than "anything" cake
directions: Mix everything together (except chocolate chips) for about 3 minutes.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: tuna fish and noodles
directions: Cook noodles and drain. In a 9 x 13 inch pan, mix mayonnaise, tuna, onion and salt and pepper (to taste). In a saucepan, mix soup and milk until creamy. Add cheese and cook over low heat until cheese is melted. Add noodles and soup mixture to tuna mix and mix well. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Blend in a blender for 3 minutes.
Pour in pie shell and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 small pies or 1 deep dish pie.

title: crab puffs
directions: *Zip seasoning is a medium hot combination of paprika, chili pepper, cumin, oregano, coriander, cayenne, and lemon seasonings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Blend all ingredients and fold in broccoli.
Place cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: hello dollys
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then mix and add all of the ingredients.
Bake on 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cut immediately!

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and mix until creamy. Serve with raw veggies.

title: tomato bread
directions: Chop broccoli, tomato and onion (uncooked); drain well. Melt butter
in
baking
pan.
Mix
ingredients
well, adding cheese. Pour
into
pan
over melted butter.
Bake at 275° or 300° for about
40 minutes in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. This bread freezes well and is good any time.

title: toast cake
directions: Roll Rusks fine and mix with sugar, cinnamon and melted butter.
Reserve
cup
of
this	mixture for the top.
Line buttered spring-form pan with remaining mixture.
(Spring-form pan to have hole in center.)

title: sesame chicken
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together to make marinade.
Put chicken pieces in the marinade and marinate at least 1/2 hour (it's best to make marinade in the morning - cover the dish and refrigerate until dinner for best flavor).

title: potato skins
directions: Prick potatoes with a fork.
Bake in a 425° oven for forty to fifty minutes or until tender.
Cut into quarters.
Scoop out the insides (reserve for another use), leaving 1/2-inch thick shells. Brush both sides of potato skins with margarine.

title: kentucky style roast venison
directions: Place roast in a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Pour the soup and water over roast.
Cover well with foil and bake at 325° for 2 or 3 hours until tender.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
I always double and it's a great way to use up those bananas.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients; form into meatballs.
Put on cookie sheet.
Mix the remainder of the ingredients; dip the meatballs into it.
Place back on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Heat Carnation milk, sweet milk and butter over low heat.
Mix together flour, sugar and salt.
Beat egg yolks slightly and add vanilla.
Combine sugar and egg mixtures.
Add this to heated milk and butter.
Stir and cook on low until thick.
Add 1 cup coconut. Put in baked 9-inch crust.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour boiling water over raisins and let stand.
Cream sugar and oil; add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Add vanilla.
Drain raisins.
Add with nuts and dates.
Mixture will be very stiff.
Spread in shallow pan (cookie sheet).
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Cut in squares and dust with powdered sugar.

title: ham and cheese bread
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions. Drain and cool. Roll each loaf of dough into a 15 x 10-inch rectangle. Place one in a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Sprinkle with broccoli, cheese and ham to within 1/2-inch of edges.
Place second rectangle on top, sealing edges.
Brush the top with butter; sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: yeast hush puppies
directions: Dissolve yeast in the half cup of water.
Combine meal, salt, flour and grated onion.
Add beaten egg, oil, milk and dissolved yeast.
Mix well.
Let stand 30 to 40 minutes.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil and cook until brown.

title: white sugar cookies
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and shortening.
Add baking powder, baking soda and flour.
Add milk and vanilla.
Roll and cut.
Bake at 375°.

title: chocolate cookies(soft)
directions: Melt shortening and chocolate in saucepan.
Cool 10 minutes. Stir in brown sugar.
Beat in egg, vanilla and milk or water. Sift together the dry ingredients and add to chocolate mixture. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Frost with any good chocolate frosting.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Chop or grate
cabbage.
Chop apples into small chunks. Add sugar, salt, black pepper and enough salad dressing to mix well. Sprinkle
paprika on top.
(This is an old recipe.
Mom used to make her own mayonnaise for this recipe.)

title: play dough
directions: Put into the dish in the order given; stir.
Add food coloring, if you wish.
Store, covered, in the refrigerator.

title: nacho sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add taco seasoning mix.
Add water and mix well.
Then add rest of ingredients.
Let simmer about 20 to 25 minutes (not necessary!).

title: parfaits
directions: Mix juice with fruit cocktail.
Spoon into parfait glasses every other layer vanilla ice cream and then the fruit mixture along with some juice.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
May garnish with a maraschino cherry, if desired.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer a short time before serving.

title: oven fried rice
directions: Mix.
Cover with foil.
Let cook for 1 hour and 5 minutes at 350°.
Do not touch until cooked.

title: asparagus with gruyere
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Break off tough ends of asparagus as far down as stalks snap easily.
Arrange in single layer in ungreased rectangular baking dish, 11 x 7 x 2-inch.
Sprinkle with salt. Cover with aluminum foil and bake about 25 minutes or until tender.
Heat margarine over low heat until light brown; drizzle over asparagus.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 5 to 8 minutes or just until cheese softens.

title: aunt clarine's hot chocolate
directions: Mix together and store in airtight container.
For 8 ounce cup of hot chocolate, mix 8 ounces of boiling water and 3 heaping spoonfuls of mix.

title: upside down pizza
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together. Drain grease. Add tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce mix. Let cook for 10 minutes. Put meat mixture in 9 x 1 dish. Spread sour cream over mixture and sprinkle cheese on top. Stretch crescent rolls on top. Use rolling pin to stretch rolls. Bake for 25-30 minutes or until rolls have browned.

title: corn casserole
directions: Use uncooked spaghetti, broken up.
Chop onions; dice cheese. Stir together all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, covered and 1/2 hour more, uncovered, and enjoy.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corn and flour with a wire whisk.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Bake in a buttered, large baking dish for 1 hour or until set, at 325°.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: yum yum date roll
directions: Reserve 1/4 cup cracker crumbs.
Combine remaining crumbs with marshmallows, dates and nuts.
Moisten with Pet milk and mix well. Form into a roll and roll in the remaining crumbs.
Wrap in wax paper, then foil and chill.
Slice and serve.

title: oatmeal crisps
directions: Cream Crisco and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Add flour to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats.
Mix well.
Drop teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: lemon layer cake
directions: Mix together and pat in a 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: sourdough starter
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm (105° to 115°) water.
Stir in 2 cups warm water, flour and sugar or honey.
Beat until smooth.
Cover bowl with cheesecloth and let stand at room temperature for 5 to 10 days or until mixture has a fermented aroma, stirring 2 to 3 times a day.
To store, transfer to a jar. Cover with cheesecloth and refrigerate.
Do not cover tightly with a metal lid.

title: chile casserole(excellent)
directions: Grate sharp and mild Cheddar cheeses (or cheat and buy them already grated).
Keep separate.
Grease a 2-quart casserole dish. Layer ingredients in this order: sharp Cheddar cheese on bottom, half the chilies, the mild Cheddar cheese and cheese and chili mixture.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 325°.
Add Monterey Jack cheese during the last 10 or 12 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: sussex county slick dumplings
directions: Mix flour, salt and broth together until it makes a dough consistency.
Knead several times.
Roll out on floured surface and roll out as thin as possible, turning dough over and rolling several times.
Cut into squares and drop into pot of boiling broth.
Cook for about 20 minutes; stir often as they will stick together.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Let oleo sit until room temperature, then mix together well with cream cheese.
Add sugar to cream cheese and oleo mixture and cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour and a pinch of salt.
Beat mixture for 3 minutes.
Add flavoring and beat mixture for 2 more minutes. Pour into greased and floured tube pan and place on cool oven. Turn oven on and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop onto cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: 4 layer chocolate cake
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix first 3 ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Mix in order given.
Add reserved juice.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes until done.

title: seasoned crackers
directions: Mix together oil, dressing and dill.
Pour over crackers and mix well.

title: broccoli-bacon quiche
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on the package; drain.
Cook bacon. Beat eggs.
Add milk.
In pie shell, crumble cooked bacon.
Add broccoli.
Pour egg-milk mixture.
Add cheese.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: beef-wine spaghetti
directions: Mix all ingredients, except spaghetti and cheese, in 3-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and microwave on High (100%) 15 minutes; stir.
Cover and microwave on Medium-low (30%), stirring every 30 minutes until tender, 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Spoon sauce over hot spaghetti.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: pineapple-buttermilk congealed salad
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar in saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring.
Remove from heat.
Add jello, stirring well.
Cool. Add buttermilk; stir well.
Fold in cream and pecans.
Stir well. Pour into 13 x 9-inch dish and chill.

title: marinated fresh vegetable salad
directions: Marinate all cut up vegetables in dressing for
4 to 6 hours.

title: santa claus salad or preacher's delight
directions: Add 1 cup boiling water to jello. Stir until dissolved.
Mix fruit together and add to jello after it has cooled some.
Put half of the mixture in mold or bowl and put in refrigerator to set. Mix sour cream, nuts, mayonnaise and sugar.
Put this over jello to make layer, then add rest of fruit mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: graham crackers great
directions: Melt sugar and margarine.
Place pecans over crushed crackers. Pour sugar and margarine on pecans.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: ice cream cone christmas trees
directions: Add a few drops of food coloring to the white frosting.
You will now have green frosting.
Invert a sugar cone, and spread the frosting all over the cone.
Now, decorate the cone with small edible decorations.
Voila!
Use your tree for decoration, or have fun eating it.
I have used this at holiday time for my preschoolers, and they loved it.

title: kourambie thes(walnut butter biscuits)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the butter, 1 ounce of the sugar and the baking powder in a large mixing bowl.
Then gradually add the flour, beating constantly.
Finally, add the walnuts.

With floured hands, form 1 1/2 tablespoons of the dough into round biscuit shapes, 1 1/2-inches in diameter and 1/2-inch thick. Place them on a floured baking tray, keeping them 1-inch apart. Bake about 15 minutes, until light brown and firm.
Cool on a cake rack and sprinkle with remainder of the confectioners sugar.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Blend together salad dressing, sugar and vanilla.
Add all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: grilled chicken and orange sauce
directions: Grill breasts and put in baking pan. Mix the first 6 ingredients and bring to a boil on low heat. Mix cornstarch and water until smooth and add to mixture. Simmer until sauce thickens. Pour sauce over chicken and bake for 15 minutes in low heat oven. Serve with rice pilaf or unseasoned rice of your choice.

title: slaw for freezer
directions: Combine all ingredients except vegetables and bring to a boil. Pour over prepared vegetables.
Do not stir for 1 hour.
Put into boxes and freeze.

title: sunday breakfast
directions: Place half the broken bread in bottom of a buttered casserole dish. Top with half of the sausage and half of the cheeses. Repeat combination.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over mixture. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: killer mashed potatoes
directions: Wash and cube potatoes; leave skins on.
Cook until tender. In pan, saute the onions (2 tablespoons of regular onions can be used instead) until golden.
Mash potatoes, skins and all.
Add sauteed onions and rest of ingredients.
Can be made the night before and reheated.

title: gingersnap meatballs
directions: Mix meat, bread crumbs, onion, salt, pepper, 3 teaspoons lemon juice and water in bowl.
Mix well; form into 1-inch balls.
Heat margarine in medium skillet; brown meatballs.
Remove balls from pan.
Add beef broth and 3 teaspoons lemon juice to pan drippings. Bring to boil; add brown sugar and gingersnap crumbs.
Add meatballs to sauce; cook, covered, 10 minutes.
Stir once; allow to simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.

title: upside-down cake
directions: Sift flour again with baking powder.
Cream butter or substitute and sugar.
Add well beaten egg yolks to creamed mixture.
Add milk alternately with flour, add vanilla and fold in beaten egg whites.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter and add brown sugar. Spread in baking dish.
Add fruit, slices or crushed.
Pour cake batter over fruit.
Bake in 360° oven 45 minutes.
Turn upside down.
Serve with whipped cream.
Serves 8.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix together in a large bowl. Salt to taste. should be marinated for at least 12 hours. Will keep up to a week in the refrigerator.

title: sweet-sour chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken.
Place chicken in single layer, skin side up, in shallow baking pan.
Pour dressing mix on. Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.
Baste occasionally with drippings.
Serve hot with rice.

title: sims and micki dirty rice
directions: Cook rice.
In another pot cook shrimp and drain. Combine sausage, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook and drain off some of the fat.
Stir in rice, carrots and peas; finish cooking on low heat.

title: ground meat and gravy
directions: Brown the meat and onions until the meat is almost done.

title: eggnog cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, vanilla, egg and eggnog.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and nutmeg; then add to sugar mixture. Add nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Fry onion and tomato in a little bit of oil.
Add sour cream and 1/2 cup chicken broth.
Add deboned chicken and salt to taste.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 15 minutes before serving.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onions and brown until tender.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
This freezes well.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in small amount of water.
Mix all other ingredients together in crock-pot.
Add broccoli and cook on low all day or until it reaches desired temperature.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Combine pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Put on 1/2 of pudding mixture and then another layer of crackers.
Put on a thin layer of chocolate icing, about 1/2 of can.
Add remaining pudding and a third layer of crackers.
Top with other half of icing.
Chill and serve.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown meat in oil in large skillet.
Add water and salt and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add pineapple and vegetables.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in combined preserves, vinegar, cornstarch and soy sauce.
Cook, stirring constantly, until clear and thickened.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: pina colada slush
directions: Place in large freezing container.
Freeze for 2 days.
Fill glass with slush and add white (clear) cream soda.

title: onioned potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes, do not pare.
Cut each in 1/4-inch slices, lengthwise.
Blend soup mix with oleo.
Spread on one side of each slice.
Put potatoes back together, wrap in foil, sealing securely.
Bake 1 hour or until done.
May be baked over coals or on grill top turning only once.

title: economical queen cake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream the margarine and sugar thoroughly; add egg and beat well.
Add alternately dry ingredients, milk and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured Queen Cake tins and bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine dates, hot water and soda. Cream butter, margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Add flour, salt and cocoa. Combine all ingredients and add 1/2 package (6 ounce) chocolate chips and 1/2 package (6-ounce) butterscotch bits. Pour into greased 9 x 13 baking pan. Sprinkle remaining chips and chopped nuts on top. Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes in 9 x 13 baking pan.

title: easy german chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and flour in a bowl; mix well.
Add beaten egg, evaporated milk and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in pecans and coconut.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until set.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dutch apple bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Combine dry ingredients; add alternately with chopped apple and liquid.
Fold in nuts or cranberries.
Bake for 55 minutes at 350° in loaf pan.

title: world's best cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake in 325° oven for 14 minutes.

title: potato rolls
directions: Do not add yeast to any of these until they are lukewarm!
Cook potatoes until done.
I use that water to mix with.
Beat eggs. Add sugar and salt.
Mash potatoes and add margarine and add to eggs-sugar mixture.
Let yeast dissolve in the 3 tablespoons of water.
Add potato water and yeast, then the flour.
Let rise in refrigerator until ready to use.
Make in rolls.
Let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Bake at 400° until brown, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mud cake
directions: Put 1/2 of crushed Oreos on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut half of the worms into thirds.
Lay worms on top of "dirt."
Mix pudding with milk; add Cool Whip.
Pour over "dirt."
Sprinkle rest of dirt on top.
Cut other half of gummi worms.
Stick in top with heads and tails sticking out.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Drain peaches.
Save juice.
Combine peach juice, sugar, vinegar and spices.
Boil over low heat for 10 minutes.
Pour hot syrup over peach halves.
Let cool.
Chill thoroughly before serving.
Makes 4 pints.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top. Cook in oven for about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: monster cookies
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and peanut butter, then add remaining ingredients.
Scoop by ice cream scoop, 6 at a time, on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: grilled sweet-n-sour pork chops
directions: Combine ingredients and marinate in glass bowl for 1 hour. Grill 30 minutes.

title: freezer cabbage slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, carrot and mango as for slaw.
Add salt; mix well.
Let set 1 hour.
Squeeze out juice.
Mix remaining ingredients and boil 1 minute.
Cool, then add to cabbage.
Pack in plastic containers and freeze.
When ready to serve, let thaw completely.

title: carrot pineapple nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Beat eggs in large mixing bowl.
Add sugar and oil; beat until well blended.
Stir in flour and cinnamon; blend thoroughly.
Stir in carrots, undrained pineapple and pecans. Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes or until cake begins to pull away from sides of pan and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Spread with Cream Cheese Frosting.
Sprinkle with nutmeg, if desired.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Break up Oreos.
Beat together melted butter, cream cheese, sugar and 4 tablespoons milk.
Add the pudding mixes and 3 1/2 cups milk.
Beat and add Cool Whip.
Continue to beat until thickened.
Layer in pan, starting and beginning, with cookie crumbs.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate-coconut dessert
directions: Mix and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes and cool.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix sugar, water, tea, orange, lemon and pineapple juice in gallon jug; chill thoroughly.
This is base of punch.
Add soda and ginger ale just before serving.
Makes 40 to 50 servings.

title: mexican corn casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to instructions on package; add margarine and stir until melted.
Add corn and soup.
Add grated cheese to mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven; sprinkle some cheese and paprika on top.
Serves 6.

title: punch
directions: Mix together except ginger ale and keep refrigerated.
Just before serving, add chilled ginger ale.
Serves 100.

title: betty holmes' rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in an 8-inch ovenproof casserole dish.
Bake uncovered for 35 minutes.

title: polish reuben casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk, onion and mustard in medium bowl; blend well.
Spread sauerkraut in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with precooked noodles.
Spoon soup mixture evenly over top.
Top with sausage (or kielbasa), then cheese.
Combine crumbs and butter in small bowl; sprinkle over top.
Cover pan tightly with foil.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Garnish as desired.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in butter until lightly browned.
Stir in flour and gradually add consomme, stirring constantly.
Add basil, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, pepper and nutmeg.
Slowly simmer mixture for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Lightly brown strips in a slightly greased and salted skillet.
When strips are tender, add them to sauce.
Add drained mushrooms to sauce.
Just before serving, add sour cream; heat.
Do not boil.
Serve with rice or noodles.
Serves 4.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and buttermilk in blender.
Add melted butter and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce temperature to 300° and bake approximately 30 minutes or until lightly browned and custard is set.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Puree tomatoes, peppers and garlic with olive oil. Chop onion and cilantro. Combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Enjoy with baked chips.

title: fortune cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly.
May need to add more water.
Make 1 cookie at a time on lightly greased skillet or griddle.
Pour 1 teaspoon of the batter.
Spread to 3 1/2-inch circle.
Cook over low heat until browned, turn and cook 1 more minute, working quickly.
Put fortune in center of cookie; fold cookie in half and then fold again over edge of bowl.
Place cookies in muffin pan to cool. Enjoy!

title: coconut cream candy
directions: Melt butter; add milk and sugar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved, heating slowly, boil 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from fire and add coconut and vanilla, beating until creamy.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix water, sugar, cornstarch and food coloring together. Bring to boil and cook until it is thick and clear.
Remove from heat.
Add jello.
Cool and pour over strawberries which have been put in 2 baked pie crusts.
Cover with whipped cream.

title: thanksgiving cranberry salad
directions: Make jello, less 1 cup water called for.
Chill for 15 minutes.
Stir in cran-orange sauce.
Chill 30 minutes.
Stir in celery and walnuts.
Pour 1/2 of jello mix into a bowl; spread with sour cream.
Spoon remaining jello over the top.
Chill overnight.

title: italian style zucchini
directions: Combine corn, undrained tomatoes and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and cook 2 minutes.
Stir in zucchini. Cook, uncovered, 3 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: upside-down monkey bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10-inch tube pan.
Combine jam and pecans; spread evenly in bottom of pan.
Stir sugar and cinnamon together in a small bowl.
Cut each biscuit into quarters; roll in sugar mixture to coat evenly.
Layer biscuits in pan.
Combine brown sugar and butter; pour over biscuits.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Boil apple juice, cornstarch, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon until thickens.
Place apples in prepared pie crust, juice mixture over apples. Add top pie crust.
Bake as with any apple pie.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Chop in the cheese in small pieces. Put the macaroni in 2-quart casserole dish.
Add stewed tomatoes, cheese, onions and salt and pepper.
Mix together.
Add milk and butter.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese generously on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: touchdown tortillas
directions: Combine cream cheese, onions, green chillies and mustard. Spread on tortilla; add slice of meat and cheese.
Tightly roll up jelly roll style.
Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate until served.
Serve whole or cut in pieces.
May be made days ahead of time.
To make tortillas pliable, warm in microwave 10 seconds. Leftovers may be frozen for short period.

title: ms. juanita's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together first 5 ingredients. Sift together remaining ingredients. Add to creamy mixture and mix well. Flatten on cookie sheet and bake 10 minutes.

title: guilt free chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 8-inch round pans. In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add water, vanilla, oil and vinegar.
Stir until smooth and thoroughly blended.
Pour into prepared cake pans.
Bake 22 to 25 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes. Remove pan.
Cool completely on wire rack.

title: fruit punch
directions: *Note:
For green punch, add 1 large or 2 small cans frozen limeade and 3 large or 6 small cans of water.
For pink punch, use pink lemonade instead of lemonade and use pink grapefruit-pineapple juice instead of grapefruit-pineapple juice.

title: diabetic candy
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Stir in sugar replacement, water and vanilla extract.
(Dough may be divided into parts and different flavorings and/or food coloring added to each part suggested in various recipes.) Knead or work with the hand until dough is smooth.
Use as directed in the recipes.
Yield:
1 cup (250 ml).
Exchange full recipe:
4 fruit, 6 fat.
Calories per recipe:

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Cook chicken breasts and broccoli separately.
Lay the pieces of broccoli in the bottom of baking pan.
Lay chicken, broken in large pieces, on top.
Heat soup, cheese and Miracle Whip together and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and butter on top. Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: old fashioned apple butter
directions: Wash, core and quarter apples (do not peel).
Combine apples and apple juice in lightly oiled crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low for 10 to 18 hours (high setting, 2 to 4 hours).
When fruit is tender, put through a food mill to remove peel.
Measure cooked fruit and return to crock-pot.
For each pint of fruit, add 1 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, 1/2 teaspoon allspice and 1/2 teaspoon cloves; stir well.
Cover and cook on high 6 to 8 hours.
Stir every 2 hours.
Remove cover after 3 hours to allow to cook down. Makes 5 (1/2-pint) jars.

title: damson plum pie
directions: Remove seeds from fruit; add enough water to make 4 c. fruit and fruit juices combined.
Add cornstarch to sugar and then add to fruit.
Cook until very thick, stirring constantly.
Add small amount of fruit mixture to beaten eggs and mix well.
Add to remainder of fruit mixture which has been set aside until blended with eggs.
Return to heat and cook 5 minutes.
Cool.
Put in pie shells; top with desired topping.
Serves 12.
Makes 2 pies.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in a greased tube pan.

title: orange chiffon salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: breezy tuna boats
directions: Open the can of tuna; drain out in sink.
In a medium size bowl, mix together the tuna fish, cottage cheese, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Spoon 1/4 tuna mix into each hot dog bun.
(If you're using soft rolls, cut off each top and scoop out some of the insides to make a pocket, then fill pockets with tuna mix.) Cut each cheese square to make 2 triangles.
Place a toothpick through each.
Stick into each boat to make a sail.

title: chicken with pecans
directions: Combine honey and mustard and spread on both sides of chicken. Season with salt and pepper.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Place chicken in a lightly greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until tender.

title: seasoned black-eyed peas
directions: Rinse peas and place them in a large saucepan.
Cover with water and let soak for 45 minutes.
Cook Canadian bacon until crisp in a skillet over medium-high heat.
Drain on paper towels. Chop and set aside.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Mix syrup and peanut butter well together.
Stir dry milk and sugar mix.
Add handful Spanish peanuts.

title: devil's food filled cookies
directions: Lightly grease cookie sheets.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla, beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda, cocoa and salt; add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Drop by tablespoons 2 inches apart onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until cookie springs back when touched lightly in the center.
Cool.
Put two cookies flat sides together with 1 tablespoon of Creme Filling.
Makes 16 to 18 filled cookies.

title: dill dip with rye bread
directions: Mix and chill.
Serve in a hollowed out round loaf of rye bread.
Use rye bread to dip.

title: winter gone all afternoon stew
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Put all ingredients in large casserole dish.
There is no need to brown meat first.
Mix ingredients. Cover and bake for five hours.
Serves 6.

title: "foo-foo" salad
directions: Drain cottage cheese and pineapple.
Mix the cottage cheese, pineapple and dry gelatin together.
Fold in whipped topping. Chill 30 minutes before serving.

title: apricot jello
directions: Use 13 x 9-inch dish or pan.
Dissolve apricot Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add apricot nectar and crushed pineapple. When slightly jelled, add sour cream and swirl through.
Serves 24.

title: carrot and ripe olives salad
directions: Peel and slice carrots in rounds.
Cook in a little water. Drain.
While warm, add olive oil, vinegar, oregano and salt and pepper to taste.
Add olives.
Mix well.

title: spoon bread
