directions: Bring milk to boiling point in saucepan. Stir in cornmeal. Cook until thick, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and cool. Add eggs, baking powder, salt and butter. Beat. Pour into greased casserole dish and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: fried salmon patties
directions: Remove bone from salmon.
Add 1 egg and flour; mix together well.
Heat oil.
Dip salmon out with a spoon; cook in oil until brown.
If you need to, you may add more flour to get salmon to stick together.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Layer potatoes, onions and carrots in a 9-inch baking pan, seasoning each layer with salt and pepper.
Add enough milk to cover vegetables.
Coat pork chops with flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Arrange over vegetables. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown; turn chops.
Bake for 15 minutes longer or until tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Pour into prepared pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Turn down to 350°.
Bake 35 minutes.
Cool.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: carrot parsnip stir-fry
directions: In a large skillet, saute parsnips in butter for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add carrots and onion; cook and stir until vegetables are tender, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: italian beef
directions: Cook roast, water, bouillon and paprika in roaster at 375° for 1 1/2 hours (minimum).
Cool and slice thin.
Heat liquid from roaster and add remaining ingredients.
Pour over meat in crock-pot.
Cook in crock-pot an additional 3 to 4 hours.

title: riceland rice ole
directions: Brown meat and onions in fat, stirring to break meat apart. Stir in rice, water, bouillon cube and tomato paste.
Add seasonings.
Heat to boiling; stir well.
Cover.
Lower heat and simmer for 25 minutes.
Add cheese cubes and toss lightly.
Serve at once.

title: melva pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then lower to 350° until done.

title: impossible quiche
directions: * The first 3 ingredients can be varied (ham, seafood, mushrooms, sausage, spinach, broccoli, etc.)

title: arequipe dessert
directions: Combine ingredients in a saucepan and simmer until thickened. Stir constantly, preferably with a wooden spoon, until you see the saucepan while stirring (4 to 5 hours).
Add the egg yolks and let cook 2 or 3 minutes longer.
Remove cinnamon stick.
Let cool. This recipe must be watched constantly.

title: cheese-stuffed baby vegetables
directions: For filling, in a small mixing bowl, stir together the Ricotta cheese, cream cheese, radish, chives, desired snipped fresh or dried herb and onion salt; mix well. Set aside.

title: oklahoma casserole
directions: Cook hamburger, onion, spices and salt and pepper.
Drain. Put in casserole.
Put half can of beans on top.
Mix soup with 1/2 cup milk; pour 1/2 over beans and hamburger.
Add a layer of cheese and a layer of tortillas.
Layer remaining ingredients. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: valentine cutouts
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray cookie sheet with nonstick spray. With rolling pin, roll out cookie dough to 1/4-inch.
Using a floured heart shaped cookie cutter, cut out cookies and place them about 1-inch apart on sheet. Bake about 7 to 10 minutes or until edges are very lightly browned. Remove immediately.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate with butter over low heat until blended or in microwave.
Mix in milk.

title: oriental cole slaw
directions: Break up noodles and add almonds and sesame seed to frypan with a little butter; toast until light brown.
Stir often and watch closely (burns easily).
Set aside or do the day before. Make dressing.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix
oleo
and graham crackers together.
Spread evenly in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat egg whites until stiff.	Fold in 2 cups
powdered sugar and 1 stick of softened oleo.	Pour over crust.
Arrange
bananas
over
top
of mixture.
Spread pineapple over
bananas.
Top
with	Cool
Whip.
Refrigerate overnight. Just before serving, top with nuts and cherries.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening well with mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add buttermilk.
Put 1/2 cup flour in small bowl with cut up orange slices, coconut and pecans.
Mix well.
Add rest of flour to sugar and shortening mixture.
Mix well.
Add orange slices to mixture.
Mix by hand.
Pour into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: meat loaf in mug
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pat into custard cups. Make hole in middle to bottom.
Microwave 6 to 8 minutes.
Drain off fat.
Let stand 3 minutes.

title: grandma's rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add mashed potatoes, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cover and let stand in warm place until bubbly.
Work in flour.
Knead several minutes.
Put in bowl and cover.
Put in refrigerator.
Take out and shape rolls 1 hour before baking at 400°.

title: hidden treasures cake
directions: Spray an 11
x
7-inch
pan
with Pam.
Sprinkle bottom with 1 cup coconut and 1 cup chopped pecans.

title: bammy phillips butter cookies
directions: Cream butter with vanilla.
Gradually add sugar and baking soda; cream well.
Gradually add flour; mix thoroughly.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mullet broccoli bake
directions: Place
fillets	in
greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Cook broccoli as directed, adding onion.
Drain; spread over fish.

title: penne with sausage and mushrooms
directions: Saute the sausage in butter and olive oil until the meat is brown, about 15 minutes.
Add the mushrooms and cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Stir in the garlic and peas, then salt and pepper to taste.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until smooth.
Add buttermilk; stir.
Pour into deep dish pie crust.
Now, cover top with walnuts and a little coconut. Bake 50 minutes at 325°.

title: pineapple upside-down cake(microwave)
directions: In a 2-quart (8 x 8-inch) glass baking dish, melt butter (20 seconds).
Blend in brown sugar and pineapple; spread evenly over bottom of dish.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package, using half the ingredient amounts.
Pour over pineapple mixture in pan, spreading to cover pineapple.
Cook, uncovered, 8 minutes and 30 seconds, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Let stand 1 minute before loosening edge and inverting onto serving plate.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream.

title: aunt jeanne's spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute the garlic and onion in oil for about 15 minutes.
Do not burn.
Add ground beef and saute until the meat is all brown. Add tomato paste, tomato sauce and water.
Simmer for one hour. Any grease may be skimmed off at this time, then for the last 15 minutes, add all the spices.
This makes enough sauce for a one pound box of spaghetti.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix together and let stand 2 to 3 hours.
Serves 4.

title: o.j. cake
directions: Mix all together. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes in 9 x 13 pan.

title: golden chocolate cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine cake and pudding mixes, oil, water and eggs. Beat on low speed for about 30 seconds or until moistened. Beat 2 minutes on high. Blend in sour cream. Stir in candy bars, chocolate chips, nuts and coconut. Pour into a greased and floured 12-cup fluted tube pan. Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool in pan 15 minutes before removing to a wire rack. Cool completely. Chill before slicing. Dust with confectioners sugar if desired. Servings: 12 to 16.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon in a large plastic bag.
Quarter biscuits and drop in sugar/cinnamon.
Shake and coat biscuit pieces.
Layer coated biscuits in a large tube/Bundt pan. Sprinkle chopped pecans over each layer.
Melt margarine and brown sugar; pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, melted margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar. Press into pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Let cool.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add water.
Bring to boil until clear and thickened.
Add jello, mixing well.
Let cool.
Add strawberries.
Place in crust.
Chill well.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix melted butter and sugar together.
Add beaten eggs.
Add syrup, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 300° at least 1 hour.
Keep checking.

title: hungarian frittata
directions: Cut salami into strips and sausages into slices.
Rinse bell peppers.
De-seed and cut into strips.
Rinse and slice tomatoes. Peel and slice onions.
Saute sausages in a skillet for 3 minutes. Add onion and pepper strips.
Saute a few more minutes.
Add tomatoes.
Reduce heat.
Beat eggs.
Pour eggs over all ingredients in pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until egg mixture is set.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve.

title: peas au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook and drain peas.
Drain water chestnuts.
Combine peas and chestnuts with soup, onions and cheese.
Pour into lightly greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken pie
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil. Pour in a sheet pan (12 x 9 x 2-inch).
Make a broth of remaining ingredients.
Pour this mixture over chicken in pan.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Boil chicken, saving broth. Debone and chop chicken. Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan. Dip tortillas in broth and line pan.
Combine all the rest of the ingredients except the cheese.
Layer tortillas and chicken mixture.
Put cheese and chili powder on each layer. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes. After cooking begins, cut through layer with big spoon.
Es muy bueno!

title: beth's little meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
With lightly oiled hands, shape into balls.
Bake in shallow baking pan 15 to 20 minutes at 350°. Yields about 20 meatballs.

title: blueberry cream cheese cake
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar, water and blueberries.
Cook, while stirring, over medium heat until sauce bubbles and thickens. Cool.

title: pasta primavera casserole
directions: Cook pasta as directed; drain.
Spoon into greased 14 x 10 x 2 1/2-inch baking dish.
Saute zucchini, red peppers, mushrooms and onions in butter in large skillet for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add tomatoes.
Spoon over pasta.
Place flour in skillet; blend in milk.
Add broth, nutmeg and pepper.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens; add broccoli and pour over vegetables. Cover and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Garnish with parsley if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: buddy burgers
directions: Saute onions in shortening.
Add beef and brown.
Sprinkle in flour; stir to blend.
Add ketchup and seasoning; stir.
Let cool.

title: lucy's pound cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions and add the pudding, sour cream, eggs and vanilla.
Beat again.
Put 1/2 cake mixture in greased tube pan.
Prepare topping by mixing together sugar, cocoa and cinnamon.
Sprinkle 1/2 topping over cake batter in tube pan.
Add rest of batter (do not stir) and then rest of topping. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: purple cow smoothie
directions: In blender, combine grape soda, ice cream, ice cubes and vanilla.
Blend until smooth.
If mixture is too thick, add milk until desired consistency is achieved.
Pour into glasses and serve.

title: coffee buttercream icing
directions: Beat 4 egg yolks until thick and lemon-colored.
Set aside. Cream 1 cup softened butter until fluffy.
Set aside.
In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, coffee and water.
Bring to boil, stir until sugar and coffee dissolves.
Cook over medium-low heat, without stirring, to soft ball stage (236°).
Quickly pour the hot syrup in a steady stream into egg yolks, beating constantly, at high speed of electric mixer.
Continue beating until thick and smooth.
Cool.
Beat in reserved butter, a tablespoon at a time. Cover bowl and refrigerate for 30 minutes, until firm enough to spread easily.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together except flour.
Add it last.
Beat until smooth.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: banana cake
directions: I usually add nuts.
I've used regular flour.

title: steak sauce
directions: Mix and heat just a little to mix and dissolve honey.

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add coconut and pecans and simmer lightly. Set aside.

title: carolyn's cut-outs
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and flavoring. Mix together dry ingredients and add with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Add enough flour to make dough hold shape (may be tacky).
Chill 1 hour.
Generously flour board and rolling pin and roll dough for cut-out cookies.
Place on cookie sheets.
Bake at 450° for 7 to 10 minutes depending on thickness (bottoms are just turning brown).

title: delila's creamy fudge
directions: Lightly grease a foil lined
9 x 9 inch pan and set aside. Heat sugar, margarine, and milk in a heavy
3 quart sauce pan over medium heat.
Heat until mixture boils, stirring constantly.
Boil for 6 minutes.
Add chocolate chips, marshmallow cream, and vanilla.
Stir until chocolate melts.
Stir in walnuts. Immediately spread in foil lined pan.
Refrigerate over night. Cut into squares and serve.

title: dreamsicle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 3 cake pans. Blend first 6 ingredients on high for 3 minutes.
Pour into pans and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool completely.
Mix next 4 ingredients and fold into Cool Whip.
Frost cake.

title: thumbalina dogs(corn dogs)
directions: Combine all ingredients; set aside.
Pat dry weenies with paper towels.
Apply corn dog sticks.
Dip into batter.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: marinated whole carrots
directions: Arrange whole carrots in vegetable steamer and steam over boiling water for 10 to 12 minutes (or until just tender when pierced).
Or cook carrots in microwave for 6 to 8 minutes in covered dish.
Plunge into cold water to cool quickly, then drain. Pack in a clean jar.
Tuck in bay leaves.
Stir in a cup all other ingredients until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over carrots.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 days or up to 2 to 3 weeks.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Serve hot.

title: raisin peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream
sugar and Crisco.
Add peanut butter and eggs and beat well.
Fold in vanilla and milk.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Fold in raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Pour cherries in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt butter and mix oatmeal, flour, sugar, powder and soda.
Crumble mixture over cherries.
Cook 30 minutes at 400°.

title: watergate salad
directions: Drain pineapple and save the juice.
Place pudding mix in a large bowl.
Add all pineapple juice.
Mix well, add drained pineapple, topping, nutmeg, and marshmallows.
Mix well, until mixture is fluffy and increased in volume.
Refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Separately, cream butter and honey; beat in egg until mixture is smooth.
Stir in pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients to pumpkin mixture, stir in nuts and dried fruits. Bake in 8 x 8-inch oiled pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt oleo.
Add consomme soup; bring to a boil.
Add rice, mushrooms and onion powder.
Put in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour.
Stir a couple of times while baking.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix butter, egg and milk in blender.
Add broccoli to mixture in blender and chop well.
Pour liquid ingredients into dry muffin mix and bake according to directions on box.

title: betty's sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine soup mix with 1/2 cup water.
Beat in eggs.
Add meat and mix well.
Shape mixture into 40 meatballs.
Combine the rest of the ingredients.
Pour half into 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Brown meatballs and drain off excess fat.
Arrange meatballs on top of sauerkraut mixture.
Pour remaining mixture over meatballs. Cover with foil and bake in 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer.
Serve as is or over rice.

title: fried cabbage and macaroni
directions: Shred cabbage, salt and let stand for 15 minutes.
Saute onion in a large skillet with vegetable oil and margarine.
Fry until slightly browned.
Squeeze out excess water from cabbage and add to onion in skillet.
Stir together and fry until brown.
Add cooked macaroni to skillet; stir together.
Brown 1/2 stick of butter in skillet, pour over mixture and serve.
Excellent reheated the next day.

title: reuben roll
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Drain sauerkraut.
Pat out hamburger mixture.
Put sauerkraut in center and as much cheese as wanted. Roll it all up (like a jelly roll).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, wrapped in foil.

title: vanilla fruit
directions: Chop fruit into pieces.
Sprinkle dry pudding over fruit. Toss.
Add water and stir.
Let sit 1/2 hour.
Serve chilled. Other fruit may be substituted.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Quarter green tomatoes.
Pour salt over them and mix.
Let stand 3 hours.
Pour brine off.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 10 minutes.
If overcooked, tomatoes will not be crisp.
Makes 8 quarts.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine flour, soda and sugar; cut in shortening and stir in yeast and buttermilk. Keep covered in refrigerator. When ready to bake, roll out and cut the biscuits. You can let rise some or bake immediately. Dough will keep in refrigerator for a week. Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: italian stew
directions: Boil cabbage in water to cover in saucepan until tender.
Pour off excess water.
Brown sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Add sausage and remaining ingredients to cabbage, mixing well.
Simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: north dakota jerky
directions: Soak for 12 hours.
Bake at 180° for 3 or 4 hours.
Place in smoker to desired texture (about 10 hours).

title: party squash casserole(serving size: 6)
directions: Cook squash in 1/2 cup boiling water for 8 to 10 minutes; drain.
Place squash in large bowl and mash.
Stir in mayonnaise and next ingredients.

title: watergate salad
directions: In a large bowl mix Cool Whip and pudding.
Partially drain pineapple and add to mixture.
Add 1 cup chopped pecans and 1 cup colored marshmallows.
Place in refrigerator for at least 12 hours before serving.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well. Add dissolved soda. Sift together flour, cloves, nutmeg and cinnamon. Add to mixed candied fruit and raisins. Mix well. Blend fruit-flour mixture into first mixture. Add apple juice slowly, mixing well. Fold in pecan halves. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet. (You may have to shape slightly.) Bake in a 300° oven for 20 minutes. Makes 10 dozen.

title: arroz con gandules y carne de cerdo(rice with pigeon peas and pork)
directions: Wash rice and drain at least 3 times.
Rinse chicken pieces under cold running water and pat dry with paper towels.
Place peppercorns, garlic, oregano and salt in a mortar and pound until crushed.
Blend in 2 tablespoons of olive oil and vinegar.
Rub chicken pieces thoroughly with the seasoning.
In our clan, if we're in a rush, we let the chicken stand for 15 minutes before cooking, otherwise we marinate for several hours or overnight in the fridge.
Heat remaining tablespoon of olive oil in a heavy kettle or Dutch oven and brown ham over moderate heat.
Add onion, bell pepper and ajf dulce.
Saute until onion is translucent.
Add tomato sauce, bouillon cube and olives.
Stir to combine.
Add chicken pieces plus 2 cups water.
Mix, lower heat to moderate-low and cook, covered, for 15 minutes.
Add rice and achiote.
Add more water to cover contents in pot, if necessary.
Mix well and simmer, covered, on low heat until rice is tender (about 30 minutes).
Stir in peas.
Cover and cook 10 minutes more.

title: tex-mex quiche
directions: Sprinkle chili powder over the inside of pie shell.
Combine cheeses with flour; place in pie shell.
Combine eggs, cream, chilies, olives, salt and pepper.
Pour over cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes before cutting into party wedges or squares.

title: happy hour punch
directions: Chill ingredients.
Mix in punch bowl.
Add carbonated beverage last.
Add ice cubes and garnish with orange and lemon slices.

title: minted meringues
directions: Beat egg whites with cream of tartar.
Gradually add sugar. Beat until stiff.
Add peppermint and some green food coloring. Place about a teaspoon meringue on a foil covered cookie sheet. Put 3 chocolate bits on top of the meringue.
Then put another dab of meringue on top of chocolates to hide them.
Makes 24 cookies. Heat oven to 350°, but turn oven off when the cookie sheets are put in oven.
Let set overnight.

title: strawberry dip
directions: Mix marshmallow cream and cream cheese together.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.
Cut top of pineapple.
Set aside for use as decoration.
Core pineapple and cut the core into chunks. Set aside.
Place dip into pineapple.
Put pineapple on a round plate and place the strawberries, pineapple chunks or other sliced fruit around the pineapple.
Serve and enjoy.

title: jiffy corn bake
directions: Mix corn, sour cream, sugar, vegetable oil and eggs; add muffin mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in 9 x 9-inch casserole.

title: bavarian kraut salad
directions: Mix and chill thoroughly.
Will keep covered in refrigerator for weeks.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken and bouillon cubes until done.
Set chicken aside to let cool off.
To make dumplings, cut shortening into the flour. You need a texture of pie crust (very crumbly).
Take 1 cup hot broth from chicken; start mixing flour and broth slowly.
You will not need the full cup of broth.
Do not make your dough wet.
Place on a floured sheet.
Roll out very thin.
Cut into strips and place in boiling broth.
Cook about 20 minutes.
Take skin and any fat off chicken.
Cut or tear into pieces.
Place chicken in dumplings; cook until hot.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix crushed graham crackers, oleo and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese and 1 cup sugar (add sugar gradually).
Mix eggs into mixture, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Pour over crust and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: chocolate walnut cookies
directions: With electric mixer, beat margarine until smooth.
Add sugar gradually and beat until light.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Combine flour, cocoa and baking soda.
Blend into creamed mixture. Stir in walnuts.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until done.

title: supermoist chocolate cake
directions: Sift and mix in bowl the flour, sugar, baking soda, cocoa and salt.
Mix well and empty into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Make 3 "holes" in mixture and in each hole put vanilla in one, vegetable oil in the second and vinegar in the third.
Over all this, pour the 2 cups of cold water; mix well with fork.
Make sure mixture is well mixed and of uniform color and consistency.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Check doneness with toothpick.
Can be frosted, dusted with powdered sugar or left as is.
Yummy!

title: calico beans
directions: Brown beef, bacon and onion; drain off fat.
Drain all beans except the pork and beans.
Combine beans, meat and balance of ingredients in large casserole.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours.
If you wish a sweeter taste, add 1/2 to 3/4 cup brown sugar.

title: curried butternut squash bisque
directions: Wash, peel, deseed and cube the butternut squash.
In a heavy soup pot, heat oil over medium heat.
Add onions and garlic; saute for 2 to 3 minutes, or until slightly softened.
Stir in curry and cumin; cook for 1 minute.
Add chicken stock, cider, rice and squash; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and cover the pan; simmer for 30 to 40 minutes, or until the squash is tender.
Pour the mixture through a strainer set over a large bowl.
Puree the solids in a food processor or blender until very smooth.
Return the puree and liquid to the saucepan.

title: cookies and cream pie
directions: Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pie filling mix; beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes. Fold in whipped topping and cookies.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 6 hours.
Remove from freezer.
Let stand about 10 minutes before serving.

title: sweet and sour red cabbage
directions: Place cabbage in Dutch oven with apples, seasonings, onion and water; simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Add butter, vinegar and sugar and simmer another hour.
Add more water if needed.
At end of cooking time, there should only be a little liquid remaining.

title: spinach and cheese dip
directions: Mix all together and store in refrigerator at least a couple of hours before you serve it.

title: joyce's pasties
directions: Mix steak, potatoes, carrots or rutabaga and onion.
Add salt and pepper.
Brush with can milk.
Bake at 475° for 20 minutes. Reduce heat to 375° for 30 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomato paste. Boil 1 hour. Stir in tomato paste until dissolved. Pour into sterile jars and seal.

title: layered crab taco dip
directions: In a large glass bowl, combine crab meat, green onions, cucumber, red onion, tomato and parsley. Combine all three juices and pour over crab mixture.
Cover and refrigerate at least 6 hours.

title: whole wheat buns
directions: Mix as any other yeast bread. Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.

title: carolyn's yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside.
Mix the dry ingredients in the order given, cutting in the shortening as you normally do for biscuits or pie dough.
Stir in the buttermilk and the water-yeast mixture; blend thoroughly.
The dough can now be made into biscuits or refrigerated.
Turn out onto a floured board and knead lightly as for regular biscuits.
Roll, then cut with a biscuit cutter and place in a greased pan.
Let biscuits rise slightly and cook in a 400° oven until lightly browned.
The dough keeps well in refrigerator for two or three days in a covered bowl.
When dough is cold it will take a little longer to rise.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together squash, cheese, margarine, onions, pepper, water chestnuts, mayonnaise, sugar, salt, egg, red pepper and 1 cup crumbs.
Place in buttered casserole dish and sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Press cream cheese on plate.
Put shrimp evenly over cream cheese.
Pour cocktail sauce evenly over shrimp sauce.

title: cajun shrimp and pasta
directions: Cook pasta and set aside.
Spray frypan with nonstick cooking spray, heat on medium-high.
Add pepper strips, cook 3 minutes, stirring until peppers are crisp-tender.
Remove vegetables from pan into bowl and set aside.
Add margarine to same frypan and melt.
Add garlic, cook 1 minute, stirring to blend.
Gradually add 1 cup chicken broth, mix until smooth.
Add thyme, hot pepper sauce, black pepper and red pepper.
Bring to a boil and add shrimp.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Cook about 5 minutes until shrimp is pink.
Return the pepper strips to the pan, cook and stir about 1 minute to heat.
To serve:
Drain pasta, place in large bowl and toss with remaining chicken broth and a sprinkle of parsley.
Add a few drops of lemon juice.
Add shrimp.

title: brandon's birthday hamburgers
directions: In a small bowl, put 1/2 can white frosting.
Add yellow food coloring.
In remaining 1/2 can, add red food coloring.
In a separate bowl, combine half bag of coconut, green food coloring and a few drops of water.
You now have "mustard", "ketchup", and "lettuce."
On a cookie sheet put the desired amount of vanilla wafers for hamburgers, rounded side down.
On the flat top side, put a smudge of "mustard" enough to stick the Oreo to.
Frost Oreo cookie with chocolate frosting and place on "mustard."
Sprinkle a little "lettuce" on top of "patty."
Put a smudge of "ketchup" on another vanilla wafer for the top bun and place on top of "lettuce."
Do the same steps for desired amount of vanilla wafers. You now have finger-size "hamburgers."

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Boil chicken, debone and dice. Combine broccoli, chicken and all other ingredients except crackers.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Crumble crackers over top.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve bubbly hot. Serves 6 to 8.
Can substitute leftover turkey.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Boil noodles.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Mix ground beef, taco seasoning, 1/2 to 3/4 jar of salsa and refried beans.
Grease 9 x 13 baking dish and layer with meat mixture, noodles, then cheeses; keep repeating until ingredients are gone.
Top with cheeses.
Bake at 375° until cheeses are melted.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix shortening in dry ingredients, using pastry blender or 2 knives until it resembles small peas.
Add buttermilk; roll on lightly floured board.
Cut and bake in a 450° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: roasted honey pepper pork
directions: Carefully score roast 1/2-inch deep completely around roast (without cutting string).
Combine all remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spoon or brush 2/3 of mixture over pork to coat.
Place in baking pan and roast at 325° for 1 hour.
Brush remaining mixture over pork and cook 30 minutes more.
Slice thinly and serve with your favorite vegetables.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: roast fresh ham with savory stuffing
directions: Have the butcher remove the aitchbone and leg bone from the ham, leaving the shank bone in.
Melt butter; add onion and celery and cook slowly for about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons sage, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper, the paprika and garlic salt.
Add the water and bring to boil.
Stir in crumbs and parsley.
Fill pocket in ham left by removing the leg bone.
It is possible to remove the bone without cutting the meat but if the meat is cut, tie together securely with cord.
Score fat, leaving skin on shank.
(When ready to serve, cut off skin and break up to serve.)
Put meat, fat side up, on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and a little sage.
Do not cover, do not add water and do not baste.
Insert the point of a meat thermometer into center of thickest part of meat, not touching bone, fat or stuffing.
Roast in preheated slow oven (325°) for about 4 1/2 hours or until meat thermometer registers 185°.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and butter.
Save 1/2 cup for topping. Pack in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream sugar and cream cheese; set aside.
Mix Dream Whip and milk until fluffy.
Add vanilla and cream cheese mixture.
Spread 1/2 of mixture on top of cracker crumbs.
Next, spread cherry pie filling.
Put remaining Dream Whip and cream cheese mixture on top.
Finish by sprinkling 1/2 cup crumbs on top.
Chill for several hours.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add beaten eggs and bananas.
Beat again.
Stir in flour, baking soda, salt, nuts and vanilla. Lightly grease loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: fresh lemonade syrup
directions: In a 1 1/2 qt. heat proof container, dissolve sugar in water. Cool and add lemon juice and peel.
Mix well.
Cover and store in refrigerator for up to 1 week.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into graham cracker pie crust.

title: coco-not cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and extract.
Add egg and beat; stir in Bisquick and potato flakes.
Cover bowl and chill 1 hour.
Heat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into marble size pieces and place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 14 minutes.
Watch carefully.
Makes 4 dozen.
Good with a hot cup of tea!

title: stuffed franks 'n taters
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl combine potatoes, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, 1/2 onions and the seasonings.
Spread potato mixture in 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Split franks lengthwise almost into halves.
Arrange franks, split side up, along center of casserole.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes or until heated thoroughly.
Fill franks with remaining cheese and onions. Bake, uncovered, 1 to 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: five layer dinner
directions: Brown meat in small amount of fat.
Arrange in layers in flat greased baking dish in following order:
meat, potatoes, onion, tomatoes and green pepper.
Season each layer.
Bake in moderate oven, 350°, for about 1 hour.

title: kiftates
directions: Mix all together.
Form into small balls.
Roll in flour and pat flat.
Fry slowly in oil or shortening.
These are good warm or cold, especially around the holidays.

title: blueberry coffeecake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together with the oleo. Take out 1 cup of dry mixture.
With remaining dry mixture, add egg yolks, milk and vanilla. Beat egg whites separately.
Add to dough.
Fold in egg whites.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add dough mixture.
Cover with blueberries.
Sprinkle the cup of dry mixture over the blueberries.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: slush
directions: Mix well and place in large container in freezer.
Stir 3 to 4 times during the first day to get right consistency.
May add ginger ale for thinner drinks.
Serves 20.

title: eggless, milkless and butterless cake
directions: To the raisin-water mixture, add cold water, lard, sugar, nutmeg, cloves, salt and dissolved soda.
Add enough flour to stiffen.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix cherry pie filling and pineapple together; fill bottom of a greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with cake mix, melted margarine and nuts.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: three-hole cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt, cocoa and sugar into cake pan.
Smooth out and make 3 holes.
In first hole, put the vinegar.
In second hole, put vanilla and in third hole, put oil.
Pour water over whole cake.
Blend with fork until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: deep fried turkey
directions: Thaw turkey.
Marinate turkey in dressing 5 to 6 hours.
Add salt and pepper.
Deep fry in hot shortening 1 hour.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of electric blender. Process until smooth.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 1/4 cups. You may want to add a little more water, as it really makes a thick milk.
It's great and inexpensive.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and butter over the top of casserole about 15 minutes before done.
Double the recipe for a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: spinach-cheese pie
directions: Mix ingredients well; turn into buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 325 degrees about 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until set.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Mix well.
Put in cool oven at 300° for 2 hours or until done.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Combine syrup, sugar, margarine and salt.
Cook on Full power for 4 minutes, stirring twice.
Add vanilla and and baking soda. Place popped corn in a large brown grocery bag; pour mixture over corn.
Stir with wooden spoon to cover corn evenly.
Cook on Full power for 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake.
Repeat and shake every 30 seconds.
Check for doneness.
It is done when it is not sticky and doesn't stick to sack.

title: old fashioned moist stuffing
directions: Fry onions and celery in butter until tender.
Toast bread until dark brown. Soak bread in cold water until soft.
Remove bread and squeeze until dry.
Put into bowl.
Add onions, celery and butter.
Sprinkle with seasonings that have been mixed together.
Mix together. Add slightly beaten eggs.
Makes enough stuffing for 14 to 16 pound turkey.

title: date nut bars
directions: Beat eggs, butter and sugar well.
Add flour, vanilla, baking powder and salt.
Flour dates and nuts, then add to mixture. Blend well.
Batter will be stiff.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 13 x 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool; cut in small squares.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: ham and cheese roll-ups
directions: Mix cheese, sugar and pineapple.
Spread on ham; roll up. Cover with wax paper and chill.
Slice and serve.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Pat biscuits into flat circles.
Cover with sauce.
Add meat and condiments.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pecan clusters
directions: Place marshmallow cream and chocolate kisses in a large bowl; set aside.
Combine sugar, milk and butter in a saucepan.
Bring to boil; cook for 8 minutes.
Pour over marshmallow cream and kisses; stir until melted.
Stir in pecans.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.
(Work fast, or candy will begin to set.)

title: raisin sauce(for ham or pork chops)
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a pan.
Place on stove; heat until
boiling
and
thick.
Pour
over
meat and serve. Makes a sweet and sour sauce.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix the first four ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to cabbage mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: grilled tomatoes with cheese
directions: Lay a single layer of sliced tomatoes on a sheet of aluminum foil.
Sprinkle with spices, then sprinkle with Parmesan and Mozzarella cheeses.
Grill on top rack until cheese is melted and lightly browned.

title: great grandma's peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar, milk and butter to a boil.
Insert candy thermometer and cook to a "soft ball".
Stir in marshmallows, peanut butter and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 pan and let set up.

title: lou and ray broussard's boiled crawfish
directions: Boil for 11 minutes.
Place in a styrofoam chest for 1 hour. (Styrofoam chest will not warp; ice chest will warp.)
You may use crab boil (4 bags).

title: barbecued beef brisket
directions: About 4 hours before serving, in covered kettle over high heat, heat to boiling brisket, onion, garlic, bay leaf and enough water to cover.
Over low heat, simmer for 2 1/2 hours until tender.

title: lemon pistachio cheese cake
directions: Mix first three ingredients and bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Let cool.
Mix next three ingredients and spread over cooled crust. Mix lemon pudding; set aside.
Mix pistachio pudding; set aside. After pudding has set, spread lemon pudding over cream cheese mixture, then pistachio pudding on top of lemon pudding.
Spread remainder of Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with pecan chips.
Place in refrigerator until cool.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and flour. Mix well. Add cocoa and vanilla; last add milk. Cook until thick, stirring at times. Add butter last. Beat well and pour into baked shell. Cool and top with egg whites or Cool Whip.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger.
In a large bowl mix cream cheese, taco seasoning and sour cream together.
Stir in the hamburger.
Layer everything in a dish.
Serve with Taco shells or chips.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Cook ground beef with onion.
Fry tortilla in oil.
Line bottom of dish with 6 tortillas.
Add layer of beef, pepper and soup.
Repeat; add cheese on top
of
last layer.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry tarts
directions: Cream the cream cheese together with the sugar.
Add in, one at a time, lemon juice, vanilla and eggs.
Mix until fluffy.

title: chicken-macaroni casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Stir together macaroni, cheese, diced chicken, drained mushrooms, pimiento, soup, milk and seasonings. Pour into ungreased casserole. Cover and bake 1 hour.

title: storybook fudge
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Gradually add sugar and stir in well. Add chocolate and stir.
Add nuts and stir.
Chill 30 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: new style sausage mac and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 3-quart baking dish.
Cook pasta according to package directions.
While pasta cooks, melt butter in large saucepan.
Whisk in flour and cook about 1 minute.
Whisk in milk and cook and stir over low heat until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat and stir in 2 cups of the cheese.
Stir in sausage and tomatoes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour drained pasta into prepared dish.
Stir sauce into pasta. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly and cheese is melted and lightly browned.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: garden relish
directions: Place all ingredients in a large kettle; mix.
Cook for 1 hour at boiling point.
Wash 6 pint jars in soap and water; fill with boiling water and let set.
Set screw tops and lids in boiling water.
Pour relish into a jar 1/2 inch from top; seal.
Yield:
6 pints.

title: cherry salad
directions: Bring cherries, juice, water and sugar to a boil.
Add jello. Stir until dissolved.
Let cool until it starts to set.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Wash mushrooms and slice through crown and stems.
Place 1 stick of butter or margarine in the frying pan.
Let butter slowly melt on low heat.
Add mushrooms, as many as you can get in the pan.
Stir so that all are covered with butter.
Cook for 10 minutes or until the mushrooms turn a medium brown.
Remove and add more mushrooms (and butter, as needed).
Put all cooked mushrooms on a platter and serve with hefty steaks and a fresh vegetable salad.

title: microwave boardwalk taffy
directions: Generously grease 8-inch square baking pan.
In a 2-quart glass measure, combine corn syrup, coffee, chocolate and salt and mix well.

Cook (micro) on High for 12 to 18 minutes or until microproof candy thermometer registers at 255° (or until small amount of mixture forms a ball hard enough to hold its shape but is still pliable when dropped into very cold water).

title: tacoritas
directions: Brown chicken, garlic and onion and set aside.
Mix together in a saucepan the cream of chicken soup, water, chili powder, sage, oregano, cumin and green chilies.
Bring to a boil and let simmer 5 minutes.

title: lo-cal custard
directions: Beat eggs, sweetener, vanilla and salt together.
Scald milk in a glass cup (on High for 3 to 4 minutes).
Add egg mixture, stirring well.
Pour into 6 custard cups.
Sprinkle each with nutmeg to taste.
Microwave on Low (3) for 10 to 12 minutes.
Put cups on shelf; rotate shelf 1/2 turn every 3 minutes.

title: wine cookies
directions: Mix oil, sugar, wine and vanilla.
Add flour and baking powder.
Break off pieces; make long strips.
Fold strip in half and twist.
Roll in mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir thoroughly by hand.
Pour into 9 x 13 pan, lightly greased.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Stir everything except pecans and cook on high for 13 minutes. Beat until slightly cool.
Add pecans and pour on waxed paper.

title: e-z coffee cake
directions: Spray Bundt cake pan with Pam.
Sprinkle nuts in bottom of pan.
Dip frozen rolls in butter and roll in sugar mixture. Stack in Bundt pan.
Pour dry pudding over rolls.
Drizzle remaining butter on top.
Put in cold oven overnight.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Blend oil in thoroughly with fork. Sprinkle all of water over mixture and mix well.
Press dough into ball.
If too dry, mix in 1 or 2 tablespoons oil.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach and drain well. Combine with other ingredients, mixing well. Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on lightly greased cookie sheets. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Makes 7 dozen.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Store in covered container.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons per cup hot water.
You may make by the cup or pot.

title: tangy party meatballs
directions: Mix together bread crumbs, ground meat, onion flakes, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, eggs, tomato paste, garlic and pepper.
Mix well.
Gently roll into firm small balls; set aside. Then add chili sauce, cranberry sauce, sugar and lemon juice; mix well. Place meatballs with sauce in baking pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until done at 400°.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: In a crock-pot, mix all the ingredients.
Cover and cook on low heat for 14 to 15 hours or until mixture is a deep brown. Pack while hot into 4 hot pint jars.
Process in a hot water bath for 10 minutes, counting the time after the jars have been immersed and the water comes again to a rolling boil.

title: peach cream pie
directions: Mix milk, lemon juice and Cool Whip until smooth.
Fold in peaches and divide evenly into pie crust.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, salt, eggs and pickles.
Moisten with mayonnaise. Serve on lettuce and garnish with additional egg slices and olives.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel and core apple; cut into 8 pieces and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Open can of rolls and separate.
Place a piece of apple on each roll and completely cover with the dough; place dumplings in a baking dish.

title: scotch eggs
directions: Hard-cook 6 eggs for 10 minutes.
Cool quickly by putting under cold running water.
Remove shells.
Divide sausage meat into 6 equal portions; flatten each piece so that it is big enough to go around an egg.
Use flour to prevent it from sticking.
Coat each egg with a little seasoned flour.
Wrap sausage around each egg, joining the edges, so the egg is completely covered.
Dip each sausage covered egg into lightly beaten raw egg, then into breadcrumbs.
Deep fry for a few minutes, or shallow fry on all sides until nicely browned and sausage is cooked.
Serve with salad.
Scotch Eggs are also good for a picnic.

title: pizza
directions: Mix Bisquick and water
together
well
and spread on a large cookie sheet or
pizza pan.
Spread spaghetti sauce over the dough.
Brown
hamburger,
onion and green pepper;
drain; then spread this
mixture
over the sauce.
Sprinkle mushrooms over the meat.
Sprinkle
Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix well and put in loaf pan.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: tomato soup franks
directions: In a skillet, cook the celery and onion until done in the shortening.
Add the franks. Cook until light brown. Stir in the soup, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes. Meanwhile cook the spaghetti.
Serve together.

title: cheese appetizers
directions: Grease an 8-inch square baking pan; set aside. Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, beat eggs; add cottage cheese and beat until almost smooth. Beat in flour, baking powder and butter until thoroughly blended. Stir in onions and cheese. Pour into prepared pan. Bake 30 to 40 minutes until firm in center. Let cool slightly. Cut into 25 squares. Serve warm.

title: fish sandwich with orange-ginger mayonnaise
directions: Melt butter.
In small bowl combine bread crumbs, ginger, salt and red pepper; set aside.
Place fillets on waxed paper.
Brush tops and sides with melted butter.
Coat tops and sides with crumb mixture.
Crumb side up place in 8 x 8 x 2-inch microwave-safe dish.
Cook uncovered for 4 to 7 minutes on High or until fish flakes.
Give dish 1/2 turn after 3 minutes.

title: salmon appetizer
directions: Drain salmon and remove bones.
Combine with the cream cheese, mashing together with a fork until blended.
Stir in lemon juice, onion, salt and liquid smoke, if used; mix well.
Add pecans and 1 tablespoon of the parsley until well combined.
Transfer to serving dish.
Chill to blend flavors.
Sprinkle with the parsley or sliced green onions before serving, or shape into a 2-inch high loaf. Wrap tightly with foil and place in freezer up to 24 hours.

title: ground beef noodle casserole
directions: Brown
chopped	beef
and onion;
drain fat.
Add 1 can tomato soup and 1 can vegetable soup, undiluted.
Simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar, then add other ingredients. Flour and butter a pan, then drop the mixture 1 teaspoon at a time. Bake at 300° until cookies are thin and crisp.

title: janice's foiled ham sandwiches
directions: Mix chili sauce and mayonnaise.
Add diced egg, onion, pickles and green pepper.
Stir in chipped ham and cheese cubes.
Put approximately 1 tablespoon of mixture on sandwich bun and wrap in foil.
Bake for 20 minutes at 300°.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen sandwiches.
Great for a crowd!

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crush cookies, a few at a time.
Put aside 2 cups of the crumbs for topping.
Combine remainder of crumbs and melted butter and spread evenly in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice ice cream and place over crumbs (it may be softened enough to spread).

title: jay's chili
directions: In Dutch oven, saute first 4 ingredients in hot oil until tender.
Add meat, one pound at a time, stirring until meat loses redness.
Drain and add water.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring after each addition.
Simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours, stirring frequently.
Season to taste with garlic salt and pepper, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken 25 minutes and dice.
Parboil broccoli in same water.
Combine soup with mayo, lemon juice, sherry and Romano cheese.
Add cooked chicken.
In 13 x 9-inch greased casserole dish, layer with broccoli first, soup mixture next.
Melt Parkay and brown bread crumbs, then sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: italian soup
directions: Melt butter or oleo in large pan.
Stir in onions and cabbage. Heat 2 minutes.
Add water.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in Veg-All, tomatoes and seasonings. Simmer 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in saucepan and cook to soft-ball stage.
Remove from heat.
In a warm mixing bowl, put marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla.
Add cooked syrup and mix well. Pour in buttered pan and cut in squares.

title: spicy confetti corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Sift together the flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt, chili powder and cumin.
Cut the pimiento into 1/4-inch dice and stir into dry ingredients. Combine the yogurt, egg, oil and scallions.
Stir yogurt mixture into dry ingredients until well combined.
Pour the batter into a buttered 8-inch skillet.
Bake until a toothpick comes out clean, 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm and cool.

title: party mix
directions: Melt margarine in open roasting pan in preheated 250° oven. Stir in seasonings.
Gradually add cereals, nuts and pretzels; stir to coat evenly.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Spread on paper towels to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: crispy onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a shallow baking pan, thoroughly blend all ingredients except potatoes.
Add potatoes and turn to coat thoroughly.
Bake, stirring potatoes occasionally, for 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Cook okra in a little water until tender, drain.
Cook onions and green pepper in margarine until tender, do not brown.
Stir in sugar and flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt, dash of pepper.
Add tomatoes, drained okra and heat through, simmer a few minutes.
You can also use fresh tomatoes, about 4 medium.

title: henderson specialty
directions: Grease casserole (2 1/2-quart).
Cook noodles.
Stir in milk and butter.
Blend thoroughly the cheeses, sour cream, green pepper, onion and salt.
Brown meat in skillet; stir in tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce, salt and Tabasco.
Layer the casserole with half the meat, half the noodles, all the cheese mixture, the remaining noodles and top with the rest of the meat.
Cover and bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: best corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in bowl, mixing after each addition.
Pour into greased and floured 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm with butter and honey.
Yields 9.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix everything together and pour into a 3-quart casserole dish or two smaller dishes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 14 to 16.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine corn, crackers, celery, onion and salt; add to this the eggs and stir in milk, butter and cheese.
Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Garnish with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Beat butter and Crisco.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Beat in vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients in a separate bowl then add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Bake in a greased 10 inch tube pan at 325° for 80 minutes or until cake bounces back when touched.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring
to a boil. Boil 5 minutes.
Then add the next 4 ingredients.
Combine and place on wax paper until cooled.
Can also be placed in cupcake liners.

title: herb pork chops
directions: Chop dry dressing to small to fine.
Beat eggs in different bowl.
Pour oil in baking tin, about 1/4 cup per pan.
Dip chops in egg then crumbs on each side and place in pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until one side is brown.
Turn and bake 20 minutes more or until brown on this side.

title: lemonade balls
directions: Mix and roll into 1-inch balls. Freeze. Serve as needed.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and pour into 2 (9-inch) pie pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until brown.
This pie makes its own crust.
Yield:
2 (9-inch) pies.

title: baked chop suey
directions: Mix all together, except noodles, and bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Top with Chinese noodles and bake 10 more minutes.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch dish or pan (greased).
Bake at 350° until done.
Remove from oven and punch holes in cake.
Combine Eagle Brand milk and cream of coconut and pour over cake.
Let cool completely.
Top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle coconut on top.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons per cup of boiling water.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and 4 tablespoons sugar.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 400° for 6 minutes, let cool.
Whip cream cheese and sugar, then add Cool Whip.
Spread over pretzel layer. Dissolve Jell-O in hot water, stir in strawberries partially set. Pour cream cheese layer.
Chill until set.

title: oven chili
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; remove and save 3 tablespoons fat. Brown meat; put in 3-quart casserole.
Cover; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add onions, garlic and 1 cup water.
Add tomato sauce and chili powder, mixed with sugar.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes. Add remaining ingredients; bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Just before serving, sprinkle with bacon.
Serves 6.
May garnish with green pepper rings.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Combine all ingredients and then stir in broccoli.
Spray a 1 1/2-quart casserole and pour mixture into it.
Top with crushed crackers and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: friendship cake starter
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 1 gallon glass jug and cover tightly. Set on cabinet (not in refrigerator) and mark calendar.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cool (or use canned chicken).
Mix with ingredients.
Cover with topping of 1 1/2 cups crumbled corn flakes and 1/2 stick margarine, melted.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Will fill 2 small casserole dishes.
It can be frozen.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Add
sugar,
salt and milk. Beat well.
Add vanilla and beat.
Pour into unbaked pie shell crust. Bake at 425° about 30 minutes until
a
knife stuck in center comes out clean.

title: apple-nut cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and set aside.
Beat sugar, eggs, salad oil and vanilla.
Add the dry ingredients gradually.
Fold into batter 3 cups diced apples and 1 cup chopped nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes (glass dish, 325°). You can grease and flour dish or use Baker's Joy.

title: remembrance strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan; stir in water.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in gelatin.
Pour over strawberries; mix well.
Pour into pie shell. Refrigerate until set.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: goulash soup
directions: In an 8-quart heavy kettle, cook bacon over moderate heat, stirring until crisp.
Transfer with a slotted spoon to a large bowl.
In the fat remaining in the kettle, brown boneless chuck in small batches over high heat, transferring it as it is browned with slotted spoon to a large bowl.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain well. In a 9x13 baking dish, layer the 6 slices of cubed bread, sausage, and grated cheddar cheese. In a mixing bowl beat the eggs, milk, salt, and dry mustard. Pour over layered mixture and bake at 350°
for 35 minutes.

title: shoestring potatoes
directions: Peel large potatoes; slice larger than for French fries.
Soak in ice water.
Make dip by combining flour, baking powder, vinegar and enough water to make stiff batter.
Dry potatoes well; dip potatoes and drop in hot grease a few at a time.
Turn once.
Keep warm in brown paper bag with paper towels.
Great with fried chicken.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Stir in remaining ingredients. Drop by tablespoon onto waxed paper. Cool.

title: yogurt
directions: Bring 1 1/2 gallons milk (skimmed off) to a boiling point. Cool to lukewarm.
Beat 3/4 cup dry mix with 2 cups of the heated milk and add yogurt.
Now add to cooled milk and let set until thick in warm place.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: pumpkin sour cream pie
directions: Heat 1 cup sour cream in the top of a double boiler.
In a mixing bowl, mix together 1/2 cup sour cream, pumpkin puree, the beaten yolks of 3 eggs,
brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger and salt.

title: finger jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and gelatine in boiling water and add the cold fruit juice.
Pour into a square dish and chill until set.
Cut into squares.

title: fettuccine alfredo with seafood
directions: Cook fettuccine to the al dente stage.
Drain well and place in warm serving dish.
Add butter, heavy cream and 1/2 Parmesan. Toss until well coated.
Add seafood and desired amount of broccoli.
Toss.
Garnish with remaining Parmesan.
Serve immediately.

title: no-fat no cholesterol chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in tube pan 45 minutes at 350°. Top with Cool Whip and cherries.

title: kentucky jam cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, sour milk and jam.
Sift together flour, spices, baking powder and soda and add through sifter to first mixture.
Stir in melted shortening and beat thoroughly.
Bake in two greased layer cake pans in a moderate oven (350°) for 25 to 35 minutes.
Spread with Fluffy White Icing.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown steak, salt and pepper.
Add 1 cup water.
Cover.
Cook 2 hours on simmer or low heat.
Arrange onion and green pepper on top of steak.
Pour tomato sauce and gravy on top.
Cover and cook another 1 hour or until tender.
Serve over rice.

title: monkey cake
directions: Put the sugar and cinnamon in a Baggie.
Cut biscuits into fourths.
Drop in bag and shake.
Arrange biscuits in layers in a tube pan or Bundt pan.
Sprinkle each layer with raisins and nuts. Bring the margarine and brown sugar to a boil; pour over cake in pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: e-z peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk, vanilla, butter and baking cocoa thoroughly in 3-quart saucepan and boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and quickly add marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Mix thoroughly and pour at once into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cape cod salad
directions: Heat water and cranberry sauce until liquified.
Add Jell-O and chill until slightly thick.
Add fruit cocktail and banana. Set until firm, preferably overnight.

title: mary wallace fudge
directions: Use large pan.
Bring sugar and milk to a rolling boil and then lower heat immediately.
Stir constantly 15 minutes.
This is very important to stir 15 minutes.
Pour sugar and milk mixture over the following (use large bowl): chocolate chips, butter, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Whip until firm and butter has melted.
Add nut meats; stir.
Pour into buttered dish or dishes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
In another bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Mix well and add to the other mixture.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ham ball
directions: Cream cheese must be at room temperature.
Chop 2
packages of ham; add ham and onion to cream cheese and garlic powder.
Mix well.
Form into ball and roll in other 2 packages of chopped ham. Put in refrigerator and let set over night.

title: grandpa's sandwich
directions: Spread peanut butter on 1 slice of bread.
Spread mayonnaise on second slice.
Put lettuce in between.
Enjoy with your favorite drink!

title: instant russian tea
directions: Shake together well.
Use 2 teaspoons to a cup of boiling water.

title: shredded meat sauce
directions: Mix in order; stir well.
Bring to a boil, turn down heat. Cook slowly for 12 minutes.
Stir often.
Omit salt if meat has been salted.
Have meat ready, mix and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: hot crab spread
directions: Mix together all ingredients except crabmeat.
Add crabmeat. Put in greased shallow baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Mix ingredients into a soft dough and divide in two parts. Roll out very thin; let dry 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut in 2-inch squares and drop into broth that is simmering.
Let cook until done, about 15 minutes.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Microwave onion until clear, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into clean jar and seal or store in refrigerator container.
Will
keep about 2 weeks.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes in 350° oven in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Dust top with powdered sugar.

title: frozen fruit
directions: Drain fruit cocktail, pineapple and peaches.
Save the juice. Mix orange juice with fruit juice.
Add sugar and heat until sugar melts.
Cool and pour over fruit.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer 30 minutes before serving.

title: spaghetti with herbed tomatoes and cheese
directions: Over medium heat, add olive oil. Cook garlic and onions until tender. Stir in tomatoes, basil and heat. Return spaghetti to saucepan; toss gently with tomato mixture. Add Mozzarella, grated cheese, salt and pepper to taste. Serve immediately.

title: spiced tea
directions: Place cloves and cinnamon in tea ball in water.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Add tea bags and steep 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Add juices and sugar.
Stir.
Remove spices.
To reheat, warm over low heat but do not allow to boil.

title: toppie's potato salad
directions: Combine Miracle Whip, paprika, celery seed, salt, mustard, vinegar and sugar.
Mix until well blended.
Pour over diced potatoes and eggs, chopped celery and onions.
Fold all of ingredients together until vegetables and eggs are well covered with dressing.
Chill 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: carameled cereal
directions: Cook until bubbling the brown sugar, oleo and corn syrup.
Add soda and salt.
Pour over Cheerios, nuts and raisins on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 15 minutes.

title: quick jambalaya
directions: Cut Spam into 2 x 1/4-inch strips.
Saute Spam, green peppers, celery, onion and garlic in oil until vegetables are tender.
Add tomatoes, water, thyme and chili powder, breaking tomatoes up with fork.
Bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice. Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.

title: microwave peanut brittle (10 minutes)
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and salt in 2-quart bowl.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave for 3 to 5 minutes on High until lightly brown.
Stir in butter, vanilla and soda.
Spread to 1/4-inch thickness on large, well-buttered cookie sheet.

title: long lasting play dough
directions: Mix, cook on medium heat and stir until thickened and forms a ball.
Cool.
Knead.
Use and enjoy!

title: beef burgundy
directions: Place all ingredients in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours. Last 1/2 hour, add 1 can mushroom soup.
Decrease heat to 250°. Serve over hot noodles or rice.
Can add mushroom soup at beginning and bake for about 3 1/2 hours.

title: fruit dip
directions: Whip all ingredients together until fluffy.
Let set for at least 1 hour.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: tarragon mustard(perfect with shellfish)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except olive oil, in blender.
Mix until smooth and creamy.
With machine running slowly, add olive oil in slow, steady stream and blend until mixture is like mayonnaise.
Pour into jars with tight fitting lids.
Store in cool place. If too stiff, add equal portions of water and oil. Makes 4 cups.

title: chili pizza
directions: Prepare pizza crust as indicated on package.
Prepare Skyline chili as indicated on package.
Brush crust lightly with mustard, if desired.
Spread Skyline chili on pizza crust.
Top with sliced hot dogs and/or onions.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake as indicated on pizza crust package.
Slice and serve!

title: ham delights
directions: Completely slice each roll through the middle, separating top
from	 bottom.
Cream
margarine,	poppy
seed, Worcestershire, mustard
and
onion.
Spread on top and bottom of rolls. Add	ham and Swiss cheese evenly over rolls. Wrap in foil and bake
at
400°	for
minutes.
To serve, cut into individual rolls.

title: fluffy mashed potatoes
directions: Boil
potatoes	(peeled
and
cubed) in small amount of water with
salt	and
a	little margarine added until tender. The saucepan needs
to	have a tight lid and use a low setting on stove.
Mash the potatoes and some margarine together in an electric mixer.
A	small amount of cream cheese may be added. Add milk that has been warmed.	This causes the potatoes to be fluffy. Season with salt and pepper.

title: strawberry-banana split pie
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and 1/2 cup melted margarine, press into 8 x 12-inch pan.
Mix powdered sugar with remaining melted margarine and egg, pour on top of crust.
Cut bananas into long thin slices, place on top of sugar mixture.
Add layers of pineapple and strawberries.
Spread top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Decorate with cherries.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes and margarine; set aside.
Mix sour cream, chicken soup, onions, salt, pepper and cheese.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put layer of potatoes and layer of cream mixture.
Repeat. Top with corn flakes and magarine, melted and mixed.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: frosty orange cooler
directions: In pitcher, combine water, juice concentrate, lemon juice and sugar; stir until sugar dissolves.
Chill.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Scoop sherbet in glasses; pour juice mixture over sherbet.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Put rice in long pan.
Pour in water.
Pour in soup.
Lay raw pork chops on top.
Cover pan with foil and place in oven.
Bake for 1 hour at 250°.

title: anisette biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients together with a fork.
Pour onto cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown.
Take out of oven; slice into long cookies.
Turn on side; brown.
Turn to other side; brown.
Takes approximately 40 minutes.

title: diet oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° until done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: holland butter cookies
directions: Cream all together and spread on greased cookie sheet.
Beat egg white stiff and spread over dough lightly.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 375° oven.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Combine cabbage, green pepper, celery, onion, tomatoes, sugar, salt and pepper in a large covered skillet (sprayed with Mazola). Cook, covered, over moderate heat about 20 minutes. Add 1 tablespoon water if dry. Add turkey or kielbasa sausage and cook until heated through.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: flavored pumpkin(popular and good)
directions: Halve or quarter pumpkin and remove seeds and stringy part. Cut into 2-inch pieces.
Slice off skin at random to give surface a mottled look and to enable flavor of dashi to steep in.

title: chocolate caramels
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Cook until candy forms a firm ball in cold water (245° on candy thermometer). Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Do not scrape pan.
Nuts can be pressed into top, if desired.
Let cool.
Cut into 3/4-inch squares.
Let dry.
Wrap.
Makes 144 caramels.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat; mix in large bowl or do separately on plates. Makes 10 medium plates.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs slightly,
beat in sugar, then add oil.
Sift dry ingredients
together;
add
to
eggs
alternately
with zucchini.
Stir in vanilla and fold in raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° in 1
well
greased
loaf pan or Bundt pan for 45 minutes.

title: tasty slaw
directions: Place first four ingredients in kettle. Cover with boiling water.
Cover kettle and let stand 1 hour.
Drain well.
Return to kettle.
Add vinegar, sugar, celery and mustard seed.
Mix.
Store in refrigerator.
Keeps long time in tightly closed fruit jars.

title: brownie pie
directions: Melt butter and cocoa over low heat.
Beat egg 5 minutes, add sugar.
Add flour and vanilla, mix well.
Add nuts.
Grease two pie pans with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli carrot bake
directions: Coat a 2-quart baking dish with cooking spray; set aside. Combine cereal with margarine.
Set aside for topping.
Thaw broccoli and carrots.
Drain broccoli well.
Spread vegetables in prepared baking dish.
Stir together soup and milk.
Pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle evenly with topping.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Bring water, potatoes, carrots and celery to boil; reduce heat and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add remaining ingredients; stir occasionally.
Ready to eat when cheese is melted.

title: fiesta casserole
directions: Crumble enough chips to cover bottom of 9 x 12-inch ovenproof casserole dish.
Saute meat, onions and taco mix until cooked, but not brown; drain liquid.
Spread meat mixture evenly over chips. Next, spread beans over meat mixture, then 1 cup cheese over beans.
Spread soup over the cheese.
Pour Ro-Tel tomatoes over cheese, spreading evenly.
Top off with remaining cheese.

title: peanut butter mousse pie
directions: Mix and pour into graham cracker crust.

title: blueberry cake delight
directions: Pour 2/3 of the cake mix in pan.
Bake and cool. Mix the cream cheese, pudding and milk together.
Pour over cold cake.
Spread pie filling on top and chill for 12 hours.
Serve with whipped cream on top (optional).

title: smoked mozzarella chicken
directions: Cook chicken on grill or stove with liquid smoke. Cut chicken in pieces. Cook pasta. Stir fry peppers and mushrooms in oil until done. Add all ingredients except cheese. Top with cheese, cook at 325 degrees, until cheese melts and is hot, (about 15 - 20 minutes).

title: baked potato salad
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Saute bacon until crisp; drain on paper towels and crumble.
Put bacon fat into a 1-cup measure; add enough oil to make 2/3 cup.
Pour into skillet.
Add onion, salt, pepper, vinegar and sugar.
Simmer, uncovered, for 3 minutes.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, lightly toss potatoes, green pepper, crumbled bacon and hot dressing.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes. Drain off excess liquid.
Makes 6 servings.

title: parmesan linguine with broccoli
directions: In a very large skillet or Dutch oven, saute garlic in 1/4 cup oil for 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Add broccoli.
Cook and stir for 5 minutes or until tender. Reduce heat.
Add hot linguine and remaining 1/4 cup oil. Toss thoroughly.
In a small bowl, mix well the milk and cheese.
Pour over linguine mixture, and over low heat, toss until cheese melts.
Add salt. Serve immediately. Makes 4 servings.

title: italian almond cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in following order: eggs, sugars, orange juice and oil. Add dry ingredients and fold in nuts.
Refrigerate for 10 minutes.
Flour hands/board and shape as for streudel (long strips).

title: egg rolls
directions: Combine vegetables in a deep bowl with salt; let stand for 15 minutes.
Drain off excess moisture.
Add remaining ingredients, except for the egg.
Place 2 tablespoons of filling in center of each egg roll skin.
Brush edges with egg.
Let egg sit 5 minutes to seal in filling.
Deep fry in 2 to 3 inches of oil at 325° until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with choice of sauce (plum or cherry).

title: pineapple deluxe cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and make 2 cake layers.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mayan chicken fricassee-guatemala(pollo en pepian dulce)
directions: Place chicken pieces in casserole dish.
Pour in chicken stock. Cover and simmer until almost tender, about 30 minutes.
Using a blender or food processor, grind the sesame and pumpkin seeds as fine as possible and shake through a sieve.
Set aside.
Put the peppers, tomatoes, onion and garlic into a blender or food processor and reduce to a course puree.
Mix the puree with ground sesame and pumpkin seeds.
Heat the vegetable oil in a skillet, add the puree, cook over medium heat stirring with a wooden spoon for 5 minutes.
Drain the chicken, save the stock and return the chicken to the casserole.
Add to the puree, 1 cup stock, the bitter orange juice, allspice, and salt and pepper to taste.
Stir and pour over chicken.
Cover and simmer gently until the chicken is tender, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Add a little more stock if necessary.
The sauce should be thick.
Soak the raisins in cold water for 15 minutes and drain.
Heat a little butter in a skillet and saut the almonds until golden, drain.
Transfer the chicken and sauce to a serving dish and sprinkle with almonds and raisins.
Serve with rice.

title: taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Thaw pie crust 10 minutes.
Prick bottom and sides of pie crust thoroughly with fork. Bake pie shell on cookie sheet for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and reduce temperature to 350°.

title: sausage spoon bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Stir in corn, sausage, egg and oil.
Turn into greased 1-quart glass baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese, grated.
Bake 5 minutes longer or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Yields 4 servings.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: In glass baking dish, add chili and cheese (cut in 1-inch cubes). Place in microwave and cook until cheese is melted. Stir and add sour cream. Top with green onions. Serve with corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: chicken and biscuits
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add flour and salt; blend until smooth.
Add chicken broth.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Then add sour cream, cayenne pepper sauce and chicken. Stir and simmer over low heat.
Make Bisquick biscuits and put around hot mixture.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Cover, simmer over low heat 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheese roll
directions: Blend the cheeses together.
Add garlic and sauces.
Mix thoroughly.
Add nuts and blend well.
Chill for 1 hour.
Sprinkle paprika on wax paper.
Pour cheese mixture on top and form into roll.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix butter, flour and powdered sugar until crumbly; pat into 9-inch square pan. Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Meanwhile, beat eggs, sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and baking powder. Add lemon juice and rind. Pour over crust and bake 25 minutes more. Cut into squares while still warm.

title: standard rolls
directions: Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt and cool to lukewarm. Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Stir and combine.
Add 1/2 flour and beat well.
Add more flour until right texture.
Turn onto lightly floured board and knead for about 10 minutes.
Put in greased bowl and let rise until double (2 hours).
Turn out and shape.
Place on greased pan and let rise 1/2 to 3/4 hour.
Brush with grease.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: blueberry angel food dessert
directions: Mix cream cheese with milk until smooth.
Blend in pudding, then fold in Cool Whip.
Pour mixture over angel food pieces that have been put in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Gently toss until pieces are coated.
Spread pie filling on top.
Chill and serve.

title: butter frosting
directions: Cream butter until soft.
Slowly stir in 1 cup sugar and the salt.
Add additional sugar alternately with cream, beating thoroughly after each addition until creamy and smooth.
Beat in vanilla.
Great on rolled sugar cookies.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Mix together and chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: hot fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit; reserve 1 cup apricot juice.
Add brown sugar and cornstarch to 1 cup apricot juice.
Pour mixture over fruit and bake until fruit is heated at 350°.

title: diabetic fruit cookies
directions: Simmer the first 3 ingredients for 3 minutes. Drop in the margarine and let cool. Add the flour, soda, vanilla and eggs. Mix well and drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Keep refrigerated when baked.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Stir in crackers until oil is absorbed. Keep in tightly covered container.
Real good to snack on.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Mix ingredients.
Form into ball.
Top with parsley, nuts or paprika.
Serve cocktail sauce on side with raw vegetables and crackers.

title: marinated venison steak
directions: Combine all ingredients to make marinade.
Place steaks in a shallow pan and cover with marinade.
Marinate at least 4 hours or overnight in refrigerator; the longer, the better.
Remove steaks from marinade.
Save marinade.
Grill over hot fire or broil for 2 to 3 minutes on each side, frequently brushing with marinade.
Do not overcook as venison will dry out

title: orange cake
directions: Cream butter and sugars, add eggs one at a time, beat after each addition.
Add orange rind.
Mix soda in buttermilk.
Add alternately with flour to creamed mixture.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) greased cake pans at 350° until cake is done.
Frost with Orange Cream Frosting.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls (about 2 tablespoons).
Drop into heated oil.
