(You can also fry it if you like.)

title: seven cup salad
directions: In a bowl, sprinkle sugar with cream.
Add oranges, coconut, pineapple and marshmallows.
Add nuts, if desired.
Stir together.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together except nuts.
Roll it in nuts. Serve it with Ritz crackers.

title: roast beef
directions: Put roast in crock pot. Season with salt and pepper. Add 2 cans cream of mushroom soup. Cook all day or over night.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Brown sausage; crumble and drain.
Add beef broth to sausage. Mix cornstarch and milk together, then slowly add to sausage and broth.
Cook until thick.
Serve over biscuits.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar and salt.
Add three eggs and beat.
Add three more eggs and beat.
Add milk.
Pour into uncooked crust and cook 10 minutes at 450°.
Turn heat down to 325° and bake 25 minutes longer until set.
If desired, sprinkle top with nutmeg just before baking.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Chill milk thoroughly and whip until thick.
Slowly add sugar. Slowly pour in lemon juice. Alternate cream and graham cracker crumbs in bowl or long dish.
Refrigerate.

title: never-fail peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk and salt for 10 minutes.
Add butter and continue boiling until mixture forms a soft ball in cold water. Remove from heat; add vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix thoroughly and pour quickly into a buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: breakfast bread
directions: Measure corn flakes; crush to 3/4 cup.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Measure margarine and sugar into large mixing bowl.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and orange peel; beat well.
Stir in orange juice.
Add dry ingredients, mixing only until combined.
Stir in nuts and raisins.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Put margarine in baking dish and melt. Mix peaches and 1/2 cup sugar and set aside.
Mix last 5 ingredients for batter.
Pour batter over melted butter, do not stir.
Pour sugared peaches over batter. Do not stir.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour until crust is light brown.

title: fabulous fruit dip
directions: Combine ingredients, mixing at medium speed on mixer until well blended.
Serve with fresh fruit chunks.
Yields 2 cups.

title: pickled carrots
directions: Wash and scrape the carrots.
Cut into shapes. Cook until tender in salted water. Drain and combine ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Add carrots and boil a few minutes longer.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: st. simon's shrimp dijon
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Dry with paper towels.
Melt margarine; add shrimp.
Saute 5 minutes.
Place shrimp in dish in low oven.
To skillet add wine, parsley, lemon juice, garlic, mustard and salt.
Cook 3 minutes.
Place shrimp in skillet.
Heat to serving temperature; do not overcook.
Serve over rice. Garnish with Parmesan cheese.

title: parsley, lemon and butter sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Add lemon juice and parsley.
Blend well and pour over fish, lamb chops or cooked vegetables, such as broccoli or cauliflower.

title: cucumber and sour cream salad
directions: Mix above and refrigerate.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine eggs, raisins and vanilla and let stand 1 hour at room temperature.
Cream shortening with both sugars until fluffy and light.
Sift flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon into creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Blend in egg mixture.
Stir in rolled oats and nuts.
Dough will be stiff.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen cookies.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Thaw broccoli.
Warm Cheese Whiz in microwave until runny.
Combine all ingredients.
Spray baking dish with Pam.
Pour mixture into pan.
Cook 350° until top is brown and mixture is thoroughly heated.

title: german chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Add buttermilk and mix.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Then add melted chocolate. Put in a greased and floured angel food cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Test with toothpick.
When it comes out clean, cake is done.
Put cake on dish and cover right away.

title: texas hash
directions: Fry onions and peppers lightly in shortening. Add meat and fry until mixture falls apart. Add tomatoes, rice and seasonings and mix. Bake in spray-coated and covered casserole at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cooked dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add egg yolks (slightly beaten), melted butter and milk.
Very slowly, add the vinegar.
Cook in top of double boiler until mixture thickens.
Cool.
Straining the dressing makes it fine grained.

title: tuna croquettes
directions: Mix together the tuna, 1/4 cup soup, 1/2 cup crumbs, onion, egg and lemon juice.
Makes 8 croquettes.
Roll in the remaining crumbs to coat.
Brown in combined butter and oil over medium heat.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve with mushroom sauce.
Serves 4.

title: cheesy cream potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Boil in salted water until tender, approx. 20 minutes. Drain.
Add 1/4 cup milk, 2 tbsp. margarine and beat with electric mixer until creamy.
Slice cheese into small chunks.
Add cheese and chopped onions back to potatoes and mix well over low heat until well blended.
Makes 4-6 servings.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Cook sweet potatoes (heat salted water to cover potatoes until boiling).
Add potatoes, cover and heat to boiling.
Cook 30 to 35 minutes; drain and slip off skins.
Mash potatoes.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Toss apples with brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Add remaining ingredients with above in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Dot with butter and cover.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave cheesy meat loaf sandwich
directions: Spread chili sauce on bread.
On four slices, place meat loaf and cheese.
Top with remaining bread.
Wrap each sandwich in paper napkin.
Arrange in glass oven tray.
Heat 2 to 4 minutes until heated through.
Cooking time:
4 minutes.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: caramel german chocolate brownies
directions: Blend cake mix according to box directions.
Cook 1/2 of mixture for 20 minutes at 350°.
Next, melt caramels with butter. Add evaporated milk and cook until real smooth.
Pour over cooled cake and sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips.
Add other 1/2 of cake mixture and bake for 20 minutes more.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: In large bowl, add crumbled cornbread, white bread, eggs, sage, onion, salt and pepper; stir. Slowly add liquid from cooked chicken. Pour into 9 x 11 pan. Cook at 350° until brown, approximately 1 hour.

title: ann's poppy seed cake
directions: Beat together all ingredients for 4 minutes (except Baker's Joy and powdered sugar); stir in seed.
Bake in Bundt pan coated with Baker's Joy.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Invert; sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: eslami cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the dry and wet ingredients separately and then slowly add the wet ingredients to the dry, mixing well.
Spread batter into a greased and floured baking pan. Place in oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: diabetic brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat vigorously until well blended.
Spread mixture into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut in 2 inch squares.

title: pistachio ice cream dessert
directions: Roll crackers.
Melt butter and sugar.
Add to crackers.
Pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix softened ice cream with pudding and milk.
Pour over crust.
Freeze in refrigerator overnight. Put Cool Whip on top when serving.

title: spicy glaced ham
directions: Bake in a slow 325° oven for 2 1/4 hours.
Mix brown sugar, corn syrup and mustard.
Baste ham.
Cook for 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix milk, brown sugar, flour and white sugar together; boil. Add oleo and vanilla.

title: senate's bean soup
directions: Wash navy beans in hot water.
Put beans and ham hocks in large heavy pot with 4 quarts of water.
Cook slowly for 3 1/2 hours.
Braise the chopped onion in butter and add to the soup. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 8.

title: supreme pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions on package.
Rinse and drain.
In large salad bowl, combine pasta, salad dressing and seasonings.
Toss in vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate.
Makes 4 or more servings.

title: hamburger taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain off fat.
Add pepper and onion and cook until tender.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well and heat thoroughly.
Serve with any kind of taco or tortilla chips. This is a very big recipe and kids love it.

title: hot dog go-round
directions: Set oven to 375°.
Rub butter on a cookie sheet.
Take a hot dog and cut 7 places but not all the way through.
(Do this to each hot dog you will need.)
Usually takes 2 hot dogs for each bun. Put hot dogs on cookie sheet.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
The hot dogs will turn and make a round circle when done.
Remove from oven.
Fix to each one's liking and enjoy.

title: pizza lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles until done.
Brown and drain hamburger. After noodles have cooled, get a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Start with a layer of noodles.
Add spaghetti sauce, hamburger, pepperoni and then Mozzarella cheese.
Do so until you have three layers.
Then add one more layer of noodles and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 15 to 20 minutes covered.
Then uncover and bake 5 more minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes and cut into squares.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet; drain fat. Mix all together. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until rice is done. Cover with grated cheese. Return to oven. Serve when cheese is melted.

title: honey and vinegar dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and mix until well blended.

title: delmonico potatoes
directions: In saucepan, heat milk, cream and spices over medium heat.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Place potatoes in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour cheese sauce over top and bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Peel and seed cucumber.
Grate cucumber (or chop finely).
Pat water out of cucumber on paper towel.
Mix ingredients.
Salt to taste.
Spread on bread.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix
the
soup,
mayonnaise,
mushrooms,
bell	pepper, onion, pimento and cheese well.
Mix with macaroni and put in ovenproof casserole.	Dot top with butter and cracker or bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt margarine in casserole.
Mix all ingredients in bowl. Pour into casserole and bake until firm in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: mindie's boiled cabbage
directions: Cut up cabbage.
Put in pot, cover with water.
Put bouillon cube in water with salt and pepper.
Boil until tender.

title: italian soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve with corn bread.

title: mo mo's pancakes
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix egg yolks, buttermilk, flour, salt, baking powder and sugar together.
Add melted butter. Fold in egg whites.
Cook on heated and lightly greased griddle. Flip.
Cook until light brown.

title: company potatoes
directions: Combine 1 lb of cheese, soup, sour cream and hash browns in a large mixing bowl.
mix thoroughly and pour into a lightly buttered 13 x 9 inch baking dish.
Sprinkle last pound of shredded cheese over top of potato mixture.
Bake at 375 degrees for 30-40 minutes.

title: pauline's lo-calorie potato salad
directions: Peel and cook potatoes until done, about 45 minutes.
Drain and let cool for an hour or so, then put in the refrigerator.
After the potatoes have cooled, add the chopped egg whites, pickles, onion, salt and pepper.
Just before you get ready to serve, make the dressing by combining the yogurt, mayonnaise and mustard.
Stir into the potatoes.
Sprinkle with parsley before serving.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs with fork until well mixed.
Stir in oil, vanilla and lemon; blend in sugar.
Add flour, baking powder and salt which had been sifted together.
Drop by teaspoonful 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet, lightly grease bottom of a glass (with oil) and dip in sugar and flatten cookie.
Keep dipping glass in sugar.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: chow chow
directions: Grind or cut up all ingredients real fine.
Put salt in and mix well.
Set 30 minutes, then drain.
Add sugar, vinegar and spices (tied up) and cook on low heat until done.
After coming to boil, cook about 2 more hours.
Makes about 12 pints.

title: helen's chicken
directions: Heat butter in skillet.
Add chicken and brown.
Remove chicken as browned.
Add fresh mushrooms; cook until tender. Remove from skillet.
Combine gravy mix, onion, catsup, water and wine in drippings, stirring constantly.
Add chicken to sauce. Cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes until chicken is tender.
Add mushrooms and olives.
Heat long enough to cook through.
Cook 1 cup rice according to directions on box.

title: buttered yeast rolls
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar.
Add Crisco.
Mix yeast with warm water.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well; refrigerate overnight. Roll out like biscuits; dip in melted butter.
Fold in half.
Let stand and rise for 2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken and broccoli; cut into large pieces.
Mix other ingredients together.
Layer casserole with sauce first, then chicken and broccoli.
Make 2 or 3 layers; end with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: holiday potato casserole
directions: Mix the ingredients together. Place in large casserole dish. Let stay overnight in refrigerator (a day or two is okay).
Melt margarine.
Mix with crushed cornflakes.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: apple cream pie
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients till smooth and creamy.
Line unbaked pie shell with apples. Pour the above mixture over apples, sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg, dot with butter.
Bake at 425° for 15 min. then turn oven down to 325° for 30 minutes or until custard is set.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until tender.
Peel and mash.
Mix with other ingredients.
Pour in baking dish.

title: irish bread
directions: Scald milk with butter.
Pour into a large bowl and cool.
Add sugar and salt.
Dissolve yeast cake in lukewarm water.
When milk has cooled, add the beaten egg and the yeast; stir well.
Add fruit and raisins, then the flour.
Beat well and let rise to double.
If not stiff enough to knead, add a little more flour but don't get too stiff; knead well.
Place in bowl and butter top.
Let rise to double; knead and shape into 2 loaves.
Let rise.
Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes.

title: elephant stew*
directions: Cut elephant into bite size pieces.
This will take about 2 months.
Cover with brown gravy and season to taste.
Cook over a fire at 465° for 5 weeks.
This will seve 3,999 people.
If more arrive, the 2 rabbits may be added, but do this with caution as most people do not like to fine hare in their stew.

title: corn pudding 2
directions: Mix these 3 ingredients in a casserole:
flour, sugar and salt.
Add milk to mixture.
Beat an egg with fork and add to mixture.
Add frozen corn.
Dot with butter.
Cook at 325° until firm.

title: joan's rum cake
directions: Grease one spring-back cheese cake pan.
Layer cookies on bottom of pan, cut cookies to fill gap.
Pour 1/2 cup rum on cookies.
Cook vanilla pudding and pour over layer of cookies. Place 2nd layer of cookies over pudding.
Pour remaining rum over cookies.
Cook chocolate pudding and pour over layers of cookies. Refrigerate 2 to 4 hours or overnight.
Remove cake from pan.
Whip heavy cream; add sugar and almond liqueur.
Cover cake with whipped cream and top with almonds.
tags: Stella D'Oro almond flavored crescent cookies

title: taco bean dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and garlic salt or powder.
Layer ingredients in order listed.
Serve with Chi Chi's stone ground white corn tortilla chips.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into greased casserole.
Set into a pan of water.
Bake at 350° until done (set).

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix chocolate pudding and pie filling.
Let come to a boil. Lower heat.
Cook slow for 3 minutes, stirring all the time. Remove.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Let cool a few minutes.
Beat until it thickens and loses gloss.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper or pour on waxed paper and cut into squares.

title: egg foo young
directions: Blend the mixture gently together with a fork. Heat about 1/2 cup salad oil in a skillet. Pour about 1/3 cup of the mixture for each cake in skillet. Flatten and shape each cake with a pancake turner. Turn when brown on the under side.

title: cheese-rice-broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli according to package but shorten cooking time to 1/2.
Drain well.
Mix all ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Put pineapple in mixing bowl; stir in pudding.
Mix in yogurt until smooth.
Pour in pie crust and top with Cool Whip.

title: spinach dip 1
directions: In medium bowl, stir spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise, soup mix, water chestnuts, and green onions.
Mix until well blended. Cover and chill for 2 hours to blend flavors.
Stir well before serving.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.

Cut shortening into flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt with pastry blender until mixture resembles fine crumbs. Stir in cheese and buttermilk until dough leaves side of bowl (dough will be soft and sticky).
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface.
Knead about 10 times. Roll or pat 1/2-inch thick. Cut with floured 2 1/2-inch round cutters.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet about 1-inch apart.
Bake until golden brown, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Yields 1 dozen biscuits.

title: frozen rhubarb jam
directions: Cook the rhubarb and sugar until tender.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Sprinkle on jello and mix well.
Pour into jars and refrigerate or freeze until needed.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, butter and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes (start timing after the mixture reaches a full, rolling boil).
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Drop onto wax paper by teaspoonfuls.
Add coconut or dates, if desired.

title: chili beef potato topper
directions: Microwave beef until done; drain any fat.
Stir in soup, water and chili sauce.
Cover and microwave 4 minutes.
Spoon over baked potatoes.
Top with grated cheese.

title: hamburger corn pone pie
directions: Cook onion in hot shortening until yellow.
Add beef and brown well.
Add seasonings, tomatoes and beans, simmer 15 minutes. Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole and top with cornbread batter, spread well to edge.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well and spread into rectangle baking pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Be sure to spray the pan with Pam before baking.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions, omitting salt or substituting seasoned salt, if desired.
Drain well; cool to room temperature.
Spoon into a large bowl; add chicken, grapes, water chestnuts and mayonnaise.
Toss gently with a fork.
Cover and chill.
Just before serving, add cashews, if desired.
Serve on lettuce leaves or line a bowl with lettuce leaves and fill with salad.
Serves 6.

title: tamale pie
directions: Layer Doritos, tamales, chili, cheese and green chilies until all ingredients are used.
Can be microwaved until warm or in a 350° oven until warm.

title: shoe peg salad
directions: Mix onion, pepper and celery.
Add drained peas, corn, pimientos and beans.
Mix and bring to a boil sugar, vinegar, oil, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Let this cool and pour over the salad.
Refrigerate.

title: open-faced sandwiches
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Let stand for awhile to blend flavors.
Spread on party rye bread or white bread cut with small round cutter.
Wait until just before serving and put a slice of cucumber on top and sprinkle with paprika for garnish. Party favorite!

title: chile n' cheese breakfast casserole
directions: Spread cut side of each english muffin with 1 tsp. butter, and place, buttered side down, in a lightly greased (13X9X2 inch) baking dish.
(I spray it with pam.)
Cook sausage in a skillet until browned, stirring to crumble, drain.
Layer half each of sausage, chiles, and cheese over English muffins.
Combine sour cream and eggs; pour over casserole.
Repeat layers with remaining sausage, chiles and cheese; cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Make a well in center.
Add eggs and oil.
Stir only until dry ingredients are moist.
Stir in strawberries and nuts.
Put in a well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Don't slice until next day.

title: keg of nails(jello dessert)
directions: Set jello the night before.
Mix well the next morning.
Use 13 x 9-inch pan or deep bowl.
Place layer of vanilla wafers, jello, pineapple, bananas, Cool Whip and nut meats.
Continue until all is used.
Save enough Cool Whip to frost the top, also nut meats.
Sprinkle nut meats over the top layer of Cool Whip.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Stir constantly on medium heat until thickened and boiling.
Boil 1 minute or microwave until clear and thickened.
Cool slightly.
Add 3 cups fresh blueberries; fold in. Pour into 9-inch baked pie shell.
Spread whipped cream or Cool Whip around outer edge of pie, leaving center uncovered.
Chill 3 hours.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Flatten chicken breasts with rolling pin or meat tenderizer.
Lay cheese and ham flat on chicken.
Roll up chicken so ham and cheese are on the inside of chicken.
Cover chicken with mayonnaise and water mixture, then roll in bread crumbs.
Put on baking sheet in oven; bake for 30 to 40 minutes, until chicken is cooked thoroughly.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Utensils needed are a Dutch oven, knife, mixing spoons, can opener and mixing bowl.

title: cheese beef ball
directions: Mix and form into ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: spaghetti sauce for the freezer
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
Cool and place in quart freezer bags.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers and put into casserole dish.
Top with crumbled crackers.
Pour melted margarine over crackers.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 15 to 20 minutes. (Double recipe for large casserole.)

title: dutch pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix together:
pumpkin, sugar, Crisco and egg.
Add flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, cloves and allspice.
Mix well.
Add vanilla, raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Drizzle with a thin powdered sugar icing while cookies are still hot.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: hot turkey salad
directions: Combine ingredients, except cheese and potato chips; toss lightly.
Pile lightly into individual bakers, or custard cups.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Shred enough cabbage to line baking dish or more if you like cabbage real well.
Brown meat, onion and pepper; drain.
Add tomato sauce, vinegar, salt, pepper and rice mix to meat mixture. Line dish with cabbage.
Add layer of potatoes, layer of beef mixture and top layer of cabbage.
Bake at 325° until tender, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Bake cake and let cool.
Put holes in cake with straw and put strawberries on top.
Next put pudding and then Cool Whip on cake.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine and stir in dressing.
Grease 8 x 10-inch casserole.
Put layer of crumbs and layer of chicken.
Mix soup with 1 can of broth.
Pour some of soup mixture over crumbs and chicken.
Repeat crumbs, chicken and soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: valentine fruit punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water.
Add orange juice and lemonade. Mix until thawed.
Add ginger ale or 7-Up.
Mix and freeze.
Thaw to a slush for serving.
Makes 2 1/2 gallons.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: In a 6 quart pan, boil water.
Add butter, salt and macaroni. Cover and turn off fire.
In a large skillet, brown ground beef, and onion until the meat is well cooked, drain.
Add garlic, chili powder, tomatoes and onions.
Cook five minutes.
Drain macaroni, add meat mixture and simmer five minutes.
Serve with salad and bread sticks.

title: wheat germ crust
directions: Combine flour with wheat germ, brown sugar, salt and cinnamon in a bowl.
Cut in shortening and butter.
Add milk to hold together.
Work dough; press into pan and prick bottom.
Bake on baking sheet at 375° on low shelf for 20 minutes or golden brown.

title: orange sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Beat eggs and rind into mixture. Sift and add 1/2 dry ingredients to creamed mixture; mix well. Add vanilla, milk and remaining dry ingredients.
Chill well. Roll 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured board.
Cut into desired shapes with cookie cutter.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: "s.l.o.p."(serves lots of people)
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add all other ingredients and simmer.
Can be served in a crock-pot to keep warm.
Serve as a hearty dip with heavy-weight chips.

title: orange cookies
directions: Cream sugar and 2 sticks butter.
Add eggs and sour cream alternately with dry ingredients.
Add juice and rind of 2 oranges.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Check after 5 minutes.
Bake until done.

title: fruit-stuffed pork roast
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add apple, onion, celery, apricots and raisins.
Cook, stirring frequently, about 5 minutes or until onion is tender.
Stir in stuffing mix, thyme, marjoram, salt and pepper.
Lay meat, fat-side up, on a cutting board. Butterfly by cutting in half horizontally almost through opposite side.
Cover cut-side with plastic wrap and pound to flatten.
Top with stuffing mixture, mounding slightly down center.
Pull sides together and secure with toothpicks.
Tie meat with string about 8 times.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 325°.

title: sweet and super salad dressing(a favorite with my "salad bar group"!)
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Combine the first four ingredients thoroughly in a blender.
Add onion.
Very gradually add the vegetable oil.
Add the celery seed.
Let stand 1 to 2 hours.
Add more vinegar if it's too sweet.

title: slaw
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: butter rolls
directions: Combine warm water and yeast; set aside.
Add yeast mixture to cold milk mixture; add flour, cover and set in refrigerator for 15 minutes.
Remove and roll out on floured dough board.
Chuck 1/2 stick oleo over top.
Fold up, cover and put back into refrigerator for 15 minutes.
Repeat this procedure 3 more times; after all oleo is used, set in refrigerator 15 more minutes.
Remove, roll out and cut into rolls.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: easy refrigerator pickles
directions: Place half of cucumber in a large bowl.
Top with half of onion.
Repeat layers with remaining cucumber and onion.
Combine vinegar and remaining ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Stir well. Bring to a boil over medium heat; boil 1 minute.
Pour hot mixture over cucumber and onion.
Let cool.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator at least 4 days, stirring twice each day.
Yields 7 cups (37 calories and 2% fat per 1/4 cup serving).
Protein 0.3, fat 0.1 (saturated fat 0), carbohydrate 9.5, fiber 0.3, cholesterol 0, sodium 44.

title: bacon and cheese oven omelet
directions: Cook bacon, cut cheese in half, arrange in bottom of a lightly buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Beat together eggs and milk.
Add chopped bacon. Pour over cheese and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before eating.
Ortega chilies optional.

title: beef and spinach pinwheels
directions: In a large bowl, combine eggs, crackers, onion and salt.
Add beef and mix well.
On foil, pat mixture into a 10-inch square; set aside.

title: pastel peppermint patties
directions: Beat syrup and margarine, blending well.
Add peppermint flavoring and salt.
Mix in confectioners sugar.
Knead until smooth.
Tint with food color.
Shape into 1 to 1 1/2-inch round patties.
Top with pecan halves.

title: tortilla roll with mustard dip
directions: Blend cream cheese, ham, chilies and olives together.
Spread evenly on
tortillas.
Roll tortillas jellyroll style; cover with plastic wrap and a damp cloth.
Refrigerate 4 hours.
Cut in 1/2-inch slices.
Serve with mustard dip.

title: hoagy sauce
directions: In a quart saucepan, stir together spaghetti sauce, lemon juice, brown sugar, onion, mustard and Worcestershire sauce over moderate heat, stirring often.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over leftover beef on buns or favorite loaf bread. Makes 1 1/3 cups sauce.
Serve hot or store in refrigerator and heat as needed.

title: turkey-rice skillet
directions: In a large skillet cook turkey until brown; drain well.
Stir in tomatoes, water, rice, chili powder and pepper.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir together milk and flour; add to skillet. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 minute more.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fudge cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs.
Add flour, sour cream and hot water.
Then add 1 teaspoon soda which has been dissolved in cold water (small amount).
Melt chocolate over hot water in double boiler.
Add chocolate to cake, saving some for icing if you want. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add 2 tablespoons water.
Cover and cook on High 11 to 13 minutes.
Turn potatoes halfway through cooking.
Combine onion, pepper and margarine in 1-quart dish.
Cook on High for 4 to 6 minutes, stirring once. Stir in flour, then milk, salt and pepper.
Cook on High 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir once.
Stir in 3/4 cup cheese.

title: sweet and sour brussels sprouts
directions: Thirty minutes before serving:
In a 6-quart saucepan, over medium-low heat, saute bacon until browned.
Remove to paper towels with slotted spoon.

title: roughy in butter sauce
directions: Pat the fish dry; salt and pepper to taste.
Dredge in flour. Shake off excess.
Heat 1/2 tablespoon of vegetable oil and 1 1/2 tablespoons of butter in a large skillet.
When butter is hot, place fish in skillet and cook for 5 minutes.
Carefully turn with spatula and cook for 5 more minutes.
Place on serving platter and sprinkle with lemon juice and parsley.
Melt additional butter (2 tablespoons); when it turns light brown, pour it over fish.

title: hot chile cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese.
Add onion, tomatoes, chilies and seasonings. Stir constantly until blended.
Serve in a chafing dish.
Add milk if it gets too stiff.

title: papaya crisp
directions: Mix papaya, tapioca, lemon juice, raisins, 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg well.
Pour into a 9-inch square baking pan. Combine remaining 1/2 cup sugar and flour.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle over papaya mixture.
Bake, uncovered, in 400° oven for 45 minutes or until lightly brown. May be served with ice cream.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Soften bread with milk.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Bake in deep casserole dish for 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven. Pineapple juice can be used, adding milk to make 1 cup.
Not like a custard.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream the cream cheese and butter.
Gradually add sugar, nuts and flour.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheets and flatten dough with wet finger until wafer-thin.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix cheese; add nuts (save some to roll ball in).
Sprinkle in garlic salt to taste.
Make long roll, then roll it in paprika and red pepper.
Chill then slice round slices.
Put on crackers.

title: favorite hermits
directions: Note:
For soft cookies, store Hermits with orange rind or a crust of bread in cookie jar.

title: hello dolly's
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

In oven, melt butter in 13 x 9 pan. Spread crushed crackers and pat down. Add in following coconut, chocolate chips and pecans. Pour sweetened condensed milk over all. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: date cake
directions: Pour the boiling water over the dates, walnuts and soda. Stir.
Add the sugar, shortening, salt and vanilla.
Stir well. Add the flour and mix well.
Put in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until tested done.
When cool, frost with Penuche Frosting.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, egg and some of the milk.
Mix the bananas with the remainder of milk.
Add dry ingredients gradually.
Add nuts.
Grease and flour pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: southern style okra
directions: Cook salt pork, onion and green pepper in skillet until pork is golden.
Stir in okra; cook over medium high heat, stirring constantly, for 3 minutes.
Stir in corn and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer until corn is tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Yield 4 servings.

title: plum cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in greased tube pan at 350° for 70 minutes.

title: one bowl macaroons
directions: Mix coconut, sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in egg whites and almond extract.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Remove from baking sheet immediately.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain fruits of liquid and add water to make 1 cup.
Use 2 cups boiling water.
Chill until firm.

title: baked herb rice
directions: Brown rice in butter for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Combine rice, 3 1/4 cups consomme and herbs in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour, stirring several times. Stir in remaining 3/4 cup consomme, vegetables and almonds. Stir well. Cover and bake for 45 minutes.
Makes about 10 servings.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Cut Twinkies in half, lengthwise through the top so there will be filling in both halves.
Line a baking dish with these.
Mix the pudding mix, sour cream and milk together and pour one-half of mixture over Twinkies.
Put a layer of fruit (bananas, peaches, strawberries, etc.) over pudding mixture and then pour remaining pudding mixture over fruit.
Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with nuts or coconut if desired.
Best if made ahead of time and refrigerated overnight.

title: overnight salad
directions: Layer all ingredients, except last 3 items.
Blend sugar with mayonnaise or Miracle Whip and spread over salad.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Refrigerate 8 to 12 hours.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Salt brisket heavily with garlic salt, onion salt, ancho chili powder and brown sugar, covering both sides. Marinate 24 hours in liquid smoke and Worcestershire sauce. Pour off liquid. Wrap brisket in foil loosely with room inside with ends tightly closed. Bake in a 275° oven for 5 to 6 hours. Last hour, open foil and brush with barbecue sauce over entire brisket. Leave foil folded back during last hour.

title: best cake frosting
directions: Mix required cake for each recipe according to package directions, adding extra ingredients.

title: cheese charmers
directions: Have cheese and oleo at room temperature.
Add flour and mix well.
Chill dough and divide into 3 parts.
Roll each third into a circle.
Cut into pie-shaped pieces.
Roll up as for crescent rolls, and place point down on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Drizzle a mixture of powdered sugar and milk on top.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Let sit 5 minutes in the bottom of a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together.
Cut margarine into dry ingredients.
Add milk.
Shape to cover fruit.
Slit top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or frozen yogurt.
Yields 4 servings at 360 calories per serving.

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown meat, onion and bell pepper.
Drain.
Then add broth and rice.
Cook in medium saucepan until rice is done.
You might have to add a little water to make sure the rice is well done.
Serve hot.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans well.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.

title: plum delicious brownies(low-fat)
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Mix next five together and add to first mixture.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350° in pans sprayed with cooking spray.
Makes 25 brownies.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup of hot water.
Add about 4 or 5 cans of water and a little sugar, if any.

title: dorothy's strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in heavy saucepan.
Add water and stir.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Add jello, butter, lemon and stir slowly until jello dissolves.
Clean strawberries; halve or quarter them.
Place in shell (amount optional).
Pour glaze over; chill.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: cottage cheese pie
directions: Mix together the oleo, sugar, flour, lemon juice, lemon rind, eggs and cottage cheese.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° until brown and done.

title: two minute microwave fudge
directions: Sift together sugar and cocoa.
Place in 1 quart microwave safe dish.
Place margarine on top and pour milk over the dry mixture.
Microwave on high for 2 minutes.

title: very easy chocolate pie
directions: Mix pudding according to box directions. Pour into cooled pie crust. Chill for 1 hour. Top with marshmallows and brown in oven on broil.

title: party pig
directions: Prepare fire in outdoor (cooker) grill.
Let it burn for at least an hour to establish a steady cooking temperature.
Skewer the sow, using the stainless steel rods.
Salt the pig both inside and outside.
Pepper as desired.
As the pig begins to brown, turn every 20 to 30 minutes.
Meat must register 375° throughout to be fully cooked.
Total cooking time, though depending on fire, will be approximately 24 hours.
Sprinkle water on fire when flames appear.
Serve on an 8 foot table.
Place apple in mouth.
Enjoy! (Serves approximately 100 people.)

title: easy lime jello salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water, then mix in pineapple, lemon juice and milk. Refrigerate until set.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Mix ingredients well, then add zucchini.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes on a greased cookie sheet.

title: salsa bean dip
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Blend on grind for 10 to 30 seconds; should be lumpy.

title: pumpkin pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, Karo syrup, sugar, pumpkin, vanilla and salt. Stir in pecans and melted margarine.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool. Serve with whipped cream; garnish with pecans.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine in a gallon jar and finish filling with water.
When ready to serve, add 1 large ginger ale and 2 quarts of sherbet. Serves 20.

title: chicken wings(appetizers)
directions: Cut tips off chicken wings.
Bring to boil rest of ingredients.
Pour over chicken wings in baking dish.
After marinating for at least an hour, bake at 350° until they are finished, approximately one hour.
Serve hot.
May be frozen and reheated.
Serves 8 to 10 guests.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in a large pot over low heat until soft.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk and bouillon cubes.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened. Add broccoli, 2 cups of the cooking water, pepper and garlic powder.
Simmer approximately 15 minutes, then add the cheese. Simmer another 10 to 20 minutes, until the cheese is melted, stirring constantly.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix corn, green beans, cheese, celery, onion and green pepper. Mix sour cream and soup and add to vegetables.
Mix the Cheese Nips, melted butter and almonds together.
Spread on top of vegetables.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Bake devil's food cake as directed on the box. Pour sweetened condensed milk on cake while still hot. Let cool. Cover with Cool Whip. Crumble Butterfinger candy bars and spread across top.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Mix 3 cups flour and butter or Crisco like pie crust.
Add milk and yeast to flour mixture.
Add beaten eggs and salt.
Add last cup of flour.
Knead well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Take out, divide into 6 parts and roll each like a pie crust.
Cut into 6 wedge-like pieces and roll large end towards the center to form crescent like shapes.
Let rise and bake until golden.
Makes 36 rolls.
Frost, if desired, with powdered sugar frosting.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar. Add eggs, apples and nuts. Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a square 8-inch pan.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Mix shrimp, cream cheese, onion and Worcestershire sauce with mixer.
Form into a ball.
Top with cocktail sauce.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Cook sugar, salt, catsup and vinegar until like syrup.
Mix cornstarch in water until dissolved.
Add to cooking mixture in a circular fashion and stir constantly (mixture has a tendency to bubble over a few seconds after adding cornstarch).
After stirring well, lower temperature to simmer.
Stir occasionally. Should be ready in about 10 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Place fruit in 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Pour over fruit.
Bake in a 300° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Crush enough Rice Krispies, about 3 cups, to coat each piece of chicken.
Dip the chicken in buttermilk, then in Rice Krispies. Spray each side of the chicken.
Place on a greased baking sheet. Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: favorite pancakes
directions: Stir all dry ingredients together.
Stir all wet ingredients together.
Put them together; hand stir.
(The batter will be lumpy.)
It will make 12 large pancakes.

title: seasoned rice
directions: Cook 1 hour at 325°.
Stir once.

title: sloppy joze
directions: Brown and season meat; add ingredients and mix well.
Heat and serve.
May add diced onions, red or green peppers and tomatoes.

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in next 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Pour mixture into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until filling is set.
Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: pineapple fluff cake
directions: Beat egg whites with salt to form moist, glossy peaks. Gradually beat in 3/4 cup sugar.
Beat egg yolks and 3/4 cup sugar until thick; add lemon and pineapple juices.
Beat until sugar dissolves.
Add flour sifted with baking powder.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in 10-inch, ungreased, angel cake pan in moderate oven (325°) for 1 hour.
Invert to cool.

title: fruit coffee cake
directions: *Substitute plums with apples/raisins and 1 can cherry pie filling when plums are not in season.

title: strawberry jello-pretzel dessert
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together; pat in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix the cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip; mix well.
Put on top of pretzel crust. Dissolve the jello in the boiling water and cold water.
Add the strawberries.
When jelled, put over the cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: sweet and savory spread
directions: Stir together cream cheese, mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar until creamy. Fold in remaining ingredients. Refrigerate. Serve on favorite crackers, bagel chips or Melba toast. Yield: approximately 1 cup.

title: whipped cream frosting
directions: Mix flour and milk in a saucepan.
Cook over low flame until thick.
Put in saucer and cool.
Cream butter and shortening for 4 minutes with electric mixer.
Add sugar gradually and beat for 4 minutes.
Add flour paste and beat for 4 minutes.
Add vanilla and blend.

title: basic sweet dough
directions: Combine milk, sugar and butter in small saucepan.
Heat over low heat until butter melts and sugar dissolves.
Cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in warm water in warmed bowl.
Add lukewarm milk mixture and 5 cups of flour.
Attach bowl and dough hook.
Turn to speed 2 and mix 3 minutes.
Continue on speed 2. Add remaining flour, 1/2 cup at a time, until dough clings to hook and cleans side of bowl, about 5 minutes.
Knead on speed 2 for 3 to 5 minutes longer.

title: light carob chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 2 baking sheets with vegetable spray.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
When set, add Cool Whip.
In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass dish, put a full layer of graham crackers.
Cover with half of the filling.
Top with layer of graham crackers, then frost.
Prepare the night before or early in the day.
Keep refrigerated.
Serves 12 to 15 people.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Microwave marinated chicken breasts about 2 minutes, then grill until done.
Dice chicken and add to cooked pasta.
Cut vegetables and toss with vinaigrette.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients until tender.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix and bake as you would chicken and dressing.

title: summer coolness
directions: Cream the flour and margarine together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Let cool.

title: mimi's mexican chicken soup
directions: Saute onion, garlic and bell pepper in oil until soft and fragrant.
Add chicken broth; bring to boil.
Add lime or lemon juice, chicken and rice.
Add tomatoes and cilantro.
Turn off heat.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Garnish with extra cilantro.

title: tomato soup salad
directions: In microwave, heat tomato soup to boiling point.
Add cream cheese and the dissolved Jell-O.
Beat until smooth.
(I like a blender, if you have one.)
Add dressing and blend some more.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a sprayed mold.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Brown beef; drain fat.
Add onion, garlic, parsley, water, tomato paste, pepper and salt; bring to a boil.
Turn heat to low; simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
In a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, layer meat sauce, Mozzarella cheese and noodles.
Start with noodles.
Make 3 layers.
Top with Mozzarella cheese; sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, until top of cheese is melted.
Can make ahead and freeze.
Serve with rolls and salad.

title: hot tuna dip
directions: Mix ingredients and serve.

title: thanksgiving dinner in a dish
directions: In medium bowl, mix bread cubes, oleo and 1 1/4 cups broth. In another bowl, mix chicken, 3/4 cup broth, chives, onion, celery, salt and mayonnaise.
Spread 1/2 of bread mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread chicken mixture on top and top this with rest of bread mixture.
Whisk eggs, milk and soup in bowl and pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: simple eggnog
directions: Using an electric mixer or whisk, beat eggs with sugar until light and thoroughly combined.
Beat in 2 cups of milk.
Cook the mixture, stirring constantly, until it reaches 170° on candy thermometer
and thickens slightly.
Remove custard from the heat and stir in 2 more cups of milk.
Chill the mixture thoroughly.
Whip the heavy cream and fold the whipped cream into the chilled egg and milk mixture.
Serve sprinkled with nutmeg.

title: manicotti
directions: Sauce:
Saute onion, garlic and meat in olive oil.
Add tomatoes and spices; cook slowly until thick.

title: bisquick-glazed raisin-cinnamon biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients except Vanilla Glaze until dough forms; beat 20 strokes.
Turn onto cloth-covered board well dusted with baking mix.
Gently roll to coat; shape into ball. Knead 10 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with 2 1/2-inch cutter dipped in baking mix.

title: refrigerator toll house cookies
directions: 375° oven for 8-10 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Mix pretzels, 1/4 cup sugar and melted margarine.
Spread in 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool. Cream softened cream cheese and sugar.
Beat in Cool Whip.
Spread gently over cooled pretzel crust and chill.
Add boiling water to Jell-O.
Chill until it begins to thicken.
Stir in defrosted berries.
Pour over cheese layer and chill until firm.
Serves 8.

title: evan's mudslide
directions: Mix pudding and milk together. Fold in Cool Whip. Layer graham crackers and pudding mixture. Pour melted frosting over last layer of graham crackers. Refrigerate.

title: coffee tin bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, water and fruit.
Mix flour, baking soda, salt and spices together and slowly add to first mixture.
Add nuts, raisins and dates (if desired).
Pour into greased 1 pound coffee tins; bake in 350° oven approximately 1 hour.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding 1 beaten egg at a time.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cowboy cookie mix
directions: Pour oats into a wide-mouth 1 quart glass jar with a tight-fitting lid.	Combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; place on top of oats.
Layer with pecans, chocolate chips, brown sugar and sugar, packing each layer tightly, do not mix.
Cover and store in a cool dry place for up to 6 months.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Measure flour and baking powder into bowl. Add butter and blend well until mixture is consistency of cornmeal. Stir in 1 egg and the milk. Mix until a soft dough is formed. Spread evenly into 8 or 9-inch square pan. Spread raspberry jam over dough. Stir together remaining egg, sugar, butter, coconut and vanilla. Spread over jam. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is lightly browned. Once cool, cut into 2-inch squares.

title: cherry sauce
directions: In saucepan boil the vinegar with sugar over moderate heat until reduced to a glaze.
Add wine, shallots and cinnamon stick. Boil until reduced to 1/4 cup.
Add broth and cherries; simmer for 5 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in water; stir this cornstarch mixture and add enough to the sauce, stirring, to thicken to desired consistency.
Simmer for 2 minutes.
Discard cinnamon stick.
Stir in lime juice.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Keep sauce warm and covered.
Excellent with roasted chicken or barbecued pork!

title: whipped cream
directions: In a chilled bowl combine whipping cream, sugar and vanilla. Beat with chilled beaters of an electric mixer on medium speed until soft peaks form.
Serve with pie, fruit desserts, cake, cream puffs and hot drinks.
Makes 2 cups (8 servings).

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Mix
together
flour, salt and baking powder.
Add egg, zucchini and enough milk to make a batter.	Drop by tablespoon into hot
oil.
Roll in sugar or margarine.
Serve with melted cheese.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; beat in eggs.
Add vanilla and milk.
Mix in sifted dry ingredients.
On floured board, roll and cut cookies.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: apple-stick relish
directions: Mix apples, onion and pickle.
Combine sugar and vinegar. Toss with apple mixture.
Chill.
Serve as meat accompaniment.

title: karo pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding pecans last.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes longer or until a silver knife inserted in center of pie comes out clean.
Pecans or shredded coconut may be substituted for pecans.
If salted nuts are used, omit salt in recipe.

title: vanillekranse(danish vanilla rings-butter cookies)
directions: Mix all the ingredients together into a dough and set aside to cool about 30 minutes.
(Refrigerate if too sticky.)
Use a cookie press (use star plate).
Fill cookie press and squirt out in long strips on table.
Cut into 3-inch lengths and form rings.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in slow oven until golden brown. Makes 150.

title: very special salad
directions: Prepare lemon jello according to directions on the jello package.
Drain the pineapple, reserving the juice.
Add the pineapple to the jello mixture along with 1/4 cup chopped nuts. Set in refrigerator overnight.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix grated cheese and margarine.
Add flour and salt; mix well.
Stir in Rice Krispies and cayenne pepper.
Flatten each ball with a fork after shaping into small balls on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool and store in airtight container to keep crisp.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: spiced sugar pecans
directions: Stir pecan meats in slightly beaten egg whites until moist. Mix sugar, salt and cinnamon in large bowl; add pecans and mix until coated well.
Place coated pecans on a cookie sheet and bake at 275° for 1 hour stirring every 15 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, soup, celery, onion, water chestnuts and mayonnaise.
Add 1 cup cornflakes.
Mix well and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top and dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll and form into a bar. Chill in refrigerator, then slice and bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Makes about 50 cookies.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off grease.
Add the rice, beans and soup.
Top with the Doritos.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of pan. Spread chili on top of this. Spread green chilies on top of the chili and add shredded cheese on top. Bake at 350° until cheese melts, about 15 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: In a small bowl, mix mayonnaise, sugar and milk.
Set aside. In another larger bowl, put in the peas and add the onion.
Now add the mayonnaise mixture and salt and pepper.
Refrigerate for at least an hour before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle some bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Heat, drain and mash sweet potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water, half should be boiling. Let it cool and then add the remaining ingredients.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch dish and let set.

title: pea and peanut salad
directions: Cook peas according to package directions.
Chill.
Mix with peanuts, cheese, celery and onion.
Mix remaining ingredients and fold into pea and peanut mixture.
Serves 8 (?).
May be served on lettuce or other greens, or plain.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to directions on package.

title: cucumber onion sandwiches
directions: Mix well all ingredients, adding spoons of canned milk to thin.
Spread on white bread and top with whole wheat.
Cut into finger sandwiches.
Can be made in advance and refrigerated.

title: apple fritters
directions: Stir until mixed (batter will be lumpy).
Drop by small teaspoonfuls into deep fat (350° to 375°).
Fry until golden brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Shake in bag with 10x sugar and cinnamon.
If some are to be kept, don't put sugar on them.
Heat them again and then put sugar on them.

title: diet fudge
directions: Set aside 1/4 cup crumbs.
Combine milk, cocoa and oleo in saucepan.
Bring to a
boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in crumbs, vanilla, Equal and nuts.
Mix well.
Cool until easy to handle. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in reserved crumbs.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Yield: 36.
Exchange: 1 fudge equals 1/2 bread, 1/2 fat and 57 calories.

title: carrot or apple salad
directions: Mix well.
Chill for few hours or overnight.
May garnish with mandarin oranges.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; debone.
Layer chips in a cake pan.
Mix deboned chicken, hot sauce and soup all together.
Spread mixture over the tortilla chips, then sprinkle the 3 types of grated cheese over to make the first layer.
Continue this process for layers 2 and 3.

title: rich devil's food
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter or margarine and sugar. Add eggs and beat well.
Alternate flour with sour cream, beginning with flour and ending with flour (3 flour and 2 sour cream additions).
Add cooled chocolate mixture last.
Add vanilla.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Test with a toothpick until crumbs remain on pick.
Can also use 2 (8-inch) round pans.
Frost with desired icing.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Sprinkle dry yeast over warm water in a large bowl, let set for 3 minutes. Add cake mix, 1 c. flour, eggs, oil and salt. Beat with mixer until bubbles appear. Add 5 1/4 c. flour, stir. Makes a soft dough.

title: glorified rice
directions: Dissolve jello in 3 cups boiling water.
Add cold, cooked rice, pineapple, almond extract, vanilla extract and sugar. Place in refrigerator until hardened.
Break with fork.
Fold in Dream Whip.

title: instant french onion soup
directions: Heat soup. Combine cheeses. Place a 1/2 inch slice of toasted French bread on bottom of each of four 1 1/2 to 2 cup ovenproof soup bowls. Sprinkle each with 1/2 cheese mixture. Top with another slice of toasted bread. Spoon hot soup into bowls, top with remaining cheese, and broil for 4 minutes or until cheese bubbles and browns. Makes 4 servings.

title: taco pie dip
directions: Mix sour cream and taco mix in bowl.
Cut up lettuce, tomato and onion into small pieces.
Place hamburger in bottom of pie plate and layer sour cream mixture on top.
Place vegetables over this.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour. Serve with any kind of chip.

title: plain pot roast
directions: Coat entire surface of meat in oil and brown.
Roast in 300° oven for 25 to 30 minutes per pound.
Salt near end of cooking time.
When done, remove from pan.

title: steak roquefort
directions: Sprinkle steaks with salt and pepper.
Cook steaks in a medium skillet over medium heat for 8 minutes on each side or to a desired degree of doneness.
Remove steaks to a serving platter, discarding drippings in skillet.
Set steaks aside and keep warm.

title: cornmeal and herb chicken coating
directions: Combine all ingredients.
To use, place 1 cup in plastic bag. Shake chicken pieces until coated.
Place on baking pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Store unused mixture in airtight container. Recipe makes enough for 3 chickens (each 2 1/2 to 3 lb.).
Great coating on fish or pork chops, also.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with mayonnaise.
Stir in Italian dressing mix.
Chill about 1 hour.

title: apple butter pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10-inch tube pan or a 12-inch Bundt pan.
Beat together sugar, margarine and cream cheese in a large bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Combine baking powder, flour, corn meal, cinnamon and salt.
Combine apple butter, bourbon and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Alternately add dry ingredients and apple butter mixture to cream cheese mixture, mixing at low speed until thoroughly blended.
Stir in pecans.
Spoon batter into prepared pan and spread evenly to edges.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted into the center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes in pan and then remove to a wire rack.
Cool completely.

title: gallon muffin mix
directions: Mix together the All Bran and boiling water and set aside to cool.
In a large bowl mix the shortening, applesauce, sugar, molasses eggs, buttermilk and the All Bran mixture.
Add the flour, soda, salt and oatmeal.
Stir in raisins, nuts or dates. Fill muffin cups full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
This recipe makes 6 dozen muffins.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Sift flour and salt, then set aside.
Combine orange candy, dates, nuts and coconut.
Add 1/2 cup of flour to this mix.
Set aside.
Work 1 cup of butter and sugar; beat well.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add baking soda and buttermilk.
Now add flour and candy mix.
Then mix well.

title: hard candy
directions: Spread large sheet of aluminum foil onto countertop. Turn sides up to form pan. Sift a heavy coating of powdered sugar over the foil; don't spare sugar (it may be reused). The sugar keeps the candy from sticking. Bring cane sugar, Karo and water to boil, 309° on candy thermometer. Remove from heat; add cinnamon oil and coloring. Pour onto foil and sift powdered sugar on top. Let cool, then break into small pieces. Other flavors and color may be used.

title: quick potato fudge
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over hot water in a double boiler. Add mashed potatoes, salt and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Blend in confectioners sugar.
Knead until smooth.
Press into a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool.
Remove and cut into squares.
Yields 1 1/4 pounds.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli and place in bottom of casserole.
Place chicken on top of broccoli.
Make a sauce out of last 4 ingredients and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle on grated cheese.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Uncover towards the end to brown.
Serve over rice.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together in a large pot.
Cook for 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve over noodles.

title: coconut refrigerator roll
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in mixing bowl and work with hands into a firm ball.
Shape into a roll 6 inches long.
On a sheet of wax paper, mix coconut and chopped walnuts.
Coat roll by rolling and pressing into coconut-walnut mixture.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate for 12 hours.
Makes 12 (1/2-inch) slices.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix bread crumbs, raisins and cinnamon.
Beat eggs; add sugar. Beat again.
Scald milk; add egg mixture and cook until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Pour over bread crumbs; mix well.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook rice exactly 14 minutes in water.
Remove from stove and add sugar and dry jello.
Mix and let cool.
When cooled, add pineapple and juice and Dream Whip.
Prepare the Dream Whip as directed on box.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken cacciatore(an easy crowd pleaser that my family enjoys.)
directions: Wash chicken breasts and pat dry.
Coat with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown with sausage for 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients to skillet and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve over hot noodles with hot garlic bread and a rich red wine.

title: play dough
directions: Stir over medium heat until a ball starts to form.
Knead a little.
Add more flour so it's not too sticky.
Now, have fun!

title: heavenly salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and cool until it begins to set. Add remaining ingredients and mold.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Combine ingredients.
Stir well.
Batter will be slightly lumpy.
Grease muffin cups.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: ham and cheese finger sandwiches
directions: Blend butter, Worcestershire sauce, onion and mustard.
Spread on split rolls. Add ham and cheese.
Replace top.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake in a
400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
May be frozen before baking for future use.

title: grandma thomans italian spaghetti
directions: Cook medium box of thin spaghetti until soft.
In skillet, brown bacon and onion.
Pour grease, bacon and onion into spaghetti.
Add whole tomatoes.
Add to taste salt, pepper, sugar, garlic salt and chili pepper.
Let stand at least 1 hour for flavor to mingle.
Better to stand for hours, even overnight!

title: surprise pie
directions: Separate sandwich cookies and place in pie plate, filling up bottom and sides with cookies.
Mix pudding according to package; fold in sour cream.
Put a layer of pudding on top of cookies. Slice banana on top of pudding.
Add remaining pudding.
Garnish with strawberries or other fresh fruit.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: ice cream(no cooking)
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Ice in freezer, electric or crank freezer using 1 box table salt.

title: louise bush's caramel corn
directions: Cook brown sugar, butter and corn syrup over medium heat until bubbles appear around the outside of the pan.
Cook 5 minutes more.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Pour over popcorn and toss to coat.
Bake 1 hour at 200°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie with squash and potato topping
directions: Drop squash and potatoes into large pot with enough cold, salted water to cover vegetables by 1 inch.
Partially cover and bring to boiling.
Boil 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain squash and potatoes; return to pot.
Add butter, cream, milk, salt, pepper, nutmeg and red pepper.
Mash with potato masher until fluffy.
Cool slightly.
Reserve egg and paprika.
Preheat oven to moderate (375°).
Prepare Filling.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Stir all ingredients together until well blended.
Chill. Serve in small dessert bowls.
Great for summer picnics!

title: p k's taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger until very crisp.
Chill. Toss with remaining ingredients.

title: shrimp and cheese casserole
directions: Break bread in pieces the size of a quarter.
Break cheese into bite size pieces.
Arrange shrimp, bread and cheese in layers in greased casserole.
Pour margarine over this.
Beat eggs.
Add mustard and pinch of salt to eggs, then add milk.
Pour mixture over ingredients in casserole.
Let stand 3 hours or overnight in refrigerator, covered.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, covered.

title: pineapple sour cream pie
directions: Combine pudding mix (dry), pineapple with juice, sour cream and sugar in bowl.
Beat slowly with mixer at lowest speed for 1 minutes or until fully mixed.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill about 3 hours.
Garnish with prepared whipped topping.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine and use for basting meats.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Have a skillet or a griddle hot.
Drop by large spoonfuls.
Turn over when they bubble on top.

title: baked rice pudding
directions: Add all ingredients.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 325° for about 2 hours, or until rice is tender.
Stir occasionally.

title: red devil's food cake
directions: Combine sugar and cream, lard or butter; beat well.
Add cocoa and hot water, flour and soda, beating all the time.
Add egg last. Bake in loaf pan or layer pan.

title: uncooked tomato relish
directions: Scald tomatoes, remove skins and as many seeds as possible, chop into small pieces, should make about 3-quart chopped tomatoes.
Put celery, peppers and onions through food chopper, using coarse grind, use finest grind for horseradish.
Combine vegetables and salt; let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Drain thoroughly in a strainer.
Add sugar, spices, mustard seed and vinegar; mix well.
Pack in hot jars and store in refrigerator. Keep for several months.
Do not store at room temperature.
Makes about 4 quarts.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Melt butter.
Add marshmallows and melt, stirring constantly. Pour over popped popcorn.
Stir together.
Form balls.
Rub hands with butter so popcorn mixture won't stick to you.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine ingredients.
Roll into walnut size balls and freeze. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 40 to 50 balls.

title: penne and chicken
directions: Boil the penne.
Saute diced chicken breasts in olive oil. Add the peppers which have been thinly sliced and the garlic. Cook together until tender.
Add the tomato sauce and black olives along with the chicken stock, thyme, rosemary, salt and pepper. Cook for a few minutes.
Add the cooked pasta, stir and serve.

title: winter fruit dish
directions: Drain and reserve juice from oranges and pineapple.
Add enough water to measure 3 1/2 cups liquid.
Pour into a saucepan. Add dry tapioca and bring to a boil.

title: "dried beef" cheese ball
directions: Tear dried beef and put in blender.
With 1/2 of the dried beef, add all remaining ingredients.
Form ball.
Roll ball in the remaining dried beef.
Store in refrigerator and serve with assorted crackers.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Combine soups, broth and tomatoes.
Blend until smooth.
Place a layer of tortillas in well-greased casserole dish.
Add layer of chicken and sprinkle on onions.
Use 1/2 of soup mixture and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake in covered dish at 325° for 1 hour. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: date balls
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients for 10 minutes, stirring constantly. When cool, add remaining ingredients.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in powdered sugar or coconut.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in pie shell.
Bake until done.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mash bananas to creamy, add to yogurt in small mixing bowl. Blend in lemon juice, brown sugar and vanilla.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Serve with variety of fresh sliced fruit.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Bring to a boil meat, onions and water.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 2 hours, until meat falls from bones.
Remove meat from broth.
Reserve broth.
Refrigerate.
Bone and shred meat (small).
Skim fat from cooled broth.

title: caramel corn
directions: Spread popcorn in large pan; may need to use two.
In heavy saucepan, mix sugar, margarine, syrup and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stir constantly until mix boils.
Continue cooking without stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and soda.
Pour syrup mix over popcorn.
Stir to coat well.
Bake at 250°
for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Break apart when cool.

title: ranch burgers
directions: Mix well. Form into 4 patties and grill or broil until done. Serves 4.

title: scotch-a-roo's cookies
directions: Place sugar and Karo in pan; bring to rolling boil.
Add peanut butter and mix.
Place cereal in a large bowl that has been buttered.
Pour syrup mixture over cereal and mix well.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Layer in pan:
crumbled cornbread, red kidney beans, vegetables (onions, green peppers, corn, cucumbers and peas, for example).
Mix sweet pickle juice and mayonnaise to a thin mixture.
Pour over top of cornbread mixture.
Top with cheese. Cover and let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: fat free zucchini casserole
directions: Slice zucchini; chop onion.
Steam until tender.
Add a few shakes of Molly McButter.
Combine this with the cream cheese in a casserole dish.
Top with crumbled potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Crush pretzels, and mix with melted butter and sugar.
Press in bottom of 8 1/2x11 inch baking dish.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 8 minutes.
Make sure it cooks completely.
Mix cream cheese, cool whip, and powdered sugar.
Spread over cooled pretzels.
Boil water, and mix in Jello.
Add pineapple and strawberries.
Let cool and pour over cream cheese layer. Refrigerate.
Cut into squares and serve.
Serves 4-6.

title: chicken-artichoke casserole
directions: Can use chicken breasts with ribs.
Simmer 1/2 hour and remove skin and bones.
Then continue with recipe.

title: tacos
directions: Stir-fry ground beef, garlic, salt and pepper until meat is browned.
Take the taco shells and place 1 1/2 tablespoons of meat mixture on each.
Next, add sour cream, then onions, lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.
Last of all, add the sauce.
Ready to eat. Makes 16.

title: caramel fondue
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Stir in sugar and syrup. Bring to a boil over medium heat. Stir in milk. Simmer on medium to low heat to 230° or soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and pour into fondue pot.
Heat.
Use fruit pieces for dip.

title: winter delights
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients for 3 minutes; take off stove. Put in the uncooked oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir well; drop onto foil or wax paper.

title: old fashioned spice cake
directions: Mix 1 1/3 cups evaporated milk and vinegar; reserve remaining milk for frosting.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or 2 round 8 or 9-inch pans.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add taco sauce and refried beans and heat through.
Bake salad shells according to package directions.
Top shells with all the fixings you like.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Pour into large casserole. Spread over top,
grated sharp Cheddar cheese.
Melt margarine and mix with Cheese Nips.
Put this over cheese.
Top with package of slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: ranch beans
directions: Fry ground beef and drain.
Mix next 7 ingredients in bowl. Add hamburger and onion.
Pour into greased shallow dish.
Top with pieces of raw bacon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: texas pie
directions: Cream oleo and sugar together; add eggs, one at a time. Add pineapple, coconut, flour, meal and vanilla; mix well and pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Makes 2 deep dish or 3 regular pies.

title: picadillo
directions: In a large skillet, saute garlic, onions, green pepper and capers in a small amount of cooking oil until translucent. Gradually add crumbled ground beef.
Stir, so it browns slightly. Add tomatoes (these may be cut up, if desired), oregano, salt, pepper, olives, raisins and vinegar.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Skim off excess grease.
Serve with rice and black beans.

title: pear salad
directions: Drain juice from pears and heat until boils.
Remove from stove and add Jell-O.
Cool juice and Jell-O 5 minutes.
Put in blender and add cream cheese and blend, then add pears; blend and add Cool Whip and blend.
Pour out in Tupperware bowl and refrigerate.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Tear tortillas in bite size chunks.
Line bottom of casserole dish with layer of tortillas.
Add layer of meat sauce and layer of cheese.
Continue to layer until all ingredients are gone. Last layer should be cheese.
Jalapenos may be added.

title: biscotti
directions: Make puddings as directed.
Layer anisette toast in glass dish.
Cover with hot chocolate pudding.
Add nuts and cherries. Layer a second layer of anisette toast. Pour hot vanilla pudding over this.
Then more nuts and cherries.
Add third layer of anisette toast.
Seal tightly with foil.
Leave in fridge 4 to 5 days to set.
Serve cold with Cool Whip.

title: cream pie
directions: If desired, add 1/2 cup well-drained pineapple.

title: sweet and sour pineapple
directions: Drain juice from pineapple into saucepan.
Put pineapple in large jar with cover.
Add sugar, vinegar, cloves, allspice and cinnamon sticks to juice and cook until mixture comes to full boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour over pineapple in jar, cover and cool to room temperature.
Refrigerate.
Serve with sour cream for dipping.
(Must be made at least 24 hours ahead.)

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken and remove bones.
Cut into small pieces Marinate overnight in French dressing.

title: miracle cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add lemon juice and cool. Cream together cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add gelatin and mix well.
Fold whipped milk into gelatin mixture.
Mix crushed graham crackers and oleo.
Pack firmly 2/3 of mixture in bottom and sides of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Add filling and remaining crumbs on top.
Chill 4 hours.

title: butter nut chewies
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs until light and foamy.
Beat in sugar, vanilla and Crisco until creamy.
In a separate bowl, combine flour with baking powder and salt.
Add dry mixture to the egg mixture.
Beat at low speed until blended.
Stir in nuts at low speed.
Spread evenly in greased 9x13 pan.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients, except cheese and peppers.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into greased iron skillet.
Sprinkle 1/2 of cheese and peppers over mixture.
Pour remaining mixture in skillet and top with remaining cheese and peppers.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pecan pralines(new orleans style)
directions: Note: For flavors, use maple, chocolate or vanilla.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine mashed pumpkin, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add flour, salt, soda, allspice, cinnamon, ginger, nuts and dates; mix well. Grease and flour 4 (1 pound) coffee cans.
Fill each half full of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Allow to cool. Cover can with plastic lid.
Let mellow 24 hours.
Can be frozen in cans.
Makes 4 loaves.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Cook almonds and sugar over low heat, stirring constantly until sugar is melted and almonds are coated.
Cool and break apart.
Store at room temperature.
Place lettuce and romaine in plastic bag; add celery and onions.
Pour sweet and sour dressing into bag; add orange segments.
Close bag tightly and shake until salad greens and orange segments are well coated.
Add almonds and shake.
Greens may be stored for 24 hours before adding dressing.

title: squash casserole
directions: Heat milk.
Add margarine and pour over bread crumbs.
Mix well and add to squash.
Add cheese and seasonings.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Pour into greased casserole and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fish batter
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then dip fish pieces into batter.
Drop in hot oil.
Fish will drop to the bottom and float to the top to brown in about 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove and drain.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients real good.
Bake in balls for 15 minutes at 400°.
These can be frozen in balls and taken out to cook as needed.

title: 5 layer casserole
directions: Layer
potatoes, beef, onions, peppers and Spanish rice in
a 2
quart
casserole.
Season
each	layer with salt and pepper. Garnish
with
sliced pepper.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Beat in sugar until thick and lemon colored, then beat in oil and vanilla; add nuts.
Combine flour, salt, cinnamon and baking powder in separate bowl.
Stir in dry ingredients alternately with grated zucchini. Pour into two large greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until done.
Freezes well.

title: mexican cornbread casserole
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and soda.
Stir in cornmeal.
Add eggs, onion, peppers, corn and buttermilk.
Brown meat; drain. Add taco seasoning and a little water.
Cook until almost dry.

title: hot fudge
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in microwave for 2 1/2 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and microwave for another 1 minute and 15 seconds. Serve warm over ice cream.

title: baby food cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs along with flour. Add baby food and oil, and blend well.
Spices or nuts may be added if desired.
Bake in tube pan for one hour at 350 degrees.

title: poulet au porto(chicken with port cream)
directions: In a wide frying pan over medium heat, melt butter.
Add chicken and cook until all sides are browned (about 20 minutes). Combine Port and cream and pour over chicken.
