Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer until meat near thigh bone is no longer pink (about 30 minutes).

title: broccoli, chicken, rice casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except cheese.
Put into casserole dish; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° about 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is golden brown.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and Crisco.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa together.
Alternately add sifted flour mixture and milk to creamed mixture; mix thoroughly. Add vanilla.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake in 325° preheated oven for 80 minutes.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars together.
Add milk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix.
Add sifted dry ingredients and stir.
Mix in oats, coconut, chips and flakes.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Remove to racks to cool. Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat 3/4 cup sugar into egg yolks.
Stir in milk slowly.
Cook in double boiler, stirring constantly, until coats spoon.
Chill.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Cook and stir beef and onion until brown.
Drain; add salt and pepper.
Spread into lightly greased 10-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth (15 seconds in blender or 1 minute with hand mixer).
Pour into pie plate. Bake at 400° until golden brown and knife inserted comes out clean, about 30 minutes.
Garnish with slices of tomato and parsley.

title: no. 2 pilgrims progress non-alcoholic drink
directions: Mix juices in a large pitcher; pour over ice.
Garnish with lemon slices.
Serves 3.

title: chinese new year cookies
directions: Melt chocolate and caramel pieces over hot water.
Mix noodles and nuts.
Stir into melted mixture. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper. Chill. Yields about 4 dozen cookies.

title: hot jezebel
directions: Combine ingredients; pour over 8 ounce pack of cream cheese and serve with crackers.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut potatoes into lengthwise pieces and arrange loosely on pan sprayed with Pam; salt and pepper potatoes. Bake 1 hour and turn to brown on all sides (turn over every 15 minutes).
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Stew fryer or white meat until done; debone and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine 2 cups chicken broth from stewing and the mushroom soup.
Bring to boil and pour over chicken.
Prepare batter; dip over chicken by spoonfuls.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: golden layer cake
directions: Sift flour, cornstarch, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add Crisco, milk and extract.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs and beat 2 more minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Check for doneness with a toothpick.

title: graham corn bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, then increase heat to 375° for 30 minutes.

title: day ahead noodle lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce; mix well. Add tomatoes, tomato paste, spaghetti sauce, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Simmer all together.
Shred Mozzarella cheese. Layer in two 9 x 13-inch pans or 1 large lasagne pan.
Cover bottom with meat sauce, then dry noodles, meat sauce and shredded cheese.
Repeat process once.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Refrigerate overnight and bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: spice cake
directions: Mix everything well.
Put in a greased pan.
Bake in the oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pretzel mix
directions: Mix oil, ranch dressing mix and garlic powder.	Pour over pretzels, nuts and Chex Mix.
Stir every 10-15 minutes until oil is absorbed.
Store in sealed zip-lock bag or plastic container.

title: easy sweet potato pie
directions: While sweet potatoes are still warm, place all ingredients in a blender.
Blend well and pour into a 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes and then 30 to 35 minutes on 350°.
Very low in cholesterol.

title: anna's easy lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large pan, brown meat mixing together.
Add whole jar Ragu sauce and water into meat.
Take off stove.
In 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish, put approximately half meat sauce.
Begin layering uncooked lasagna noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella, then meat sauce and repeat layering, ending with cheese.
Sprinkle remaining cheeses on top.
Cover completely with foil.
Bake 1 hour.
My favorite add-in, sauteed button mushrooms.

title: mom's fresh apple fruit cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar; add eggs and beat well. Add flour, salt, cinnamon, soda and vanilla. Beat well. Fold in apples, walnuts and raisins. Pour into tube pan that has been greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. If oven bakes hot, put on 325°.

title: green beans with bacon
directions: Trim beans and cook in boiling salted water until tender, about 10 minutes.
Drain.
Cut bacon into approximately 1-inch pieces.
Cook in large frying pan until crisp.
Remove bacon with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons bacon fat.
Add beans to frying pan.
Stir over medium heat until heated through.
Stir in bacon, pepper and lemon juice.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, shortening and milk.
Cream together; add flavoring.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake in a 350° oven until springs back.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Mix and bake cake mix in oblong cake pan according to package directions.
While cake is hot, poke full of holes.
With fork, mix together cream of coconut and Eagle Brand milk and pour over hot cake.
Let cool.
Top with Cool Whip, then top with shredded coconut.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Saute celery and onions in margarine.
Add stuffing mix, reserving 5 Tbsp.
Add balance of ingredients.
Mix and place in 3 qt. casserole or 9x13-inch baking pan.
Add parmesan cheese to reserved 5 Tbsp. stuffing (add paprika liberally if desired). Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar and corn syrup. Bring to a full boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda, vanilla and butter extract.
Mixture will appear foamy.

title: ham and vegetable casserole
directions: Cook frozen vegetables and ham until done.
Mix all ingredients well and place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and add next 4 ingredients to mixture.
Top with slivered almonds and bake, uncovered, 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: stew(beef or chicken)
directions: Cut chicken or beef into bite size pieces.
Marinate chicken or beef with onion, salt and pepper.
Heat oil in skillet.
Saute meat.
Add tomato paste, about 2 tablespoons to 2 pounds of meat. Let cook over medium heat for about 15 minutes.
Add potato and 1 cup of water.
Cook until meat is tender.

title: brown bread
directions: Mix 4 cups warm water, yeast, 1/2 cup brown sugar and salt. Then add whole-wheat flour, then let set around 40 minutes.
Then add 1 cup warm water, oil, 3/4 cup brown sugar, honey and white flour.
Knead well.
Let rise until double.
Knead again and let rise again.
Fold into 6 loaves.
Let rise and bake 30 minutes or until golden brown at 325°.

title: hamburg dumpling stew
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients into small cakes.
Brown on both sides in deep kettle.
Lift out meat cakes.
Blend 1 tablespoon flour with chili sauce, tomato soup and hot water.
Bring to boil and add cakes.

title: ham and stuff impossible pie
directions: Grease a quiche pan or 10-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle meat, mushrooms and onions in bottom of pan.
Mix milk, Bisquick and eggs together and pour over ingredients in pan.
Sprinkle cheese over the top.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes until brown and set.

title: french fried eggplant
directions: Slice and peel eggplant.
Beat eggs, salt and pepper together.
Dip eggplant in egg mixture, then in cracker crumbs. Redip in each.
Fry in butter until tender.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses, mixing until well blended.
Add other ingredients and chill.
Mold into ball and roll in nuts on waxed paper.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Put on stove to thicken the sugar, water and cornstarch.
Cool slightly.
Add dry jello; stir to dissolve.
Cool and pour over strawberries in pie shell.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix chicken, sour cream, soup and lemon juice together.
Place in 3-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle crackers and poppy seed on top.
Melt margarine and dribble on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese grits(breakfast)
directions: Cook grits as directed on box.
Remove from heat.
Add one stick of butter, stir till melted.
Then add cheese, chilies, salt, worcestershire, eggs.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 350 for 1 hour.

title: pork chops and sauerkraut
directions: Place chops in casserole.
Put in apples, onion and kraut. Place in a 350° oven.
Cook for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Cover with lid or foil while cooking.

title: ratatouille
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and grease a large shallow casserole. Slice zucchini, celery and green pepper and cube eggplant.
Blanch in salted water, boiling water, until barely tender.
Drain and reserve.

title: diabetic pineapple cookies
directions: Sift flour, cinnamon, soda and salt together.
Cut in oleo. Mix together like pie crust.
Stir in raisins.
Combine egg, pineapple juice and sweetener.
Drop by tablespoons onto cookie sheet.
Sprinkle coconut on each cookie and press with back of fork so they will be level.
Bake at 300° or 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cottage cheese loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except Special K.
Mix in Special K with a large spoon.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or microwave, covered, on High 17 to 19 minutes.

title: mexican soup
directions: Brown meat and onions in Dutch oven on medium heat.
Add all other ingredients.
When hot, cut heat back to low and simmer (very low); let simmer for at least 3 to 4 hours.
Serve with cornbread or thin tortilla chips, breaking a few at a time on top of soup when served.

title: texas chewies
directions: Blend all ingredients and bake in lightly greased 8X8 pan at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until top is golden brown. Cool and cut into squares.

title: frozen peanut butter pie(yields three 8-inch pies)
directions: Cream the cream cheese and peanut butter together.
Add milk and vanilla to cream cheese/peanut butter mixture and blend until smooth.
Add powdered sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crusts.
Squeeze chocolate syrup in lines over top and swirl through gently with a knife.
Freeze.

title: pea salad
directions: Fry
bacon; let cool.
Chop up one head of lettuce; add one package
of frozen peas.
Chop up the six eggs and bacon. Mix
all together in a bowl. Add mayonnaise (however much you like); stir.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple together. Add marshmallows, Cool Whip and nuts. Mix well and chill. Can be frozen.

title: mexican chili
directions: Melt Crisco in large skillet and brown onion, green pepper and ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients, stir and cook over low heat, 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: ambrosia supreme
directions: Mix well.
Pour into rectangular pan.
Bake at 300° until brown.
Cool.
Roll into small balls, then roll in powdered sugar.

title: molasses pudding
directions: Beat eggs firm.
Add molasses, sugar and bacon drippings. Stir until well mixed.
Add 2 cups of self-rising flour, allspice, a dash of salt and water.
Mix all ingredients well.
Beat about 10 minutes.
Pour into greased baking pan or cake pan.
Cook about 15 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix together butter, flour and nuts. Press into Pyrex dish. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: cocktail franks
directions: Heat jelly and mustard until melted.
Add franks and refrigerate overnight.
Heat when ready to serve.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter until tender. Stir in soup. Gradually blend in milk and cook until bubbly. Stir frequently. Add cheese to soup mixture.
Heat and stir until melted.
Stir moderate amount of cheese mixture into beaten eggs. Return to hot mixture. Cook until bubbly. Add crab and spices.
Keep warm (with fondue pot or small crockette).
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: quick barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and cook for 30 minutes over slow heat.

title: broccoli-raisin salad
directions: Chop broccoli and onion.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to broccoli and onion.
Toss to mix.
Refrigerate.
Serve cold.

title: cocoa pink cuplets
directions: Sift together flour with cocoa.
Add sugar gradually to shortening, creaming well.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Combine soda and cold water.
Add alternately with dry ingredients to creamed mixture beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Blend thoroughly after each addition.
Use low speed with electric mixer.
Fill muffin pans half full.
Sprinkle 1 cup chocolate pieces and nuts over cupcake batter.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: orange roughy oriental
directions: Cut fish into 4 servings; place in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Top with combined vegetables.
Combine soy sauce, oil, sherry, ginger root and orange peel.
Pour over fish and vegetables. Cover; marinate in refrigerator 20 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork. Remove fish and vegetables to serving platter.
Keep warm. Gradually add marinade from baking dish to yogurt in small saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until warm. Serve sauce with fish.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Add more raisins, if desired. Will refrigerate for 3 weeks.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix salmon, bread crumbs, egg yolks, onion, lemon juice and milk.
Beat egg
whites
and
fold	into
mixture.	Put in casserole dish and bake 1 hour at 350° or until firm.

title: african chicken(eating light)
directions: In large skillet, heat oil over high temperature.
Add chicken and brown, turning, on all sides.
Remove and discard all but 2 tablespoons oil.
Reduce heat to low and add onion.
Cook, uncovered, about 5 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, eggs add 1/2 c. melted butter with mixer and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Mix brown sugar, pecans, flour and 1/2 c. melted butter.
Sprinkle on top of casserole mixture.
Bake at 325 degrees for 30 mins.

title: tuna delight
directions: Saute onion in oil in skillet until tender.
Add rice and green beans; mix well.
Stir in tuna and mushroom soup.
Cook until heated thoroughly.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
Drain the meat and mix in the remaining ingredients (including all liquids).
Let simmer in large pot until flavors blend together, about 30 minutes. Makes 12 servings (approximately 1 cup each).

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat first three ingredients in saucepan; bring to boil. Remove from heat and add flour; mix well.
Add 1 egg at a time to mixture; mix thoroughly.
Drop batter on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 400° until puffed.

title: easy and delicious
directions: Bake according to directions in cookie sheet pan.

title: homemade chicken soup
directions: In a large pot, filled with water, place chicken.
Allow to boil.
Remove surface film, reduce heat and add remaining ingredients.
On a low heat, cook for approximately 3 hours.

title: ice cream punch
directions: Have pineapple juice and ginger ale chilled until ready to add ice cream and sherbet, which have softened slightly.

title: quail on toast
directions: Cook the butter and flour in saucepan for 2 minutes.
Add the milk and mace until you have a smooth, creamy sauce.
Stir into this the quail.
Heat thoroughly.
Add salt and paprika.
Put generously on toasted slices of bread.
Place shredded pimento on top and serve on a platter.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour and salt gradually.
Stir in vanilla and crushed pineapple.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan or two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans for 1 hour or until done at 350°.

title: easy cherry pie
directions: Mix together first 2 ingredients until fluffy.
Add whipped cream.
Pour into baked crust and put cherry pie filling on top.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and remove stems of mushrooms.
Mix cream cheese and deviled ham.
Fill caps of mushrooms with mixture.
Broil 5 to 6 minutes or until heated and browned.

title: dressing
directions: Mix all together and put in a large jelly roll pan or large casserole.
Bake for 1 hour or until browned and firm.

title: chicken and hoisin sauce
directions: Place chicken cubes in bowl and sprinkle with cornstarch.
Pour in sherry and soy sauce and toss.
Heat wok and pour in 1 tablespoon oil; heat until hot.
Add green peppers, water chestnuts, mushrooms and salt.
Stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove and set aside.
Pour remaining oil in wok.
Heat and add marinated chicken.
Stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes.
Add hoisin sauce, stirring well.
Add vegetables.
Add almonds and stir to heat through.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine; add cooked broccoli, cooked rice, soup and cheese.
Season to taste.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° until bubbles.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Add bananas, butter and milk. Beat on low speed until blended, then on high speed for 2 minutes. Add eggs and remaining flour; beat until blended. Stir in nuts. Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: In a saucepan, cook beef, onion and garlic over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain.
In a slow cooker, combine the remaining ingredients.
Stir in beef mixture.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 9 hours or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 10 servings.

title: spicy apple juice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart pitcher.
Chill and serve.

title: infamous potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on until fork tender.
Drain, cool, peel and cut potatoes into bite size pieces.
Chop onion and add to potatoes.
Mix oil, vinegar, salt and pepper together and pour over potatoes and onions.
Stir thoroughly to coat potato mixture. Let sit at room temperature for a few hours.
Just before serving, add chopped eggs, mayonnaise to coat mixture, stir well and serve.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine sugar, flour and baking soda.
In a saucepan, melt together on low heat the water, margarine and cocoa. Pour over flour mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch jelly roll pan.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Sift flour in a bowl.
Add flour and milk, starting with flour and ending with flour.
Add flavoring and coconut.
Pour in a greased and floured 9-inch tube pan. Place in a cold oven on 350° and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain well.
Cook Minute rice.
Warm soups and cheese together.
Mix broccoli, rice and soup mixture.
Pour in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy chicken stir-fry
directions: Pour oil into wok, coating bottom and sides.
Heat to medium high (325°) for 2 minutes.
Add chicken and almonds; stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add vegetables; cover and cook for 4 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine soy sauce, pineapple juice and cornstarch; add to vegetables and chicken.
Cook for 2 minutes, or until thick.
Serve over hot rice.

title: sandy's beans
directions: Brown hamburger; drain fat.
Throw hamburger and all other ingredients in a crock-pot.
Stir well; cover and cook on low 4 to 6 hours.
Feeds many.

title: joanie's potato salad
directions: Peel and boil potatoes in saltwater. Boil eggs separately. Drain potatoes. Peel eggs and rinse. Put potatoes (cut up) in large bowl. Add chopped eggs. Add pickle relish, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, celery powder, onion powder, salt, olives and mayonnaise. Add more of any of the seasonings for your own taste. Add more mayonnaise if not moist enough.

title: easy 1-2-3 cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour into small 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Add fruit.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: red pepper dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well.
Best if chilled overnight.
Garnish with chives.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix and press into long casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool completely and press down in bottom of dish.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Mix all together and pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: jim smith's tea cakes
directions: Stir together using a spoon the sugar, margarine, baking soda, lemon flavoring and eggs.
Then add flour, two cups at a time.

title: granny's chili
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion, spices, tomatoes and juice.
Add water until pot is 3/4 full; simmer for almost 2 hours on low.
Add pork and beans in the last 20 minutes of cooking.
(Never boil the chili, only simmer.)
Good with saltines and iced tea.

title: pea saladgroves, texas
directions: Prepare vegetables while the peas and beans drain, marinate with the following:
1 Tbsp. salt, 3/4 c. sugar, 1/4 c. corn oil and 1/4 c. vinegar.

title: sausage-corn skillet
directions: Crumble sausage into large skillet.
Add green pepper and onion.
Cook over medium heat until sausage is browned, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and drain off fat.
Stir in corn, tomato, garlic, basil and pepper.
Return to heat.
Cover and cook until heated throughout, 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pumpkin-orange chiffon pie
directions: For filling, stir together 1/2 cup sugar, gelatin and spice in a saucepan.
Beat together egg yolks and milk.
Add to saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Stir in pumpkin, orange peel and juice.
Chill until partially set.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Gradually add remaining sugar and beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold into pumpkin mixture.
Pour into prepared pie shell.
Chill until firm, at least 6 hours.
Serve with sweetened whipped cream, garnish with grated orange peel.

title: lasagne
directions: Note:
Measurements are approximate and can be modified to taste.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix first 5 dry ingredients together in large bowl, then make a well in center.
Add liquids.
Mix well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Use your favorite icing.

title: creamy onion dip
directions: Combine in small bowl and cover and chill.
May substitute low-fat yogurt for sour cream.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All and water chestnuts.
Add mayonnaise and chicken soup.
Blend well.	Add onion.
Blend again.
Pour ingredients into greased casserole.	Top casserole with mixture of cheese, cracker crumbs and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: mom's easy chile
directions: Saute together the ground beef, onion and celery.
Place beef mixture in a crock-pot along with the tomato sauce, soup, chile, pepper and chili powder.
Add water (by rinsing the 3 cans) to the crock-pot.
Simmer all day on low.

title: rice krispies marshmallow treats
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Add peanut butter and stir well, cooking 3 to 4 minutes more.
Remove from heat. Add Rice Krispies and stir until well coated.
Press into margarine coated 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top and when slightly melted, swirl around to frost.

title: chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients together. Stir until all ingredients are mixed well. Pour in a 9-inch pie shell. Cool for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: *Cook Rice-a-Roni as directed on the box.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick.
Place first 5 ingredients in top of double boiler, stirring constantly.
Slice bananas and place wafers in a baking dish; repeat.
Pour mixture over.
Beat egg whites until thick, adding sugar.
Brown in oven.

title: blackberry frozen yogurt(low calorie)
directions: Thaw berries if frozen. In a medium saucepan add sugar and gelatin; stir in milk and 1/4 cup water. Heat just until gelatin dissolves. Set aside to cool. In food processor bowl, process berries until smooth. Press through sieve; discard berries. Stir puree, yogurt, orange peel and juice into gelatin mixture. Then pour into 9X5X3 inch pan. Cover. Freeze about 6 hours. Break into chunks. Put in bowl to chill. Beat with mixer, until smooth but not melted. Return to cold loaf pan to freeze for about 8 hours.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside. Combine dry ingredients; mix well. Cut in shortening with the yeast and dry ingredients until mixture resembles coarse mix. Add buttermilk to mixture. Mix well. Turn out on floured surface; knead about 2 minutes. Roll or pat out and cut into biscuits. Bake in 400° oven for about 15 minutes.

title: easy pork chop italiano
directions: Brush pork chops generously with salad dressing.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; coat with crushed croutons.
Place pork chops on a rack in a shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Layer bottom of a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan (glass) with 1/3 graham crackers.
In bowl beat pudding mix with milk, add cream cheese and fold in whipped topping.
Spread half of pudding mixture over crackers.
Repeat layers, ending with graham crackers on top.
Spread with chocolate topping.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients and marinate in refrigerator for 3 to 4 days.
Turn chicken wings everyday.
Bake, uncovered, in shallow baking pan for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients, keeping blueberries for last.
Place in sprayed (greased) muffin pans.
Bake at 375° until golden brown, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tex-mex casserole
directions: Cook hash browns according to package directions and place in an ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In a large skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Pour salsa over beef and cook for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Place beef mixture into the middle of the hash browns.
Sprinkle cheese over all.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and drain.
Cook rice until done and drain.
Saute onions in margarine.
Combine all other ingredients, saving 1/2 cup cheese.

title: wynona's noodle and rice
directions: Brown noodles in margarine.
Add 2 cans chicken and rice soup, two cans of water, onion dip and mushrooms.
Mix thoroughly. Bring to a boil and add Minute rice.
Cover and turn off heat.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well, make a small ball, put on a greased cookie sheet.
Flatten balls with fingers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until light brown.

title: one-dish meal
directions: Brown beef, onions and celery in fat.
Place in 2 1/2-quart buttered casserole.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: grandma chokel's potato soup
directions: Prepare potatoes, onions and celery.
Place in kettle.
Add water, salt and pepper.
Cover and turn heat to high.
When it starts to boil, turn heat down and simmer.
Cook about 15 minutes. Then add milk and bring almost to a boil again, using high heat.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Crushed potato chips are good on top.

title: green pepper steak
directions: With a very sharp knife, cut beef across the grain into thin strips.
Combine soy sauce, garlic, ginger and beef.
Toss and set aside while preparing the vegetables.

title: exquisite pie
directions: Combine all ingredients listed.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until set.

title: cake frosting
directions: Make paste with milk and flour.
Let cool.
Put in refrigerator.
Beat margarine and Crisco for 4 minutes.
Add sugar.
Beat 4 more minutes.
Add paste and vanilla.
Beat 4 more minutes.

title: peach jam
directions: Combine peaches, orange juice and Sure-Jell.
Bring to boil. Add sugar.
Boil 1 minute.
Skim with metal spoon.
Stir 7 minutes. Put into sterilized jars and seal with paraffin.

title: death by chocolate cake
directions: Cook cake by directions and cool.
Mix pudding.
Keep Cool Whip thawed, but not frozen.
In a punch bowl, crumble cake to form layer, then add thin layer of pudding.
Add thin layer of Cool Whip and repeat layers until Cool Whip ends on top.
Grate chocolate bar and sprinkle over top.
Chill in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: walnut turtles
directions: Cover cookie sheets with waxed paper and arrange nut pieces in clusters (about 28 to 30 clusters) spaced about 1 inch apart.

title: huevos acapulco
directions: Beat eggs until light; combine with rest of ingredients.
Stir chilies in last.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve Ortega green chili salsa on the side.

title: bread pudding
directions: Blend water and milk.
Add eggs.
Blend salt, vanilla and sugar; stir into milk.
Add raisins and butter.
Mix in bread only until moist (do not overmix).
Pour into well-greased 13 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until browned.
Use toothpick test for doneness.
While warm, drizzle with sauce.

title: linguini with mixed vegetables
directions: Blanch carrots for 3 minutes in boiling water.
Blanch zucchini for 1 minute.
Rinse in cold water and drain.
Set aside. In a separate saucepan, cook linguini in boiling water according to package directions.
Rinse under cold running water, then drain and set aside.
In a skillet, melt butter and cook garlic and green onion until soft.
Add carrots and zucchini and saute for 3 minutes.
Add basil, parsley and spinach.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour vegetable juice and tomatoes into mixture and heat. Fold in linguine.
Stir and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cranberry salad *
directions: Mix cherry Jell-O according to directions on box.
Peel apples and chop.
Peel oranges and chop sections.
Mix apples and oranges with nuts and whole berry cranberry sauce.
Combine this with the cherry Jell-O.
Pour into mold and let it congeal.
Can be served on a lettuce leaf, if desired.

title: bubble bread(use a bundt cake pan)
directions: Remove frozen bread from freezer at night and place in refrigerator and let rise until double in size.
Melt butter in small pan, being careful not to brown.
Combine sugar and cinnamon in small bowl.
Break walnut size pieces of bread dough off.
Roll in butter, then in sugar mixture.
Place in rows in bottom of well-greased Bundt cake pan.
After bottom is covered, sprinkle 1/2 cup nuts on top.
Put second layer of bread dough over nuts until all is used up.
Pour on remaining butter; top with remaining sugar mixture.
Sprinkle remaining nuts on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool, right side up, 5 minutes and turn out on plate.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Pour into three 9 x 12-inch loaf pans, greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Freezes well, if desired.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour and water alternately.
Add flavoring. Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: apricot delight
directions: Heat to boiling the gelatin and pineapple.
Add cream cheese, stirring until cheese is melted.
Add sugar and baby food.
Chill until syrupy.
Beat milk until thick.
Fold in chilled mixture. Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Serves 10.

title: chocolate washington pie
directions: Bake devil's food cake in layers as directed.
Cool.
Split one layer in half to make two thin layers.
Spread custard sauce between thin layers.
Cover top with whipped cream and decorate with shaved chocolate.
Serve in wedges.
Serve remaining layer later.

title: teddie's tortissa casserole
directions: Cut tortillas into 1-inch strips and set aside.
Beat eggs, red pepper, salt, sour cream, mushroom soup and milk.
Butter a square Pyrex dish and place 3 layers of tortillas, onion, chicken or turkey, green chili, olives and cheese.
Cover each layer with sour cream mixture and end up with cheese.
Bake, covered, in a 325° oven for about 45 minutes.
This casserole is excellent fresh, but it is not as good warmed.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; beat well.
Add eggs and beat again.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop small balls of dough on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten slightly with the bottom of a glass dipped in sugar (dip glass in sugar before flattening each cookie).
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Should be lightly brown.
Do not overbrown.
Taste is much better if not brown.

title: hello dolly
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Mix in graham cracker crumbs.
Spread.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips, coconut and nuts. Pour condensed milk over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool before cutting.
Can be frozen.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Stir together and put into casserole dish.
Cover with Ritz cracker crumbs and 1 stick melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: biscuit pizza
directions: Put biscuits on plate; put tomato sauce on biscuits.
Place a layer of cheese, 1 pepperoni and then more cheese.
Put in microwave for 30 seconds to 1 minute or until cheese is melted.

title: pearl britton's salad delight
directions: Slice onions thin and separate.
Break lettuce in bite pieces.

title: brownies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured pan at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook noodles. Brown hamburger meat, sausage, green pepper and onion.
Drain.
Add sauce and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
In a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex, put 1 layer of noodles.
Pour meat sauce and cheese.
Repeat 2 more times. End up with cheese on top. I add more cheese. Cook 30 minutes at 300°. Serve with garlic bread and fresh veggies and dip.
